Increased pump speed to 12 bpm while allowing DPP to level off at ICP (4;600 psi). Continued to maintain CP constant at 2;700 psi as DPP dropped as per schedule. Once 13.3 ppg CaBr observed at surface; swapped to active system; then staged down pumps to 6 bpm maintaining CP/DPP at or above BCP of 1;500 psi. After 792 bbls reveresed out; shut down and lined up pumps on HPDU. Continued reversing out 2 additional DP volumes through HPDU. Note: As per Alternative Compliance #9 in the permit: BOP/BSR/Diverter Function Tests and Pressure Test will not be conducted when completion tubulars for Frac Operations are across the BOP. Testing of such BOPE will be conducted once operationally feasible. 11/08/2018: Continued reversing out 2 additional DP volumes through HPDU. Shut down; trapping BCP on the DP and casing. Allowed SITP to stabilize. Stripped up to dump seals and closed MCS. Performed test against system to 500 psi over SITP. Opened LAP and flow checked well - static. Rigged down Frac iron. Laid out Frac head. TOH to 28;428' and made up to TDX (service tool in neutral position). Performed Full System test to 500 psi with the cement unit. TOH 1 stand and slacked off to set ShurMac on lower indicating nipple at Zone 2 with 20k down at 28;378' DPM. Lined up cement unit to pump down the DP. With cement unit; tested seals against MCS on the service tool to 1;500 psi. Rigged up Frac head and iron. Tested to 14;000 psi with Baker frac boat. Performed Zone 2 acid/frac job. Stripped up to Reverse position and reversed out; establishing returns. Once 13.3 ppg CaBr observed at surface; swapped to active system; then staged down pumps maintaining CP/DPP at or above BCP. Shut down trapping BCP of 1;500 psi on the DP/casing. Strip up to dump seals. Did not see indications of seals dumping. Continued to strip up to close MCS. Applied 500 psi to backside; did not see communication between annulus and DP. Applied 4;500 psi down back side with no reaction on DP observed. Bled off pressure and stripped back down to Reverse position. Lined up pumps on HPDU and continued reversing out. Flow check well on trip tank. Well static. Slacked off with 20k down; isolating MCS from annulus. With annular open; applied 500 psi down DP for 5 mins testing MCS - good test; MCS confirmed closed. Rigged down Frac iron and control lines. NOTE: On 11/08/2018 at 15:12 hours; Mr. Adriano Garcia (BSEE) provided Mr. Matt Hensgens (Chevron) an additional 72 hour extension for casing evaluation. Note: As per Alternative Compliance #9 in the permit: BOP/BSR/Diverter Function Tests and Pressure Test will not be conducted when completion tubulars for Frac Operations are across the BOP. Testing of such BOPE will be conducted once operationally feasible. 11/09/2018: Continued rigging down Frac head and laid down same. TOH from 28;114' to 6;248' while testing choke and kill manifold offline. Slip and cut drill line. Note: As per Alternative Compliance #9 in the permit: BOP/BSR/Diverter Function Tests and Pressure Test will not be conducted when completion tubulars for Frac Operations are across the BOP. Testing of such BOPE will be conducted once operationally feasible. 11/10/2018: With service tool mule shoe at 6;248'; continue with slip and cut drill line; made repairs to BlockTilt cylinder on Main Block. Note: As per Alternative Compliance #9 in the permit: BOP/BSR/Diverter Function Tests and Pressure Test will not be conducted when completion tubulars for Frac Operations are across the BOP. Testing of such BOPE will be conducted once operationally feasible.

Tagged lower zone VCH packer at 28;138'. P/U and place TCP guns on depth; R/U surface iron and test. Set packer and apply 500 psi on backside. Perforated upper zones 3; 4 and 5. Pumped 50 bbl HEC pill down the work string and circulated surface to surface. 11/20/2018: Circulated surface to surface at 15 bpm. Pickled work string; RU frac boat and flush/test lines. Pump 580;804 lbs sand - max rate 35 bpm. Reversed out 15;229 lbs sand. Note: BSEE Inspectors Paul Reeves; Clint Campo; Gabe Orellana; Cedric Bernard arrived on ship at 09:00 hrs. Monthly inspection completed with no INCs. Departed ship at 13:00 hrs. 11/21/2018: Continued reversing out DP volume. Dumped seals and closed Zone 3 MCS. Tested MCS integrity. R/D Frac head. Space out service tool in Zone 4. M/U Frac head and lines. Opened MCS and Acidize Zone 4. Performed Main Frac on Zone 4 (pumped 566;766 lbs of sand @ 35 bpm). Strip up to reverse position and circulate 2 DP volumes. Dumped seals and closed Zone 4 MCS. R/D Frac head. Tested MCS integrity. Spaced out service tool in Zone 5 and tested same. M/U Frac head and lines. Obtained P/U and S/O weights and locate WDS position. Closed LAP; applied 500 psi to backside and strip up to reverse position. Broke circulation and filled surface lines. 11/22/2018: Flushed surface lines and pressure tested. Baker Stimulation Vessel Blue Dolphin waiting on inclement weather to pass. Brought in Stimulation Vessel and R/U Frac hose. Calibrated flow meters. P/U and opened MCS (observed 175 bph losses). Positioned tool in Rev position to stop losses. Filled and flushed lines from Frac boat. Pressure tested 4" lines to 14;000 psi. Acidized Zone 5. Performed Main Frac on Zone 5 (pumped 581;537 lbs of sand @ 35 bpm). Strip up to Rev position and circulate 2x DP volumes. Dumped seals and closed MCS. R/D Frac head. TOH to 27;002' and test MCS integrity. TOH to 20;030'. 11/23/2018: TOH with ESTMZ service tool to 1;273'. L/D ESTMZ service tool assemblies to surface (no abnormalities observed). R/D elevators; becket; bails and removed GP handling equipment from RF. Slip and cut drill line. Performed PMs on TDX; drawworks and iron roughneck. P/U and RIH with ESTMZ cleanout 3.5" wash pipe to 1;346'. P/U and RIH with Cleanwell tools to 1;613'. TIH with ESTMZ cleanout assembly on 5-7/8" DP to 9;758'. Functioned UBSR/LBSR from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod and from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod. 11/24/2018: TIH ESTMZ cleanout assembly to 27;113'. Activate VacTech activation ball. Washed down to lower VCH packer. Circulated bottoms up. TOH to 28;188'. Monitored well for 30 mins and allow debris to fall. TIH (no pumps) and landed out on VCH packer - no fill observed. TOH to 25;502'.

Pressure tested rams to 300/ 8;000 psi; annular to 300/ 4;500 psi and Kelly hose to 300/ 7;000 psi. Function tested BOPs from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod and from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod. Function tested diverter from Toolpusher's Panel. R/D BOP test stand. TOH to 1;746'. Recovered debris from Cleanwell VacTech chambers. Pumped base oil through the flow head and down the landing string. Pressure tested top of upper crown plug with cementer (12;600 psia). Displaced the kill line with 240 bbls of seawater. Prepared to unlatch THRT. Unlatched THRT and continued to displace with SW for 2x landing string volumes. Spiked LS and rigged down all surface lines on rig floor. Specific instances include L&L is installed and locked with the tubing hanger landed.

Pulled BOP/LMRP on marine riser from 6;884' to 6;509'. Deck crew replaced secondary retention on yoke. Continued pulling BOP/LMRP on marine riser from 6;509' to 3;509'. BOP on beams at 19:45 hrs. Lay out double and rig down riser running equipment. 12/11/2018: MSV Harvey Deep Sea installed tertiary tree cap and filled with Transaqua.

Note: The pressure spikes were not associated with an influx. The service tool was spaced out in a unique position where the open hole packers and a package of the service tool seals aligned perfectly; causing pressure spikes as the seals washed off the tool and bridged against the ID of the open hole packer and the OD of the service tool. These were the "rubbers" we recovered at surface. Since recognizing this situation; efforts have been made with Halliburton to add additional space out puts to move the packer up ~20 ft to avoid this from ever happening again.

Stripped up to Reverse position and reversed out;  establishing returns. Once 13.3 ppg CaBr observed at surface; swapped to active system; then staged down pumps maintaining CP/DPP at or above BCP. Shut down trapping BCP of 1;500 psi on the DP/casing. Strip up to dump seals. Did not see indications of seals dumping. Continued to strip up to close MCS. Applied 500 psi to backside; did not see communication between annulus and DP. Applied 4;500 psi down back side with no reaction on DP observed. Bled off pressure and stripped back down to Reverse position. Lined up pumps on HPDU and continued reversing out. Flow check well on trip tank. Well static. Slacked off with 20k down; isolating MCS from annulus. With annular open; applied 500 psi down DP for 5 mins testing MCS - good test; MCS confirmed closed. Rigged down Frac iron and control lines.

NOTE: On 11/08/2018 at 15:12 hours; Mr. Adriano Garcia (BSEE) provided Mr. Matt Hensgens (Chevron) an additional 72 hour extension for casing evaluation. 

Note: As per Alternative Compliance #9 in the permit: BOP/BSR/Diverter Function Tests and Pressure Test will not be conducted when completion tubulars for Frac Operations are across the BOP. Testing of such BOPE will be conducted once operationally feasible.

11/09/2018: Continued rigging down Frac head and laid down same. TOH to 28;114' (30 ft above VCH packer); closed annular; and performed Full System test to 1;500 psi. Performed pit management for displacement. Displaced well from 13.3 ppg CaBr to 14.0 ppg CaBr. TOH from 28;114' to 6;248' while testing choke and kill manifold offline. Slip and cut drill line. 

Note: As per Alternative Compliance #9 in the permit: BOP/BSR/Diverter Function Tests and Pressure Test will not be conducted when completion tubulars for Frac Operations are across the BOP. Testing of such BOPE will be conducted once operationally feasible.

11/10/2018: With service tool mule shoe at 6;248'; continue with slip and cut drill line; made repairs to BlockTilt cylinder on Main Block. P/U and TIH with ValiTech/MagTech to 6;586'. While pumping slug; swivel packing started leaking. Changed out same to new ceramic style swivel packing and tested. P/U PBL - Jet Sub and TIH from 6;586' to 13;635'. Jet WH/XT/BOPs at 18 bpm and sweep to surface; recoverd ~5 gals of solids. M/U Double Dutch stand and test BOPs; as per IPT test plan; on 5-7/8" DP from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod with 14.0 ppg CaBr2. Surface equipment and  safety valves tested to 250-350/ 10;000 psi; Pipe rams and associated valves tested to 250-350/ 8;000 psi; Annulars to 250-350/ 4;500 psi. 

Note: As per Alternative Compliance #9 in the permit: BOP/BSR/Diverter Function Tests and Pressure Test will not be conducted when completion tubulars for Frac Operations are across the BOP. Testing of such BOPE will be conducted once operationally feasible.

11/11/2018: Continue BOP pressure testing on 5-7/8" DP using 14.0 ppg CaBr2 from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod. Pressure tested surface equipment and safety valves to 250-350 /10;000 psi; pipe rams to 250-350/ 8;000 psi; kelly hose to 250-350/ 7;000 psi and annulars to 250-350/ 4;500 psi for 5 mins. Function tested BOPs on 5-7/8" DP from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod and from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod. Performed Diverter function test in auto sequence from Toolpusher's Panel diverting to Port. Performed Diverter function test from Driller's Chair with Diverter button. Short trip to lay out jet sub and inspect MagTech and ValiTech for fill (3-1/2" of fill); TIH 2 stands and pick up BWTT and Nu-Tech assy. TIH and land out BWTT in XT; released from Nu-Tech tool and TOH 2 stands. Pressure tested UBSR/LBSR to 250-350/ 8;000 psi using 14.0 ppg CaBr2 for 5 min from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod as per IPT test plan. Function tested UBSR/LBSR from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod and from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod. Flushed grease from Choke/Kill manifold. Re-engage Nu-Tech and BWTT. Unseated BWTT from XT. Swept BOP and riser with 50 bbl HEC Hi-Vis at 18 bpm down kill line. TOH to 4;646' (midnight depth).

Note: On 11/11/2018 at 11:47 hours; Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) provided Matt Hensgens(Chevron) with an additional 24 hour extension for casing evaluation and permission to proceed with operations with acoustic system isolated due to system leak.

11/12/2018: Continue TOH from 4;626' to surface; laying down BWTT/Nu-Tech and ESTMZ Service Tool assemblies. Rig up WL and RIH with 60 arm casing caliper to 11;850' WLM and lost comms with the tool. POOH and reestablished comms at 1;200'. Continued POOH to surface; troubleshot and swapped out Baker's crossover to Weatherford's tools. RIH from surface to 28;034' and log up to 10;801'.

Note: On 11/12/2018 at 15:35 hours; Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) provided Matt Hensgens(Chevron) with an additional 24 hour extension for casing evaluation.

11/13/2018: Continue POOH with 60 arm casing caliper evaluation tool. R/D E/L equipment. Performed planned rig maintenance. P/U TCP BHA and TIH to 12;000'.

Note: On 11/13/2018 at 18:48 hrs; Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) granted approval to proceed with permitted well operations after reviewing casing integrity evaluation results and requested revised permit to reflect a derating of casing due to wear.

11/14/2018: Continue TIH with TCP guns from 12;000' to 28;100'. Tagged lower zone VCH packer at 28;138'. P/U and place TCP guns on depth; R/U surface iron and test. Set packer and apply 500 psi on backside. Perforated upper zones 3; 4 and 5. 
Zone 3 perforations: 28;058' - 28;121' MD (27;416' - 27;476' TVD). 
Zone 4 perforations: 27;762' - 27;913' MD (27;136' - 27;279' TVD). 
Zone 5 perforations: 27;392' - 27;543' MD (26;785' - 26;928' TVD).
Observe initial losses of 12 bph; losses stabilized at 3.2 bph on TT after 30 mins. Reverse out 1-1/2x DP volumes. Flow check well and R/D surface iron. TOH from 28;118 - 24;390'.

11/15/2018: Continue TOH with TCP assembly from 24;390' to 1;287'; L/D TCP assembly from 1;287' to surface; all shots fired. P/U and RIH with CleanWell Deburr assembly from surface to 639'.

11/16/2018: Continue P/U and RIH with Cleanwell Deburr assembly from 619' to 1;048'. TIH with Cleanwell Deburr assembly from 1;048' to 27;362'. Obtain parameters prior to activating eductor head on VacTech. Activate VacTech with 1-3/4" steel ball and wash down through perfs at 8 bpm. Shut down pumps and rotary. Slacked off and tagged no-go on VCH PKR at 28;138' with 20k. P/U 5 ft and circulate bottoms up and until brine was to spec. Shutdown pumps and P/U 1 stand above VCH PKR. Monitored well while letting debris fall - well losing at 1.2 bph.

11/17/2018: TOH from 28;000' to surface with Halliburton Deburr assembly. Rig up to pick up ESTMZ assembly. M/U and RIH with gravel pack service tool assembly on 4" wash pipe. M/U and RIH with Zone #3 assembly. Pressure tested Zone 3 assembly to 250 psi for 5 min to ensure sleeve integrity - good test.

11/18/2018: M/U and RIH with Zone 4 - Zone 5 GP assemblies. Pressure tested Zone 4 and 5 assemblies and isolation packer sleeve integrity to 250 psi for 5 mins. RIH with ratch-latch retrieval suspension tool on 4-1/2" fishing string (inner string) and retrieved ratch-latch and suspension tool. Pressure tested to 250 psi for 5 mins to ensure FCS/MCS sleeve integrity and performed 2 circulation tests. L/D pups and performed RIH pressure test to 250 psi for 5 min. P/U VCH packer and RIH with same. P/U gauge bundle carrier and RIH with ESTMZ assemblies on 5-7/8" DP to 8;614'. Function tested BOP and diverter. RIH with ESTMZ assemblies from 8;614' to 10;917'.

Function tested UBSR/LBSR from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod and from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod. Function tested BOP from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod and from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod. Functioned diverter from Driller's Panel.

11/19/2018: RIH with ESTMZ assemblies from 10;917' to 28;134'. Latched into lower zone VCH packer. Set upper VCH packer at 27;277' IES. Released Heavy Hang Weight Tool from VCH packer. Pressure tested VCH packer to 1;500 psi - good test. Set isolation packers (Zone 4 packer at 27;556' IES and Zone 3 packer at 27;932' IES). Pumped 50 bbl HEC pill down the work string and circulated surface to surface.

11/20/2018: Circulated surface to surface at 15 bpm. Pickled work string; RU frac boat and flush/test lines. Pump 580;804 lbs sand - max rate 35 bpm. Reversed out 15;229 lbs sand. 

Note: BSEE Inspectors Paul Reeves; Clint Campo; Gabe Orellana; Cedric Bernard arrived on ship at 09:00 hrs. Monthly inspection completed with no INCs. Departed ship at 13:00 hrs.

11/21/2018: Continued reversing out DP volume. Dumped seals and closed Zone 3 MCS. Tested MCS integrity. R/D Frac head. Space out service tool in Zone 4. M/U Frac head and lines. Opened MCS and Acidize Zone 4. Performed Main Frac on Zone 4 (pumped 566;766 lbs of sand @ 35 bpm). Strip up to reverse position and circulate 2 DP volumes. Dumped seals and closed Zone 4 MCS. R/D Frac head. Tested MCS integrity. Spaced out service tool in Zone 5 and tested same. M/U Frac head and lines. Obtained P/U and S/O weights and locate WDS position. Closed LAP; applied 500 psi to backside and strip up to reverse position. Broke circulation and filled surface lines.

11/22/2018: Flushed surface lines and pressure tested. Baker Stimulation Vessel Blue Dolphin waiting on inclement weather to pass. Brought in Stimulation Vessel and R/U Frac hose. Calibrated flow meters. P/U and opened MCS (observed 175 bph losses). Positioned tool in Rev position to stop losses. Filled and flushed lines from Frac boat. Pressure tested 4" lines to 14;000 psi. Acidized Zone 5. Performed Main Frac on Zone 5 (pumped 581;537 lbs of sand @ 35 bpm). Strip up to Rev position and circulate 2x DP volumes. Dumped seals and closed MCS. R/D Frac head. TOH to 27;002' and test MCS integrity. TOH to 20;030'.

11/23/2018: TOH with ESTMZ service tool to 1;273'. L/D ESTMZ service tool assemblies to surface (no abnormalities observed). R/D elevators; becket; bails and removed GP handling equipment from RF. Slip and cut drill line. Performed PMs on TDX; drawworks and iron roughneck. P/U and RIH with ESTMZ cleanout 3.5" wash pipe to 1;346'. P/U and RIH with Cleanwell tools to 1;613'. TIH with ESTMZ cleanout assembly on 5-7/8" DP to 9;758'. Functioned UBSR/LBSR from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod and from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod.

11/24/2018: TIH ESTMZ cleanout assembly to 27;113'. Activate VacTech activation ball. Washed down to lower VCH packer. Circulated bottoms up. TOH to 28;188'. Monitored well for 30 mins and allow debris to fall. TIH (no pumps) and landed out on VCH packer - no fill observed. TOH to 25;502'.

11/25/2018: TOH with ESTMZ cleanout assembly to 23;892'. Pressure tested BOPs on 5-7/8" drill pipe from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod using 14.0 ppg CaBr2. Pressure tested rams to 300/ 8;000 psi; annular to 300/ 4;500 psi and Kelly hose to 300/ 7;000 psi. Function tested BOPs from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod and from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod. Function tested diverter from Toolpusher's Panel. R/D BOP test stand. TOH to 1;746'. Recovered debris from Cleanwell VacTech chambers.
Note: Choke manifold was pressure tested on 11/24/2018 to 300/ 10;000 psi.

11/26/2018: Recovered debris from CleanWell VacTech chambers. Laid out ESTMZ cleanout 3.5" washpipe. R/U handling equipment. P/U and RIH with HES Isolation assemblies (Zones 1 - 5) to 1;493'. TIH with Isolation assembly to 21;730'.

11/27/2018: TIH with Isolation assembly to 27;170'. TIH opening MJPS and FCS production sleeves across Zones 5 - 1 (max loss rate @ 600 bph). Sting into VCH seal bore at 28;624' (losses stopped). Confirmed latch with 30 klbs overpull. Pressure tested FS-2 and seals in VCH packer seal bore to 1;000 psi. Pumped down 1-7/8" ball and pressured up to 2;500 psi. Bled off and attempted to release from PBR with 30k overpull (no success). Pressured up to 2;500 psi and released from PBR. Obtained new string weights. Slacked off and tagged PBR at 27;146' with 10k. Closed MVBR to mark pipe. Pumped slug and TOH to surface. Slip and cut drill line. Performed planned rig maintenance. R/U handling gear. 

11/28/2018: P/U TNT packer and PBR assembly to 339'. R/D WFD handling equipment. TIH with TNT packer assembly to 26;706'. Locate tool joint and TIH 2 stands. Land out PFZ anchor latch by setting 30k down at 27;160' DPM (mule shoe depth). Confirm latch with 30k overpull and performed 1;000 psi "feel good" test. Set TNT permanent packer at 26;951' (IES). P/U 30 ft and S/O setting 10k down on PBR. Closed MVBRs and pressure tested TNT packer to 5;000 psi for 5 mins with 14.0 ppg CaBr2 (WSEA 10-E). Bled off pressure; opened MVBRs and TOH to 23;331'. 

11/29/2018: TOH with Halliburton TNT Packer running tool/ wash pipe from 23;331' to surface. P/U BOP jetting assembly and TIH to 7;342' (bit depth). Jet BOP with Tornar tool. Pump 50 bbl HEC sweep and circulate B/U. TOH with jetting assmeblies to 333'.

11/30/2018: L/D BOP jetting assembly. No debris recovered in Vali Tech; 3.5 lbs wet metal fines recovered on Mag Tech. Function test UBSRs/LBSRs from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod and from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod. Function test CSRs from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod. TIH with BOPTT/Jetting assembly. Pressure test BOPs on 5-7/8" DP from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod; using 14.0 ppg CaBr2. Pressure tested rams and associated valves to 300/ 8;000 psi; annular to 300/ 4;500 psi. Choke manifold and all surface safety valves tested to 300/ 10;000 psi. Function tested BOP from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod and from Toolpushers's Panel on Blue Pod. Function tested diverter from Driller's Panel. Jet BOP. Retrieved bore protector with 22k overpull. TOH hole with BPRRT to 7;345'. With Jet sub at 7;032'; jetted TH profile. Pumped 50 bbl HEC sweep and circulate out of hole. TOH with BPRRT on 5-7/8" drill pipe to 593'.

12/01/2018: TOH from 593' to surface. Laid out assemblies and inspected 10-3/4" ValiTech/ Bore Protector. Riser ValiTech = 1.5 lbs of LCM MagTech = 2.6 lbs (wet metal fines). 10-3/4" ValiTech = 0.75 lbs of LCM. TIH with 17.8" NuTec centralizer from surface to 7;030'. No obstruction observed while running/pulling 17.8" NuTec through BOPs. TOH to surface. Slip and cut drill line. R/U and run production tubing to 787'.

12/02/2018: RIH in stands with 4-1/2" 17 ppf Vam Top tubing from 787' to 15;289'. Drifted tubing from derrick with 3.615" drift. M/U tubing to 8;500 ft-lbs. Installed cross-coupling control line protector/clamps across every connection.

12/03/2018: TIH with production tubing from 15;289' to 17;433'. M/U pups; timed pup and SCSSV to string. Terminated and tested SCSSV control lines. RIH with remaining 4-1/2" tubing and 6" VIT. M/U tubing hanger. R/D WFD handling gear prepare to terminate lines. 

12/04/2018: Took P/U and S/O. Function tested SCSSV valves 3x. Took Well Dynamics gauge readings. Lowered Helix and positioned tubing for contol line termination. Rough cut control lines and passed thru Helix. Performed control line terminations and testing as per plan. TIH with upper completion on 7-5/8" MaXit landing string from 19;873' to 26;808'. Make up soft land stand and land tubing hanger at 26;908' (63' seal engagement) and applied 45k down(200 psi increase on soft land). Pick up and position hanger above BOP. 

12/05/2018: Spot 14.0 ppg CaBr2 inhibited packer fluid in tubing x casing annulus. Broke out soft landing stand. Rigged up CTLF and associated equipment. Picked up SFT and made up to LS. Get on CMC PHC (mid stroke). Installed torpedo packers. Land and lock tubing hanger. R/U HPDU and surface iron. R/U PXF hydraulic lines and function valves. Pressure tested tubing hanger upper seals (12;600 psia); SCSSV1 and SCSSV2 control lines (12;600 psia); gallery seal (12;600 psia); production bore (12;600 psia); casing x tubing annulus (5;000 psi). Engage and test electrical penetrators. Repeated gallery seal test. R/U slickline lubricator. 

12/06/2018: Continued R/U slickline lubricator. Pressure tested SFT and lubricator (10;000 psi). Pressure tested landing string; SFT body and production tubing (4;500 psi). Negative tested SCSSV (4;800 psi). 

12/07/2018: RIH and set with Lower Crown Plug. POOH with slickline to surface. Tested below LCP (7;400 psi differential) down kill line from cement unit with base oil. Make up; RIH and set UCP. POOH with slickline to surface. Perform pressure test between LCP and UCP via IWOCS (12;600 psia). Rigged down lubricator while cycling FS2 valve. Bullhead base oil and negative test SCSSV. 

BSEE Inspectors Gabe Orellana; Joshua Naquin; Chris Trelano; and Troy Boudreaux arrived at the Deepwater Conqueror on 12/7/2018; at 9:00 am. No INC's were issued and the inspectors departed the ship at 13:45 hrs.

12/08/2018: Sent in results of negative test on SCSSV for approval. Pumped base oil through the flow head and down the landing string. Pressure tested top of upper crown plug with cementer (12;600 psia). Displaced the kill line with 240 bbls of seawater. Prepared to unlatch THRT. Unlatched THRT and continued to displace with SW for 2x landing string volumes. Spiked LS and rigged down all surface lines on rig floor. Removed torpedo packers from landing string. Laid out SFT and CTLF. Rigged up landing string handling equipment. TOH with L&L on 7-5/8" LS. 

Note: As per Alternative Compliance #9 in the permit: Function and pressure tests on the BOP (including VBRs; BSRs; and annulars) and diverter will not be conducted when procedures require having completion tubulars across the stack. Specific instances include L&L is installed and locked with the tubing hanger landed.

12/09/2018: Rigged down tubing running equipment and cleaned rig floor. Performed diverter operator test. Back-spool expro umbilical through sheaves. Rig up riser running equipment. Rigged up riser handling equipment. Picked up diverter running tool. Laid out diverter and running tool. Made up landing joint to slip joint. Unlatched BOP/LMRP at 14:58 hrs. Move to DOZ. Remove drape hoses and storm loops. Lay out slip joint. Rig up riser turning device. 

12/10/2018: Crane crew continued to rig up riser turning devise on yoke and spreader beam while installing riser tilt cylinder on Main TDX. Pulled BOP/LMRP on marine riser from 6;884' to 6;509'. Deck crew replaced secondary retention on yoke. Continued pulling BOP/LMRP on marine riser from 6;509' to 3;509'. Held TOFS on rig floor to re-inspected riser handling equipment while crane crew recalibrated riser gantry crane (lost sync). Continued pulling BOP/LMRP on marine riser from 3;509' to surface. BOP on beams at 19:45 hrs. Lay out double and rig down riser running equipment.

12/11/2018: MSV Harvey Deep Sea installed tertiary tree cap and filled with Transaqua.

07/10/2015: Completed planned rig maintainance. Made up BHA #3 and TIH with BHA #3 to 500' above mud line in DOZ. Moved rig over well center and TIH with BHA #3 to 8;193'. Washed/reamed from 8;193' to 8;427' and drilled 26" hole from 8;427' to 8;861' with 10.1 ppg PAD mud.

07/14/2015: TOH with BHA #4 from 6;307' to surface with FWD rotary. R/U 22" casing handling equipment on AFT rotary and RIH with 22" casing to 3;476'. R/D casing handling equipment.

Washed down from 10;494' to 10;519' and landed and locked HPWH in the LPWH.

07/16/2015: Pumped 13.5 ppg spacer followed by 14.0 ppg lead slurry and 16.4 ppg tail slurry and displaced cement with 8.6 ppg seawater. R/D cement manifold. Preloaded and set HPWH in LPWH. Released Wellhead Lock Down tool from HPWH. Dropped nerf ball into landing string and circulated landing string with 8.6 ppg seawater. TOH from 10;065' to 3;040' and L/D Wellhead Lock Down tool.

Note: During the 22" cement job; we initially encountered losses and established returns during the job @ ~1600 bbls. We pumped 2;500 bbls of cement versus 777 bbls required in RPD. We did not confirm cement at the mudline. Chevron conducted a CBL/temperature log on the 22" casing & interpreted a TOC @ ~7;100'; which is 50' below the mudline.

07/17/2015: Moved rig to DOZ. TOH from 3;040' to surface with inner string. R/U CBL E-line equipemnt. P/U CBL E-Line tool string. 

Note: On 07/17/2015 10:11 AM; Mr. Chris Gerlitz (Chevron) notified Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) that the original 72 hour notice for the initial BOP latch up to the Jack PS001 well would be delayed.

07/18/2015: RIH with CBL E-line tool string to 300'. Calibrate and surface test tool string - good test. TIH from 300' to 900' with the tool string. ROV located and monitored tool string while RIH from 900' to 500' above mud line and began transit to well center.

","WAR_START_DT":"2015-11-15","WELL_NAME":"PS001"},{"   ":85,"API12":608124005201,"TEXT_REMARK":"11/22/2015: Short trip with displacement assembly on 5-7/8" drill pipe from 26;883' to 25;895'. Monitored riser on trip tank - well static.

11/24/2015: Continued pressure testing BOPs against 5-7/8" drill pipe on Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod using 14.1 ppg CaBr2 per IPT test plan: UVBRs/MVBRs and associated valves to 250/8;000 psi - all good tests. 23 of 23 tests completed. TIH with TCP gun and test tool assembly on 5-7/8" drill pipe to 2;110'.

Zone 4: 27;828' - 27;935' MD (107') / 26;879' - 26;973' TVD (94')
Zone 3: 28;547' - 28;654' MD (107') / 27;513' - 27;607' TVD (94')

Zone 1: 29;049' - 29;156' MD (107') / 27;955' - 28;049' TVD (94')

Established loss rate of 16 bph. Reversed out 1.5 drill string volumes. Monitored well on trip tank for 20 mins (12 bph steady loss rate). Unset the TCP packer and TOH to 28;880' with the spent TCP assembly. Monitored the well on trip tank with losses at 12 bph stabilized. TOH from 27;359' to 15;475' with spent TCP assembly. Monitored well on trip tank (12 bph loss).

Pumped 70 bbl pickle job; then reversed out to circulate hole clean. 
","WAR_START_DT":"2015-11-29","WELL_NAME":"PS001"},{"   ":87,"API12":608124005201,"TEXT_REMARK":"12/06/2015: Pumped Zone 1 (perf interval 29;049' to 29;156' WLM) acid job and spotted on perfs. Injected acid into Zone 1 and allowed to soak. Performed and evaluated mini frac treatment on Zone 1. Performed main frac pack job on Zone 1. Reversed proppant out of the drillstring and circulated 14.1 ppg CaBr2 to spec following reverse out. Monitored well on the mini-strip tank with service tool still engaged; 6 bph losses. Opened annular and monitored the well on the trip tank with service tool still engaged; 6 bph losses. P/U to dump the seals on the service tool and monitored well on the trip tank; 20 bph losses. Cycled the service tool to close the Mechanical Closing Sleeve (MCS) and Frac Circulation Sleeve (FCS) and loss rate stabilized at 6 bph. R/D frac iron; lines; and frac head. Closed the annular and attempted to pressure test the MCS/FCS to 500 psi using the cement unit - no success. Opened the annular; cycled sleeves open once then cycled closed 5 times; loss rate steady at 12 bph. Discuss forward path with office and decided to proceed. TOH with the service tool on 5-7/8" DP from 29;218' to 29;012'. P/U frac head and R/U associated lines. Placed service tool on depth for performing Zone 2 (perf interval 28;831' to 28;938' WLM) stimulation. Pressure tested service tool seals to 1;500/500 psi - good test.

12/07/2015: Flushed lines from stimulation vessel. P/U and opened MCS; losses steady at 12 bph. Pressure tested service tool assembly and discussed options with office. Began troubleshooting gravel pack system. POOH from 29;012' to 28;736' and positioned tool in Zone 3. Identified leak path in screen assemblies. TIH from 28;736' to 29;012' to Zone 2 and P/U frac head. R/U chiksans and control lines. Tested surface lines to 7;500 psi - good test. Cycled service tool and positioned in reverse out position and broke circulation. Pressured up down drill string attempting to test service tool seals and Zone 2 MCS - slight leak in MCS noted. 

12/08/2015: Performed reverse out test by pumping down annulus taking returns up drill pipe. Pumped Zone 2 acid job and spotted on perfs. Injected acid into Zone 2 and allowed to soak. Performed main frac pack job on Zone 2. Reversed proppant out of the drillstring. Observed pressure on casing 220 psi and 150 psi on tubing; shifted Zone 2 MCS and bled back 10 bbls. Circulated 14.1 ppg CaBr2 to spec following reverse out.

12/09/2015: R/D frac iron and frac head. POOH from 29;012' to 28;736' to place service tool in Zone 3 (perf interval 28;547' to 28;654' WLM). Attempt to test service tool to 1;500 psi - leak noted. Performed troubleshooting test on surface equipment. Retest service tool to 1;500 psi - slight leak in noted. Decison made to proceed with Zone 3 frac operations. P/U frac head and R/U assocated lines. Opened MCS and performed reverse circulating test. Flush and test frac lines from stimulation vessel to frac head to 13;800 psi - good test. Pumped Zone 3 acid job and spotted on perfs. Injected acid into Zone 3 and allowed to soak. Performed main frac pack job on Zone 3. Reversed proppant out of the drillstring.

12/10/2015: Continued reversing proppant out of the drillstring. Worked service tool while pumping at 12 bpm with 3;000 psi and freed tool. R/D frac head and associated lines. 

12/11/2015: P/U frac head; removed single and laid back out. POOH from 28;736' to 27;229'. Made up SES stand and chiksans. Pressure tested MVBR and test rams to 250/8;000 psi for 5 min each on 5-7/8" DP - good tests. Function tested BOPs from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod and from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod - good tests. R/D test lines and chiksans and rack back SES stand. Function tested diverter from Toolpusher's Panel - 40 secs to close. POOH with service tool from 27;229' to 1;553'; loss rate steady at 19 bph. R/U service tool handling equipment and POOH with service tool from 1;553' to 1;450'.

12/12/2015: POOH with service tool from 1;450' to ESTMZ service tool crossover weldment with 253' of fish in hole with an estimated top of fish at 28;478'. R/D service tool handling equipment. Slip and cut drill line. Serviced rig equipment. Function tested Upper and Lower BSRs from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod - good tests. Performed dropped objects inpsection on forward MDDM; forward PRS and aft PRS. Performed drawworks calibration and brake test. M/U 5-7/8" muleshoe and TIH from surface to 8;432' on 5-7/8" TFM drill pipe; loss rate 17 bph. M/U SES stand and chiksans. Began pressure testing BOPs to 250/8;000 psi on 5-7/8" DP.
","WAR_START_DT":"2015-12-06","WELL_NAME":"PS001"},{"   ":88,"API12":608124005201,"TEXT_REMARK":"12/13/2015: Tested BOPs on 34# 5-7/8" drill pipe against test rams from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod to 250/8;000 psi for 5 min each. Rigged down cement stand and began pulling out of hole with EZSV running tool on 5-7/8" DP from 27;692' to 24;903'. Attempted to perform pressure test on cement plug; no success. Deployed ROV to inspect riser; BOP; and SSPT; confirmed no SBM releases to the environment. Performed troubleshooting steps by closing MVBRs and pressuring up in 500 psi increments to 2;800 psi. Pressure immediately bled off to 0 psi. Well began losing at 56 bbls/hr and then decreased to static over 2 hours. TOH from 24;903' to 12;884' with EZSV running tool on 5-7/8" TFM DP.

12/19/2015; Continued TOH with EZSV running tool from 12;884' to surface. Performed UBSR/LBSR function test from Driller's panel on Yellow Pod. RIH with EZSV from surface to 26;033'. Set EZSV at 26;030'. 

Note: On 12/19/2015 at 09:19 hrs; Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) notified Mr. Douglas Nally (Chevron) that Chevron may proceed with the revised plugback operations.

On 12/19/2015 at 21:33 hrs; Mr. Douglas Nally (Chevron) notified Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) that the Discoverer Clear Leader plans to begin stump testing the BOP/LMRP on surface as soon as Tuesday; 12/22/2015.

12/24/2015: Finished rigging up riser equipment and unlatched BOPs. Moved rig 1;200' to dropped object zone.

08/22/2016: Skidded BOP from park position straight back to port side of moonpool and out to moonpool beams. 08/23/2016: Ran Riser and LMRP/BOP while installing IWOCS clamps from 3;421' to 6;799' (90 jts total). Rigged up testing cap and pressure tested riser auxiliary lines (good test). Rigged down testing cap. Installed termination joint; intermediate flex joint and slip joint. Installed drape hoses to termination joint and tested C/K lines to 11;500 psi for 5 mins and boost and RC to 5;000 for 5 mins (good test). Made up HWPJ and landing joint.

08/24/2016: Moved rig 50' from Jack PS001 wellhead and completed installation of IWOCs turndown assembly and SDC ring. ROV removed trash cap and inspected the XT mandrel. Landed and latched BOP to XT. Took 100k overpull and performed a slump test (375k) with ROV inspecting(good test). Unlocked slip joint and scoped out same. Laid out landing joint and installed diverter. Rigged down riser running tools and rigged up DP handling tools. TIH with muleshoe and 2 stands of 5-7/8" DP and performed diverter function test from Driller's and Toolpusher's panels with 35 sec closeure time; then performed flow test on port and starboard (good test). P/U BWTT/Dual Cam Assy and began TIH to 2;298'.

08/25/2016: TIH with Boll Weevil Test Tool/ Dual Cam Tool and landed out at 7;035'. Backed out Dual Cam and performed deadman test per TOI procedure. Made up to Dual Cam Tool; and unseated BWTT. POOH with 2 stands and spaced out 5-7/8" 34 ppf drill pipe across BOP for testing. Located annular with tool joint. Spaced out for BOP test. Pressure tested MPR; UPR; and Annular against test ram. Function tested BOP from Toolpusher's Panel; Blue Pod. Functioned well control button on Driller's chair and confirmed all upper and lower FSVs were closed; bleed valves opened; and annular closed. POOH to surface with BWTT/Dual Cam assembly on 5-7/8" DP.

08/26/2016: Suspended operations to monitor tropical storm conditions. Picked up 8-1/2" cleanout assembly and TIH from surface to 7;576'. Washed down from 7;576' to 8;000' with no indication of hard cement. Displaced lines with 13.9 ppg SBM. Displaced wellbore with 13.9 pp SBM. 

08/27/2016: TIH from 8;000' to 9;950' with 8-1/2" cleanout assembly; tagging with 20k down. Pumped down from 9;950' to 10;020'; tagging with 20k down. Circulated while monitoring tropical storm. Drilled out cement plug from 10;150' to 10;532' and tagged EZSV. Drilled EZSV from 10;532 to 10;536'.

","WAR_START_DT":"2016-12-04","WELL_NAME":"PS001"},{"   ":108,"API12":608124005203,"TEXT_REMARK":"12/11/2016: TIH with OH (open hole) ESTMZ from 24;500' to 29;455' (VCH depth at 26;100'). Set VCH packer at 26;100' and verify packer set with "Push/Pull" test. Release Heavy Hang tool and test VCH packer at 1;500 psi on annulus. Mark service tool positions. Reverse out packer setting ball and WARP mud. Position tool in weight down position and set OH packers with 4;000 psi. Perform strip test with 2;600 psi on annulus. 216k overpull to initiate strip thru annular. Position tool in weight down circulate position and perform 1;500 psi test; good test.

Packer Setting Depths:
Zone 3: Swell Packer @ 27;913' MD; Isolation Packers @ 27;700' MD and 27;886' MD.
Zone 2: Swell Packer @ 28;706' MD; Isolation Packers @ 28;803' MD and 29;028' MD.
Zone 1: Isolation Packers @ 29;096' MD and 29;282' MD.

12/12/2016: Test service tool down annulus at 500 psi. M/U frac head assy and frac iron. Test frac head and frac iron at 8;000 psi. Mark tool positions. Pickle workstring. While displacing pickle to end of workstring; observed pressure spikes. Reverse out pickle; close middle pipe rams due to pressure considerations. Line up to circulate down workstring in attempt to troubleshoot pressure spikes. Pump at 12 bpm; pressure spiked up to 6;300 psi. Reduce pump rate to 10 bpm with stabilized pressure at 5;020 psi. Pulled up to "Contingency Reverse" position; close middle pipe rams and reverse out annular capacity; staged pumps up to 15 bpm at 6;200 psi. Established circulating rates down workstring and reverse circulating at 4; 8; 10 and 12 bpm. Shift service tool to "Final Reverse" position and established circulating rates at 4; 8; 10 and 12 bpm. Acquire flow rates thru flow meters. Spot 110 bbls of 6.6 ppg base oil in kill line 1;950 psi. Pressure test frac iron to 13;500 psi.

Note: The pressure spikes were not associated with an influx. The service tool was spaced out in a unique position where the open hole packers and a package of the service tool seals aligned perfectly; causing pressure spikes as the seals washed off the tool and bridged against the ID of the open hole packer and the OD of the service tool. These were the "rubbers" we recovered at surface. Since recognizing this situation; efforts have been made with Halliburton to add additional space out puts to move the packer up ~20 ft to avoid this from ever happening again. 

12/13/2016: Finished flushing and filled lines from frac boat; tested treating line to 13;500 psi. Pumped 636 bbls of linear gel with Nalco at 15 bpm for mini-frac. Analyzed mini-frac data. Pumped main frac on zone 1 in WDC position. Pumped total of 552;903 lbs of propant. Did not screen out. Reversed out 2;707 lbs proppant. Closed FCS and MCS; isolating Zone 1. Reverse circulated 2 drill string volumes. R/D down 4" chiksans and control lines off frac head. L/O frac head and pup jts. Tested Zone 1 sleeves to 500 psi down DP - good test. Acquire 20k wt down; 90k wt down; PU; initial reverse and full reverse positions in Zone 2. 

12/14/2016: Tested treating line to 13;500 psi. Pumped 731 bbls of linear gel with Nalco at 15 bpm for mini-frac. Analyzed mini-frac data. Pumped main frac on Zone 2 in WDC position. Pumped total of 663;810 lbs of proppant. Did not screen out. Reversed out 1 DP volume in contingency reverse position. No proppant observed. Attempted to reverse circulate out 2 drill string volumes. Well taking ~300 BPH. Re-shifted FCS and MCS sleeves closed. Reverse circulated 2 DP volumes. Max gas 169 units. R/D down 4" chiksans and control lines off frac head. L/O frac head and pup jts. Tested Zone 2 sleeves to 500 psi down DP - good test. Acquire 20k wt down; 90k wt down; PU; initial reverse and full reverse positions in Zone 3. RU frac head.

12/15/2016: Tested treating line to 13;500 psi. Pumped main frac on Zone 3 in WDC position. Pumped total of 367;614 lbs of proppant. Did not screen out. Reversed out 1 DP volume in final reverse position. Trace proppant observed. Shifted FCS and MCS sleeves closed. Reverse circulated 2 DP volumes. R/D down 4" chiksans and control lines off frac head. L/O frac head and pup jt. Tested Zone 3 sleeves to 500 psi down DP - good test. POOH to 25;905'. U-tube base oil out of kill line. POOH from 25;905' to 18;857'.

12/16/2016: POOH with ESTMZ service tool from 18;857' to 13;203'. Pressure tested BOPs against test rams on 5-7/8" drill pipe using 14.1 CaBr2 per APM; utilizing IPT SureTec system from Toolpusher's Panel; Blue Pod. Annulars tested to 250-350/4;500 psi for 5 mins each. VBRs tested to 250-350/8;200 psi for 5 mins each. Function tested BOPs from Toolpusher's Panel; Blue Pod; and from Driller's Panel; Yellow Pod. Function tested diverter from Toolpusher's Panel. Continued to POOH from 13;203' to 3;359'. Rack back 4" wash pipe and lay out ESTMZ service tool from 3;359' to 174'.

12/17/2016: POOH and L/O ESTMZ service tool. Slip and cut drill line. M/U 4" mule shoe; FCS and MCS close shifter; 4" wash pipe and fluted no-go. TIH to 26;069'.

11/26/2012: Complete testing UBSRs/LBSRs. Pull of hole to surface. Make up and run in hole with lower completion through zone 2.

11/27/2012: Continue to run in hole with lower completion zones 3 through 5. Retrieve suspension tool and pressure test lower completion assembly to 250 psi for 5 min.

11/28/2012: Function test UBSRs/LBSRs from Driller's panel; Yellow pod and ToolPusher's panel; Blue pod. Run in hole with lower completion to 19;827'.

11/29/2012: Continue to run in hole with lower completion to 27;938'. Set VCH packer at 26;356' MD. Pressure test backside to 1;500 psi for 5 min.

11/30/2012: Reverse out packer setting ball. Set Rok Anchors. Set isolation packers. Function BOPs. Rig up Frac head and chicsans. Attempt to pressure test completion service tool seals; no success. Troubleshoot service tool seals.

12/01/2012: Pressure test service tool seals in zone 2 with no success. Pull out of hole with service tool 300'. 

","WAR_START_DT":"2012-11-25","WELL_NAME":"PS002"},{"   ":178,"API12":608124001701,"TEXT_REMARK":"12/02/2012: Pull out the hole with Halliburton GP service tool from 300' to surface. Pick up backup GP service tool and trip in the hole with same to 6;229'. Slip and cut drill line. Function UBSR/LBSR from Toolpusher's panel on Yellow pod and from Driller's panel on Blue pod. Closed UBSRs using ROV hot stab; then opened from Driller's panel. Continue to trip in the hole with GP service tool from 6;229' to 20;797'. 

12/03/2012: Finish RIH with Halliburton GP service tool. Pressure test service tool in zones 1-5 to 1500 psi and rig up frac head. Monitor well on trip tank (static). Spot pickle and reverse out same. Calibrate Supreme choke manifold. Flush frac line and pressure test to 13;500 psi; successfully.

12/04/2012: Perform mini frac and evaluate. Perform main frac test on zone 1. Start reversing out; close sliding sleeves and continue to reverse out and monitor well (static). Rig down frac head and iron; and make up MDDM to DP. Successfully test lower completion sleeves in all zones to 500 psi. P/U to zone 2 and test tool upper seals to 1500 psi and test lower completion seals to 500 psi; successfully. P/U frac head and rig up frac iron. Flush frac line and pressure test to 13;500 psi; successfully.

12/05/2012: Successfully test lines from frac boat to frac head to 13;500 psi. Perform mini frac and evaluate. Perform main frac of zone 2. Reverse out and monitor well (static). Test sleeves in zone 2 to 500 psi; successfully. Rig down frac head and iron; and make up MDDM to DP. P/U to zone 3; close annular and successfully test lower seals to 500 psi and upper completion seals to 1500 psi. Pick up frac head and rig up frac iron. Perform maintenance on rig equipment while waiting on Stim Star III's (frac boat) arrival.

12/06/2012: Waiting on Stim Star III's (frac boat) arrival. Perform maintenance on rig equipment. Function BOPs from Toolpusher's panel from Yellow pod and from Driller's panel on Blue pod. Function test Diverter from Toolpusher's panel. Pump brine down drill pipe; then boost riser and flush choke and kill lines. Stim Star III arrives on location. Flush frac line and pressure test to 13;500 psi; successfully. Perform mini frac and evaluate. Start main frac of zone 3.

12/07/2012: Continue with main frac of zone 3. Attempt to pull to reverse out position to reverse out. Tool string determined to be stuck. Troubleshoot and free tool string. Reverse out; open well and monitor (static). Test lower completion sleeves to 500 psi; successfully. Open annular and monitor well (static). P/U to zone 4 and test service tool lower seals with no success. Troubleshoot service tool lower seals and test successfully. Test service tool upper seals; successfully. Start flushing frac line and pressure testing to 13;500 psi.

12/08/2012: Continue pressure testing frac line to 13;500 psi; successfully. Perform mini frac and analyze data. Perform main frac of zone 4. Reverse out and test lower sleeves to 500 psi; successfully. Open well and monitor flow (static). R/D frac head and iron to space out for zone 5. P/U frac head and M/U iron.
","WAR_START_DT":"2012-12-02","WELL_NAME":"PS002"},{"   ":179,"API12":608124001701,"TEXT_REMARK":"12/09/2012: Finish rigging up frac iron and test lines. Pick up and open zone 5 sleeves. Test frac lines to 13;500 psi; successfully. Perform main frac of zone 5. Reverse out and monitor well on open choke (static). Test MCS for zones 1 - 5 to 1;000 psi; successful. Bleed pressure; open annular and monitor well on trip tank (static). Rig down all frac iron; Supreme manifold and control panels. Pull out of hole to 25;727'. Pressure tested lines with cement unit for BOP test.

12/10/2012: Pressure test BOPs on 5-7/8" from Driller's panel; on Blue pod; with 14.1 ppg CaBr2 fluid to 250 low/ 7500 high for 5 minutes each. Function BOP and diverter from Toolpusher's panel; on Yellow pod. Test kelly hose 250 low/ 6500 high for 5 minutes each; successful. Test lower MDDM IBOP valve for benchmark 250 low/ 10;000 high and chart; successful.

12/11/2012: Complete testing MDDM IBOP valves 250/ 10;000 psi for 5 minutes each. Rig down test lines and POOH to 5;974'. Function Upper and Lower BSR from Driller's panel on Yellow pod and Toolpusher's panel on Blue pod. Continue POOH to 1;512'. Rig up Tesco base plate and tong cart. Pull and lay out 4" washpipe.

12/12/2012: Continue POOH with Halliburton service tool assembly from 1;300' to surface. Boost riser and change out saver sub on FWD MDDM. R/U Tesco equipment and P/U Halliburton shifting tool assembly; zone 1 - 5 isolation assemblies; latch isolation assembly and FS1 and lower PBR assembly. R/D Tesco and R/U to run 5-7/8" drill pipe out of derrick. TIH from 1;637' to 5;130'.

12/13/2012: Continue TIH with Halliburton isolation assembly from 5;130' to 6;405'. Slip and cut 149' of drill line. Continue TIH with Halliburton isolation assembly from 6;405' to 26;684'. Change out CTM-57 saver sub.

12/14/2012: TIH from 26;684' to 27;837'; opening isolation sleeves zone 5 through 1. Max loss rate 337 bbls/hr. Total losses 385 bbls. Land and latch isolation assembly with 30k down. Pull 30k over to confirm latch. Close annular and test VCH packer seals and FS1 to 250 low/ 1000 high. Good test. Release running tool. Monitor well; static. POOH to 13;894'. Continue POOH to surface and lay out setting tool. Boost riser to clear spike fluid and rig up Tesco base plate and tong cart system.

12/15/2012: Complete picking up TNT packer assembly and inner string and TIH to 338'. Rig down Tesco and rig up to run 5-7/8" drill pipe. TIH with TNT packer assembly to 26;230'. Sting into isolation assembly PBR at 26;256' and continue to slack off and land out at 26;270' with 30k down. Overpull 30k to confirm latch. Set packer at 26;070.88' and test per Halliburton procedures. POOH.
","WAR_START_DT":"2012-12-09","WELL_NAME":"PS002"},{"   ":180,"API12":608124001701,"TEXT_REMARK":"12/16/2012: POOH with TNT packer running tool from 26;230' to 15;629'. Function test BOP from Driller's panel using Yellow pod and Toolpusher's panel using Blue pod. Function test diverter from Toolpusher's panel. Continue POOH with TNT packer running tool from 15;629' to 326'. Pressure test upper and lower BSR against FS1 valve to 250 psi/ 1000 psi for 5 min from Driller's panel using Blue pod. Function test upper and lower BSRs from Toolpusher's panel using Yellow pod. P/U and TIH with Halliburton Cleanwell assembly and Cameron bore protector running/retrieval tool (BPRRT) to 727'.

12/17/2012: Continue TIH with Halliburton Cleanwell assembly and Cameron BPRRT to 7;325'. Jet BOP and SSPT. TIH and land out on bore protector. Test 9-5/8" fixed rams and BPRRT to 250 psi/ 7;500 psi for 5 min. Monitor SSPT for any leaks past BPRRT (successful). Function 9-5/8" fixed rams; from Toolpusher's panel using Yellow pod and Driller's panel using Blue pod. Pull and unseat bore protector with 35k. POOH with Halliburton Cleanwell assembly and BPRRT bore protector to 858'. Function diverter from Driller's panel. POOH with Halliburton Cleanwell assembly and BPRRT bore protector. Boost riser and rig up Tesco tubing handling equipment. P/U and RIH with lower seal assemblies.

12/18/2012: Trip in hole with 4-1/2" production tubing from 221' to 5;766'; installing control line clamp at every joint. Terminate and test control lines on Halliburton DHPT gauges and Schlumberger chemical injection mandrel.

12/19/2012: Function test upper and lower BSR from Driller's panel using Yellow pod; and from Toolpusher's panel using Blue pod. Trip in hole with 4-1/2" production tubing from 5;766' to 16;517'; installing control line clamp at every joint. Pickup Schlumberger SCSSV assembly; terminate and start testing control lines.

12/20/2012: Finish testing Schlumberger SCSSV control line; terminate and test LDHI control line on CIM. Trip in hole with 4-1/2" production tubing from 16;517' to 17;511'; installing control line clamp at every joint. Trip in hole with 6" VIT tubing from 17;511' to 18;127'. Operations suspended at 14:00 hrs due to high winds.

12/21/2012: Operations suspended until 09:00 hrs due to high winds. Trip in hole with 6" VIT tubing to 18;967'; pick up and make up Cameron tubing hanger. 

12/22/2012: Terminate and test control lines on Cameron tubing hanger. Make up Expro SSTT to tubing hanger and trip in hole with 7-5/8" landing string from 18;979' to 19;149'. 
","WAR_START_DT":"2012-12-16","WELL_NAME":"PS002"},{"   ":181,"API12":608124001701,"TEXT_REMARK":"12/23/2012: Trip in hole with Expro SSTT/ Cameron tubing hanger from 19;149' to 25;920'. Break circulation and slack off with indication of seals entering seal bore at 25;958'; pickup to 25;939'. Spot concentrated inhibited packer fluid. 

12/24/2012: Soft land Cameron tubing hanger at 26;015' with 20 kips down. Pick up and remove top 2 singles of 7-5/8" landing string and put in 30' 7-5/8" landing string pup. Rig down Tesco landing string handling equipment and trip in hole to 25;976'. Pickup CCTLF from riser deck to primary rotary; rig up and function test. Observe leak in CCTLF compensating cylinder. Rig down CCTLF and lay down from primary rotary to riser deck.

12/25/2012: Wait for DCL CCTLF to arrive on location. 

Note: On 12/25/2012; Ms. Laura Hogge (Chevron) notified Mr. Bobby Nelson; Ms. Natasha Bland; Mr. Stephen Walsh; and Kelly Johnson (all of BSEE Houma District) that the Jack PS002 ST01 flow test has been postponed from 12/26/2012 to 12/29/2012.

12/26/2012: Wait for DCL CCTLF to arrive on location. Wait on weather to offload DCL CCTLF. Offload CCTLF; assemble and perform deck test on same.

12/27/2012: P/U CCTLF to forward rotary and function test. Transfer Surface Flow Tree to FWD rotary and M/U to landing string. Install Torpedo Packers. Land and lock tubing hanger; take 100k overpull; over landing string weight. Commence pressure testing tubing hanger.

12/28/2012: Finish pressure testing tubing hanger. Pressure test SubSea Test Tree per Expro. Test Surface Flow Tree to 250/ 12;500 psi. Function Diverter from Toolpusher's panel.

12/29/2012: Rig up slick line and pull isolation sleeve. RIH with protection sleeve on wireline and set same. L/D lubricator to 6-3/8" night cap. Spot base fluid in landing string to under balance well. Cycle FS1 valve; open at 19 cycles. Monitor well pressure while waiting on daylight to begin well test. 

Note: Mr. Joe Gordon (Chevron) received written approval from Mr. Bryan Domangue (BSEE Houma District) on 12/29/2012 for commencement of well test operations at WR758 Jack PS002 ST01 after review of documentation pertaining to Schlumberger Well Test package Safety Systems and ESDs in lieu of formal onsite inspection.
","WAR_START_DT":"2012-12-23","WELL_NAME":"PS002"},{"   ":182,"API12":608124001701,"TEXT_REMARK":"No Wireline Logs Run 12/30/2012: Monitor well pressure while waiting on daylight. 
Note: Jim Burt (Chevron) notified Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE Houma District) via email and voicemail at 05:00 hrs on 12/30/2012 that initiation of well testing operations would take place on 12/30/2012 at day break. Hold pre-job meeting on well test operation; open well and begin well test. 

12/31/2012: Continue well test operation.

01/01/2013: Continue well test operation.

01/02/2013: Continue well test operation. 
Note: Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE Houma District) approved the Revision of Permit to Modify Well at Surface Location Lease: G17015; Area: WR; Block: 758; Well Name: PS002; with API Number: 608124001701; at 07:41 hrs on 01/02/2013.

01/03/2013: Continue well test operation.

01/04/2013: Continue well test operation.

01/05/2013: Continue well test operation.
","WAR_START_DT":"2012-12-30","WELL_NAME":"PS002"},{"   ":183,"API12":608124001701,"TEXT_REMARK":"01/06/2013: Continue well test operation. Initiate well shut in and commence build up period.

01/07/2013: Continue well test operation.

01/08/2013: Continue well test operation.  

01/09/2013: Continue well test operation.

01/10/2013: Continue well test operation.

01/11/2013: Continue well test operation. Rig up to transfer production fluid from rig holding tanks to Pen 120 barge.

01/12/2013: Continue well test operation. Close the SCSSV and AMV. Open lower ball valve and bleed off landing string pressure to 2;500 psi. Continue transfer of production fluid from rig holding tanks to Pen 120 barge.
","WAR_START_DT":"2013-01-06","WELL_NAME":"PS002"},{"   ":184,"API12":608124001701,"TEXT_REMARK":"01/13/2013: Displace kill line and landing string to 6.6 ppg base oil. Rig up Halliburton Slickline; pull bore protection sleeve from SSPT; and install Cameron Lower Crown Plug. Continue transfer of production fluid from rig holding tanks to Pen 120 barge.

01/14/2013: Test Lower Crown Plug to 10;200 psi. Make up and run in hole with Upper Crown Plug on Halliburton Slickline and attempt to set UCP. Upper Crown Plug did not set and came back on setting tool. Make up back-up Upper Crown Plug and run in hole. Continue transfer of production fluid from rig holding tanks to Pen 120 barge.

01/15/2013: Set Upper Crown Plug. Pull out of hole with SSR running tool and find indicating pins at 5/8"; indicating unsuccessful set. Run back in hole with SSR running tool to fully set Upper Crown Plug; pull out of hole with SSR and indicating pins at 1/4"; indicating successful set. Test between Upper and Lower Crown Plug to 12;600 psia for 30 minutes. Test above Upper Crown Plug to 10;200 psi for 30 minutes. Rig down Halliburton Slickline unit. Displace choke line to 14.1 ppg CaBr2. Unlatch Cameron THRT and start displacing landing string from base oil to 14.1 ppg CaBr2.

01/16/2013: Finish displacing landing string from 6.6 ppg base oil to 14.1 ppg CaBr2. Rig down Expro SFT control lines and 2" chick-san. Remove torpedo packers from landing string. Rig up Tesco tongs and break out Expro SFT and move to center mousehole. Remove SLB well test coflex hose from Expro SFT. Wait on weather to lay down CCTLF. Start pressure test of UBSR and LBSR from Toolpusher's panel on Yellow pod.

01/17/2013: Continue pressure test BSRs to 250/7;200 psi from Toolpusher's panel on Yellow pod; function test BSRs from Driller's panel on Blue pod. Wait on weather until 13:00 hrs. Lay down CCTLF and associated equipment from Fwd well center to riser deck. 

01/18/2013: Trip out of hole with Expro SSTT/ Cameron THRT on 7-5/8" landing string from 6;987' to 116'.

01/19/2013: Lay down Tesco CDS tool. Transfer SSTT to center mousehole. Displace riser from 14.1 ppg CaBr2 to seawater. Bullhead 6.6 ppg base oil (55 bbls) down kill line to below SCSSV. Close SCSSV and perform negative test to loss of riser margin (690 psi on kill line). Displace choke and kill lines with seawater. Flush pumps. Rig up for riser pull operations. 
","WAR_START_DT":"2013-01-13","WELL_NAME":"PS002"},{"   ":185,"API12":608124001701,"TEXT_REMARK":"01/20/2013: Move rig 120' off location. Rig up riser gimbal. Clean diverter and lay out diverter. Unlatch BOP from WH using Blue Pod. Scope in and lock SDC ring. Remove drape hoses from termination joint. Move rig 500' off location. Lay out slip joint and termination joint. Remove Cameron IWOCS umbilical riser guide.

01/21/2013: Pull riser and BOP from 6;700' to 2;219'.

01/22/2013: Pull riser and BOP from 2;219' to surface. Perform EDS surface test. Place BOP in stow position. Rig down riser handling equipment. Move rig 2100' off location. Begin between well maintenance.

01/23/2013: Perform ROV bottom survey and pickup Compatts. End operations on PS002 ST01 at 24:00 hrs.
","WAR_START_DT":"2013-01-20","WELL_NAME":"PS002"},{"   ":186,"API12":608124005100,"TEXT_REMARK":"11/06/2011: Ran 36" from standby depth of 6773' to bottom; tagging bottom at 7050'. Jetted 36" casing in hole from 7050' to 7109'.

11/07/2011: Continued jetting 36" casing from 7109' to 7358'. Allowed to soak while monitoring with ROV.

11/08/08: Released CADA tool and pulled bit above LPH. Performed pump test.

","WAR_START_DT":"2011-11-06","WELL_NAME":"PS004"},{"   ":187,"API12":608124005100,"TEXT_REMARK":"04/01/2012: Continued with the heavy lift inspection of the Forward draw-works brakes and brake system. Waited on parts in order to finish the inspection. Made spacer shim for the re-alignment of the Forward MDDM/block retract dolly carriage. Installed the casing stabber bracket platform in the Forward derrick. Finished picking up the 6-5/8" FH 57# Range 2 rental drill pipe. Finished picking up the bit stands for the 26" drilling BHA.

04/02/2012: Finished the re-assembly of the Forward draw-works brake system and tested the brake system. Finished the re-alignment of the Forward MDDM/block retract dolly carriage system. Started rebuilding the riser fluid bearing at the Forward rotary. Picked up and rack back drill pipe in the derrick. Trial fit and functioned the "Tarantula" power slip system in the Aft rotary.

04/03/2012: Finished rebuilding the slip joint fluid bearing and pressure tested the fluid bearing on the Forward rotary. Observed a good pressure test. Lay down the slip joint from the Forward rotary in the riser bay. Picked up the 26" No.1 GT motor BHA and trip in to PS004 LPWH at 7;042' on the Aft rotary. Entered the PS004 LPWH and washed down and started drilling at 7;360'. Drilled from 7360' to 7950' on the Aft rotary. The Forward rotary finished the installation and testing the casing "Stab-Rite" equipment. Rigged down riser running equipment from the Forward MDDM and rigged up the drill equipment. Picked up the 26" No.2 PD drilling BHA and trip in to PS004 LPWH on the Forward rotary.

04/04/2012: Drilled from 7;950' to 8;408' (5' below the top of salt @ 8;403') with the 26" rock bit No.1 GT Positive Displacement motor BHA; circulated the hole clean and spotted 11.0 ppg super-saturated salt water base mud in the wellbore. Pulled out of hole with the 26" rock bit No.1 GT Positive Displacement motor BHA and ran in hole with the 26" Poly Diamond Crystal bit No.2 PowerDrive BHA. Drilled salt from 8;408' to 8;700' (avg ROP = 39 fph).

04/05/2012: Drilled 26" hole in salt from 8;700' to 9;857' (AROP - 48.2 fph). Took surveys and pumped 100-bbl; 13.0 ppg high viscosity super salt-saturated water base mud sweeps after each connection.

04/06/2012: Drilled 26" hole from 9;857' to 10;653' (AROP - 45.5 fph). Pumped spacers; displaced "black water" fluid caliper to seafloor and spotted 16.0 ppg pill on bottom. Flow checked well and prepared to TOH.

04/07/2012: FWD: Finished TOH with 26" drilling assembly on Fwd rotary; jetting LPWH on way out. AFT: TIH with 22" casing and landed HPWH out in LPWH with casing shoe at 10;584'. Overpull tested HPWH to confirm that it was locked into the LPWH. R/U cement line while circulating 475 bbls of 12.5 ppg salt-saturated WBM down DP at 8 bpm in preparation for cementing casing.
","WAR_START_DT":"2012-04-01","WELL_NAME":"PS004"},{"   ":188,"API12":608124005100,"TEXT_REMARK":"04/08/2012: Pumped 200-bbl lignite pill followed by 300 bbls of MUDPUSH II spacer. Cemented 22" casing with 9;963 cu ft of lead slurry followed by 881 cu ft of tail slurry with good cement returns to seafloor. Preloaded the HPWHH to 2MM lbs and confirmed with ROV. Released the DQ MRLD tool from the HPWHH. Racked back the GSI cement head stand. Inserted Nerf ball in DP and flushed the landing and inner strings with SW to clear cement residue. TOH with landing and inner string from 10;408' to 7;020'. Ran BOP stack on marine riser to 2;369'.

04/09/2012: RIH with BOP stack on marine riser to 6;799'. Pressure tested choke/kill/rigid conduit and boost lines. M/U flex/termination and slip joints. Installed drape hoses and storm loops.

04/10/2012: Finish running BOPs on riser; installed storm loops; closed and pinned SDC ring; hooked up fluid bearing and slip joint hoses. Performed dummy run and landed and latched BOPs on HPWHH. Stroked out slip joint and installed diverter. Performed deadman test. R/D riser equipment and tested 22" casing against UBSRs. R/U drilling equipment. Performed diverter flow and sequence test and ROV invention test. TIH to 5;407' with 18-1/8" x 21" drilling BHA and Dril-Quip BOPITT/Dual Cam test assembly.

04/11/2012: TIH and made up BOP test stand and line. Landed out BOPITT in HPWHH at bit depth of 7;401' and pressure tested BOPs and associated valves as per BSEE and Chevron requirements using the IPT (Innovative Pressure Testing) SureTec system. Function tested BOPs from CCU on Yellow Pod.

04/12/2012: Finished testing BOPs. TOH and racked back DQ BOPITT/Dual Cam assembly. Functioned BSRs and CSRs from Toolpusher's panel on Blue and Yellow Pods. Conducted diverter function test from CCU. TIH with 18-1/8" x 21" drilling BHA and tagged top of cement at 10;488'. Drilled cement to 10;534' while displacing well from seawater to 11.2 ppg SBM. Lined up all surface equipment in drilling mode. 

04/13/2012: Displaced well and surface equipment to 11.2 ppg SBM. Pressure tested BOP "test rams". Drilled out shoe track; cleaned out to 10;653'; drilled to 10;663' and performed FIT to 13.2 ppg. Activated AnderReamer and drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole section from 10;663' to 11;219'.

04/14/2012: Drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole section from 11;219' to 13;290'.
","WAR_START_DT":"2012-04-08","WELL_NAME":"PS004"},{"   ":189,"API12":608124005100,"TEXT_REMARK":"04/15/2012: Directionally drill 18-1/8" x 21" hole section from 13;290' to 15;345' (AROP: 85.6 fph).

04/16/2012: Drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole from 15;345' to 15;520' (initiated KO at 15;400'). P/U to 15;371' and made up side entry sub. Circulated down hole via side entry sub and boosted riser while changing out ruptured Kelly hose and re-racking a stand of 16" casing that fell across the derrick from the fingerboards. 

04/17/2012: Finished installing Kelly hose; pressure tested Kelly hose 250/7000 psi; rig down test lines and re-calibrated block. TIH from 15;371' to 15;520'. Established drilling parameters and directionally drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole section from 15;520' to 17;020' (AROP: 71.4 fph).

04/18/2012: Directionally drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole section from 17;020' to 17;775'. Function tested BOPs. Directionally drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole section from 17;775' to 18;680' (AROP: 70.6 fph).

04/19/2012: Directionally drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole to 19;192'. Circulated high viscosity sweep surface to surface. TOH and P/U DQ BOPITT/dual cam tool assembly. Function tested Diverter; TIH and and released from the DQ dual cam tool. Function tested CSRs/BSRs.

04/20/2012: TOH to 22" casing shoe. Replaced roller on forward MDDM block dolly. TIH and directionally drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole from 19;192' to 19;511' (AROP: 53.2 fph).

04/21/2012: Directionally drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole from 19;961' to 20;140'. While reaming from 19;987'; drill string torque up and stalled out. Jarred back to 19;780'. Circulated and displaced 12.1 ppg SBM to 11.8 ppg SBM while reciprocating drill pipe.
","WAR_START_DT":"2012-04-15","WELL_NAME":"PS004"},{"   ":190,"API12":608124005100,"TEXT_REMARK":"04/22/2012: Directionally drilled 18-1/8" x 21" from 19;961' to 20;140'; effect repairs on pipe racking system during drilling ops. Work drill string due to obstruction downhole at 20;140' - implemented various methods to free up BHA - no success. CBU from 20;140' to determine lithology. Continued jarring and worked stuck pipe free at 20;086'. TOH to 20;056'. 

04/23/2012: Slipped drill line; serviced rig equipment and performed derrick DROPS inspection. Circulated to condition mud and increased MW from 11.8 ppg to 11.9 ppg. Drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole section from 20;140' to 20;455'.

04/24/2012: Drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole section from 20;455' to 21;134' (AROP: 29.5 fph).

04/25/2012: Drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole section from 21;134' to 21;500 (AROP: 61 fph). Circulated wellbore clean. Pulled out of hole from 21;500' to 12;157'.

04/26/2012: Finished pulling out of the well from 12;157' to surface with the 18-1/8" x 21" BHA. Attempted to install drill pipe power slips but encountered interference problems. Picked up and ran in the well with a "new" 18-1/8" x 21" BHA from surface to 8;150'. Spaced out the drill pipe test joints across the BOP and started pressure testing the BOP.

04/27/2012: Finished pressure testing BOPs; function tested BOP and Diverter; ran in the well with the 18-1/8" x 21" BHA from 8;283' to 10;089' at the 22" casing shoe; activated the 21" reamer; continued running in the well with the 18-1/8" x 21" BHA from 10;089' to 20;160'; tagged up with 40k and washed down from 20;160' to 20;280' and running in the well with the 18-1/8" x 21" BHA from 20;280' to 21;293'.

04/28/2012: Directional drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole section from 21;500' to 22;052'; stopped drilling operations and pulled out of the well from 22;052' to 20;260' due to power management issues with the mud module SIPLinks that control the Hex-mud pumps.
","WAR_START_DT":"2012-04-22","WELL_NAME":"PS004"},{"   ":191,"API12":608124005100,"TEXT_REMARK":"04/29/2012: Finished pulling out of the well from 20;260' to 19;500' due to power management issues with the mud module SIPLinks that control the Hex-mud pumps. Waited on completion of repairs to the starboard-side Mud Module SIPLinks that power the Hex-mud pumps. Once the starboard-side Mud Module SIPLinks were repaired; started circulating and conditioning the 11.9 ppg SBM and sweeping the wellbore clean at 19;500'.

06/28/2012: Installed storm loops; closed SDC ring; moved rig over location; latched LMRP to BOP and performed 100 klbs O/P test. Peformed ERA offset test; tested rigid conduit line; laid out landing joint and installed diverter. R/D riser handling equipment; function tested diverter; displaced riser to 13.6 ppg SBM and R/U drilling equipment. TIH to 6;851' with RTTS retrieving tool. Slipped and cut drill line and performed ROV intervention BSR function test.

06/29/2012: Function tested upper BSRs and lower CSRs. TIH and tested LMRP connector to 4;900 psi. TIH and circulated high viscosity slug to surface. Engaged and released the Halliburton RTTS packer with 90 klbs overpull. TOH to 21;468' to space out for testing the BOP with 6-5/8". M/U double dutch test stand and R/U test line. Pressure tested BOP stack against 6-5/8"; 34 ppf DP as per testing program. R/D test line and moved double dutch stand to aft rotary. TOH from 21;468' to 13;744' while continuing to test choke and kill manifold. Cleaned cement rings from connections as required.

06/30/2012: TOH to 12;473' and spaced out to place 5-7/8" DP test joints across the BOP stack. Pressure tested against 5-7/8" DP as per program. Function tested BOPs and diverter. 05/13/2015: Unset the TCP packer and POOH to 27;419' with the spent TCP assembly. Monitored the well on trip tank with losses at 6 bph for first 10 minutes; then stabilized at 4.8 bph. TOH from 27;419' to 15;136' and flow checked; with fluid losses at 6.0 bph. TOH from 15;136' to 9;585'. Closed annular and circulated through TCP BHA taking returns up choke line to remove any residual gun gas - no gas observed. Continued to TOH from 9;585' to 1;990' - note: losing 4.8 bph. 

05/14/2015: POOH with TCP assembly to surface. While inspecting the box end of gun #40 (blank) in the slips; the booster was still intact; indicating that all remaining guns did not fire (from 28;114' to 28;800' unfired). Laid out unspent TCP guns #41 through #1 (no shots fired). 

05/15/2015: Monitored the well on trip tank with fluid losses at a rate of 4.8 bph while waiting on TCP equipment to arrive. TIH with TCP gun assembly #2 from surface to 1;682'. Detected smoke in the FWD machinery space. Secured well. All personnel mustered at primary muster location. Fire extinguished; DP affected from smoke. Maintained yellow watch circle status while DP issues remedied; smoke was cleared from machinery space and assessment was completed on equipment. There were no injuries due to the incident.

Note: On 05/15/2015 Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) was contacted via phone at 23:01 hrs.; and notified that #2 Thruster on STBD side Forward Machinery space was down due to a Siplink meltdown. He was also informed that the well was secured with BSRs closed; and that we had also lost Thrusters #1 and #6 FWD due to smoke sensors; however; we maintained station keeping ability. NOTE: USCG was also notified about the incident by the ship's captain.

05/16/2015: Siplink damage was isolated to #2 Thruster only. Maintained yellow watch circle status with BHA at 1;600' and UBSRs closed. Did not lose more than 1 to 2 feet from station throughout the incident. Monitored the wellbore on mini strip tank until smoke was cleared from the starboard forward machinery space; five thrusters (#1; #3; #4; #5; and #6) were 100% functional. Risk assessments were performed and Well Specific Operating Guidelines (WSOG) were adjusted for operating with five thrusters. Received permission from USCG to return to work. Wait on permission to go back to work from BSEE and CVX.

Notes: 

On 05/16/2015 at 08:05; Mr. Chris Gerlitz (Chevron) notified Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) via email that the DCL had a Siplink meltdown that caused a thruster to go offline and produced smoke in the Machinery Space. The smoke caused additonal thrusters to shut down and the well was immeditately secured without losing any station keeping capabilities. All necessary precautions were taken and there are currently 5 of 6 thrusters fully functioning.

On 05/16/2015; Mr. Josh Ladner (BSEE) contacted the rig and spoke to Mr. Donald LeGros (CVX - LDSM) concerning the incident and was informed of the current status.

On 05/16/2015 at 08:05 hrs; Mr. Chris Gerlitz sent a request to Mr. Bobby Nelson for an extension for the BOP and diverter function due to suspended operations. We will perform both functions when drillpipe is across the BOP. At 08:11 hrs; Mr. Chris Gerlitz received permission from Mr. Bobby Nelson to delay BOP function testing until the rig is deemed safe for work.

On 05/16/2015 at 23:25 hrs; Mr. Chris Gerlitz provided to Mr. Bobby Nelson the approval by DNV and the USCG of the acceptance criteria for the dynamic positioning system with the isolation of thruster #2.

Note: Performed Life Boat Training in lieu of weekly Fire and Abandon Drill.

Note: On 05/18/2015 at 13:09 hrs; Mr. Chris Gerlitz notified Mr. Bobby Nelson re: simulations of thrusters required for varying weather conditions; along with the current status of repairs on thruster #2. 

5/19/2015: Unset the TCP packer and opened the annular and monitored for one hour with losses at 18 bph. TOH to 27;371'. Monitored the well with losses to formation at a rate of 16.8 bph. POOH from 27;371' to 9;114'. Closed annular and CBU through choke and kill lines; no gas noted. Opened annular and boosted riser. TOH from 9;114' to 6;000'. Fluid loss rate 15 bph.  

5/20/2015: POOH with spent TCP from 6;000' to surface and lay down TCP assembly. TIH on 5-7/8" DP with deburr assemblies from surface to 16;181'. Losing fluid to formation at 16 bph.

5/21/2015: TIH with deburr assemblies to top of perforations. Wash and ream area and circulate bottoms up. Well losing at 15 bph.

5/22/2015: Completed circulating bottoms up and POOH from 28;953' to 27;832'. TIH from 27;281' to 28;953'. POOH from 28;953' to 26;875'. Performed BOP pressure tests from Toolpusher's panel on Yellow Pod against 5-7/8" DP and 6-5/8" Stim Tech using 14.1 ppg CaBr2 per the IPT test plan. Annular and associated valves tested to 250/4;500 psi; UVBRs/MVBRs and associated valves tested to 250/8;000 psi - tests successful. Function tested the BOPs on 5-7/8" DP from Driller's panel on Blue Pod - test successful. Function tested diverter from Toolpusher's panel. POOH to 18;890' - test successful.

5/23/2015: POOH from 18;890' to surface and lay down deburr assemblies. Pressure tested the kelly hose to 250/7;000 psi; and the upper; lower and middle IBOPs to 250;10;000 psi on the primary MDDM and choke manifold per the IPT test plan - tests successful. 
","WAR_START_DT":"2015-05-17","WELL_NAME":"PS004"},{"   ":214,"API12":608124005103,"TEXT_REMARK":"05/24/2015: Finished rigging up tubing handling equipment. (Functioned BSRs offline from Driller's panel; Blue Pod - good test.) RIH from surface to 2;938' with gravel pack assemblies.

05/28/2015: P/U on tool string from 28;911' to 28;883'. Pumped acid job. Performed mini-frac injection test. Performed frac job on Zone #1. POOH from 28;883' to 28;667'.

05/29/2015: Pumped acid job. Performed mini-frac injection test. Performed frac job on Zone #2.
 
05/30/2015: POOH from 28;667' to 28;341'. Pumped acid job. Performed mini-frac injection test. Performed frac job on Zone #3. 
","WAR_START_DT":"2015-05-24","WELL_NAME":"PS004"},{"   ":215,"API12":608124005103,"TEXT_REMARK":"05/31/2015: POOH with HES service tool assembly on 5-7/8" DP from 28;368' to 27;944'. Pumped acid job. Performed mini-frac injection test. Performed frac job on Zone #4. 

06/01/2015: POOH from 27;944' to 27;687'. Service tool failure prior to Zone #5. POOH with service tool from 27;687' to 6;822'. Function tested BOP from Driller's panel on Yellow Pod and Toolpusher's panel on Blue Pod. Function diverter from Driller's panel - good tests.

06/02/2015: POOH with service tool from 6;822' to surface. Functioned BSRs - good test. P/U new HES service tool assembly and TIH from surface to 11;874'. 
 
06/03/2015: TIH with service tool assembly #2 from 11;874' to 27;690'.	

Note: On 06/03/2015 @ 13:02 hrs; Mr. Chris Gerlitz (Chevron) received approval from Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) via email "to delay BOP function/pressure 48 hrs beyond the completion of Procedure Step 13; the goal being that the production packer will be set within that time frame and the BOP will be tested as captured in Step 14."

06/04/2015: Pumped acid job. Performed mini-frac injection test. Performed frac job on Zone #5. POOH with service tool assembly #2 from 27;690' to 21;120'. 

06/05/2015: Continued to POOH with service tool assembly #2 from 21;120' to surface. PU and TIH with Zone 1-5 HES isolation assembly and fluid loss device on 5-7/8" DP from surface to 1;663'. 
 
06/06/2015: TIH from 1;663' to 27;284' with isolation assembly. Opened sleeves across Zones 1-5 and observed losses of 500 bph while TIH. Landed isolation assembly and losses ceased. Pressure tested isolation assembly and fluid loss device to 1;000 psi - good test. POOH with running tool from 27;266' to 25;369'. 
","WAR_START_DT":"2015-05-31","WELL_NAME":"PS004"},{"   ":216,"API12":608124005103,"TEXT_REMARK":"06/07/2015: Function tested BOPs from Driller's panel; Blue Pod; and Toolpusher's panel; Yellow Pod;and Diverter from Toolpusher' Panel - both good tests. TIH with TNT Packer Assembly on 5-7/8" TFM drill pipe to 1;552'.
