06/08/2015: TIH from 1;552' to 27;229' with TNT Packer Assembly and sting into PBR to set TNT Permanent Packer. Test TNT Permanent Packer and casing to 4;000 psi for 30 mins with 14.1 ppg CaBr2 - good test. POOH with TNT Hydraulic Setting Tool from 26;959' to 26;862'. 

Note: On 06/08/2015 @ 15:33 hrs; Mr. Chris Gerlitz received permission from Mr. Bobby Nelson via email that Chevron may proceed with an alternate casing testing plan for the remainder of completion operations; provided no prolonged operations have occurred as outlined in 250.518(b). Casing will be tested during permanent packer installation to 4;000 psi for 30 minutes and the tubing by casing annulus will be tested once the tubing is landed to 5;000 psi for 15 minutes.

06/09/2015: TOH from 26;682' to 25;327' MD and tested BOPs from Driller's panel; Blue Pod to 250/8;000 psi - good test. Annular and associated valves tested to 250/4;500 psi. Kelly hose tested to 250/7;000 psi; and MDDM valves tested to 250/10;000 psi. Functioned tested the BOP from the Driller's panel; Blue Pod; and Toolpusher's panel; Yellow Pod - good test. POOH with setting tool from 25;327' to surface. Cleaned and cleared rig floor.
 
06/10/2015: M/U and TIH with Bore Protector Retrieval Running Tool (BPRRT) and jetting assembly. Jetted SSPT; function tested the 9-5/8" fixed rams; and pressure tested the 9-5/8" ram to 250/8;000 psi - good test. Unseated the Bore Protector; jetted SSPT and CBU. TOH with BPRRT and jetting assy to 5;604'.	

Step 17 of the approved completion procedure: Land & Lock the TH in the horizontal production tree testing between TH and 9-5/8 Lower Pipe Rams with 14.1 ppg CaBr2 completion fluid to 7;700 psi surface. Test TH per Cameron procedure.

Note: On 06/10/2015 @ 07:56; Mr. Chris Gerlitz notified Mr. Bobby Nelson that the SSXT would be powered from the Jack & St. Malo (JSM) FPU due to the inability to deploy the IWOCS system in the high loop currents existing at this time. 06/11/2015: TOH from 5;604' to surface with BPRRT and jetting assembly. Rigged down drilling equipment and rigged up production tubing handling equipment. Installed TH running tool umbilical through the derrick. Picked up upper completion lower assembly and RIH on 4-1/2" single to 309'. R/U control lines in derrick and terminated tandem CIM's and DHTPG.

06/12/2015: Completed securing control lines on DHPTG. Rig up equipment for 4-1/2" tubing and control lines. TIH from 309' to 10;518' with 4-1/2"; installing clamps at each connection.
 
06/13/2015: TIH from 10;518' to 17;383' with 4-1/2" tubing and terminated control lines to SCSSV. Function tested SCSSV to 10;000 psi for 15 mins on chart - good test.
","WAR_START_DT":"2015-06-07","WELL_NAME":"PS004"},{"   ":217,"API12":608124005103,"TEXT_REMARK":"06/14/2015: Completed terminations and pressure testing on the SCSSV and LDHI-CIM - good test. 06/15/2015: Waited on weather to make up tubing hanger assembly. Monitored well on trip tank; well static.

Note: On 06/15/2015 at 10:07 hrs; Mr. Chris Gerlitz (Chevron) notified Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) on the status of the #2 thruster repair and provided an update of one (1) day for the thruster to potentially be back online.

06/16/2015: Waited on weather. M/U tubing hanger assy. Terminated and externally tested SCSSV control lines - good test. Tested CIMs and TEC gauge line fitting - good test. Conducted test on DHPTGs - good test. Function tested SCSSV on both ports 3 times each - good test. Internally pressure tested both ports on SCSSV to 10;000 psi / 10 min - good test. Recorded gauge pressures and temperatures. Re-installed the helix and secured all control lines. Transferred land and lock assy to forward rotary. Latched land and lock to tubing hanger. Tested control lines SV1; SV2 and utility stab to 10;000 psi for 15 minutes - Good test

Note: On 06/16/2015 at 06:44 hrs; Mr. Chris Gerlitz notified Mr. Bobby Nelson that the ROV is unable to launch to perform riser inspection due 06/16/2015 due to high currents and that the riser inspection would be performed once the sea currents are acceptable.

06/17/2015: Completed testing land and lock assembly - good test. TIH from 20;191' to 26;916' with production tubing and associated jewelry on 7-5/8" landing string. Land hanger with seals in PBR and confirmed space out. P/U to 26;955' with seals above the PBR.	

Note: On 06/17/2015 at 13:08 hrs; Mr. Chris Gerlitz notified Mr. Bobby Nelson that the riser and BOP inspection from 1;200' below surface to BOP had been completed.

06/18/2015: Pumped inhibited packer. P/U Compensated Coil Tubing Lift Frame (CCTLF) to rig floor and R/U same. P/U Surface Flow Tree (SFT) assy. Installed 2 of 3 torpedo packers. 

06/19/2015: Completed installing torpedo packers. Landed tubing hanger. Unlocked and stroked out CCTLF; adjusted pressures and position. Pressure tested tubing hanger; and casing x tubing annulus - good test. Engaged and tested electrical penetrators. Pressure tested the SFT; landing string; and tubing. Performed differential test on the SCSSV with 5;000 psi differential pressure - all tests good. Rigged up slickline equipment. 

06/20/2015: Completed rigging up slickline. Test lubricator - good test. Retrieve isolation sleeve. Reverse out 1-1/2 times the tubing volume. Displaced landing string and kill line to base oil. Bled off tubing x casing annulus. RIH with slickline and set lower crown plug. POOH. Began testing lower crown plug.

Note: On 06/20/2015 at 13:19 hrs; Mr. Bobby Nelson approved Mr. Chris Gerlitz's request to perform SCSSV negative test after opening FS1 valve.
","WAR_START_DT":"2015-06-14","WELL_NAME":"PS004"},{"   ":218,"API12":608124005103,"TEXT_REMARK":"06/21/2015: Finished pressure testing lower crown plug to 10;590 psi (for 15 mins) from above - good test. 06/24/2015: POOH with Land and Lock from 137' to surface. Pulled and laid down diverter. Made up landing joint and stroked in slip joint in preparation for unlatching BOP. 

06/25/2015: Unlatched BOP from Jack PS004 at 01:10 hrs. Moved rig 800' south of Jack PS004 to DOZ. Unlocked SDC ring and secured. Laid out landing joint and pulled heavy wall pup from 6;980' to 6;864'. Removed drape hoses and pulled termination joint from 6;864' to 6;787'. Pulled pup joints from 6;787' to 6;722'. Pulled BOP/LMRP on marine riser from 6;722' to 3;046'. 

06/26/2015: Pulled BOP/LMRP on marine riser from 3;046' to 119'. BOP on cart at 10:00 hrs. Remove riser from LMRP and laid out final 2 riser joints. Skidded BOP out of moonpool and pinned LMRP/BOP. DCL ROV installed tree cap; locked in place; and injected corrosion inhibitor.

Note: On 06/26/2015 at 12:09 hrs; Mr. Chris Gerlitz (Chevron) provided Mr. Bobby Nelson and Mr. Josh Ladner (BSEE) 72 hour email notification for initial BOP testing for Jack PS001.

06/27/2015: M/V Juan C ROV performed final SSPT survey and clear bottom survey.
","WAR_START_DT":"2015-06-21","WELL_NAME":"PS004"},{"   ":219,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"11/08/2011: Ran 36" from standby depth of 1;271' to Mudline at 7;053'. Jetted 36" conductor from 7;053' to 7;361'. Allowed casing to soak.

11/11/2011: Standby on PS005 while commission operations for the cement unit take place.

","WAR_START_DT":"2011-11-08","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":220,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"11/13/2011: RIH with 26" Mud Motor Assembly to 7361'. Drill with 26" BHA to 8320'. Dispace well to 11.0 ppg SSPAD mud. POOH to surface and rack back BHA.

Mr. Gabriel Barragan (CVX) received a verbal approval from Amy Wilson (BSEE Houma District) to not perform a clear bottom survey before leaving WR 758 Jack PS005 to WR634 St. Malo PN001 as the rig Discoverer Clear Leader will be shortly latching up to Jack PS005 for deepening RPD and will perform the clear bottom survey when they complete approved work.

11/18/2011: POOH to 300' above LPWHH. Run 3328' of 22" casing on Aft. R/U and cement 22" casing with 10;735 cu-ft of Class H cement.

11/19/2011: POOH above HPWH. TIH with 12-1/4" BHA. Tag top of cement at 10;160' with 30 klbs down. Displace 22" to 12.5 ppg inhibited PAD mud. POOH.

Slip and cut 149' drill line. The Clear Leader arrived on location at 06:30 hrs. Aker installing upgrades to Aft MDDM. Continued general housekeeping. Subsea dry firing/function testing BOPs from Subsea CCU; Driller's panel; and Toolpusher's panel - both Yellow and Blue Pods. Test good.

11/28/2011: Subsea powered up hydraulics to stack and finished checking all SEMs. Dry fired EDS. Troubleshoot and repair SPM for Blue rigid conduit isolation dump valve. Function test BOPs from Blue Pod from CCU in subsea. Stump testing BOPs at 21:00 hrs. Offload BHA components and big bore tools from Ms Virgie. Continue rig PMs.

11/29/2011: Finished stump testing of the BOPs; prepped the BOPs to move to the moonpool. Picked up stands of 18-1/8" x 21" BHA into stands and rackback. Calibrated the dynamic positioning acoustic grid arounf the PS005 well location.

11/30/2011: Prepped the BOPs to skid from the parking spot in front of the BOP module. Skidded the BOPS from the parking spot to the moonpool Forward rotary well center. Made up slick double of marine riser to BOPs. Picked up BOPs from the beams and splashed the BOPs at 06:35 hrs. Made initial pressure test of BOPs to slick double marine riser connection. Ran marine riser and BOP to 5219'.

12/01/2011: Ran BOPs from 5219' to 6794' on 22 "Green" marine riser joints; made up 10' riser pup joint and ran BOPs from 6794' to 6804'; pressure tested the choke; kill; boost and rigid conduit lines; made up termination and slip riser joints and ran BOPs from 6804' to 6979'; made up drape hoses and pressure tested drape hoses/ choke; kill; boost and rigid conduit lines; made up "heavy weight" 16' riser pup and landing joint and ran BOPs from 6979' to 7039'. Moved over HPH. Landed and latched the BOPs. Tested casing and BSRs to 250/2200 psi for 30 min. Debra Campise relayed via email: "I just spoke to Bobby Nelson and as of 8:20 a.m.; he gave me verbal approval to latch up. He will get the RPD approved for us as soon as he can so that we'll also have the written approval."

12/02/2011: Finished installing diverter; conducted the BOP "Deadman" test and DP offset test; rigged down riser handling equipment; rigged up BHA/drill pipe handling equipment; tripped in the well with the 18-1/8" x 21" rotary steerable BHA and BOP test plug tool; performed diverter test and started pressure testing BOPs.

12/03/2011: Finished pressure testing BOPs; performed function test of BOPs; tripped out of the well with the 18-1/8" x 21" RS drilling BHA/BOPITT; changed out BOPITT with WSRRT; HWDP and drilling jars; tripped back in the well; set wear sleeve in HPWH; tripped in the well to the TOC of the temporary abandonment plug; displaced the well with 11.2 ppg SBM.
","WAR_START_DT":"2011-11-27","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":223,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"12/04/2011: Finished displacing the wellbore from seawater to 11.2 ppg SBM; performed a "choke drill" with the on tour drill crew; finished drilling out cement inside the 22" casing shoe track; wash down and clean out the rathole below the 22" casing shoe; drilled 10' of new formation to 10;445'; circulated wellbore clean; performed FIT to a 13.0 ppg EMW and drilled salt from 10;445' to 10;517'.

12/05/2011: Drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole in salt from 10;517' to 11;750'. Picked up and racked back the landing string drill pipe on the Aft drill floor.

12/06/2011: Drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole from 11;750' to 13;131'. Increased MW from 11.2 ppg to 11.6 ppg as per program. Displaced choke and kill lines with 11.6 ppg SBM.

12/07/2011: Drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole from 13;131' to 14;870'. Increased MW from 11.6 ppg to 11.8 ppg as per program. Displaced choke and kill lines with 11.8 ppg SBM. AROP: 72.4 fph.

12/08/2011: Drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole from 14;870' to 16;620'. Increased MW from 11.8 ppg to 12.2 ppg as per program. Displaced choke and kill lines with 12.2 ppg SBM. AROP: 72.9 fph.

12/09/2011: Drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole from 16;620' to 17;620' (AROP: 71.4 fph). Down-linked to PowerDrive and directionally drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole from 17;620' to 17;712' (KOP: 17;665'). Worked and jarred stuck pipe free at 17;712' while circulating and increasing MW from 12.2 ppg to 12.4 ppg.

12/10/2011: TOH to 9;981'. P/U BOPSTT and DQ dual cam tool. Perfromed BOP function test. TIH to 17;029' and hung BOPSTT off in WH. Released from dual cam tool. P/U and functioned BSRs/CSRs. Slipped and cut drill line and performed planned maintenance. TIH and screwed into dual cam tool. TOH from 17;029' to 16;942'.
","WAR_START_DT":"2011-12-04","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":224,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"12/11/2011: TOH and racked back Drill-Quip dual cam tool and Special BOP Isolation Test Tool. TIH to 17;712' and directionally drill 18-1/8" x 21" hole to 18;021'. Began increasing MW from 12.4 ppg to 12.5 ppg while working and reaming tight interval. Continued drilling from 18;021' to 18;040'.

12/12/2011: Directionally drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole in salt from 18;430' to 18;900' (average 39 ft/hr ROP). Reamed and worked pipe as required; with high torque and intermittent sticking; to condition the hole prior to connections.

12/13/2011: Directionally drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole in salt from 18;900' to 19;553' (average 46.7 ft/hr ROP). Reamed and worked pipe as required due to hole conditions; washed and reamed due to sticking drill string; continued to drill to 19;824'; pumped 100-bbl 12.9-ppg HiVis sweep and circulate bottoms up; while slowly pulling BHA/bit out of 18-1/8" rathole at midnight.

12/14/2011: Finished bottoms up; 3 std short trip; circulated and cut mud wt to 12.1 ppg; POOH to 14;000'; TIH wash/ream tight spots noted on trip out to 18;556' at midnight.

12/15/2011: Finished TIH and wash/ream wellbore to 19;824'; circulated and cut mud wt to 11.8 ppg; POOH and backream tight spots; TOH to 9;981'; installed dual cam tool; TIH with BOP test tool and 18-1/8" x 21" BHA to 16;987' - midnight depth.

12/16/2011: Finished TIH with DQ Dual Cam Tool; landed and release from tool; function tested BSRs; S&C drill line; M/U and unseated test tool; TOH with Dual Cam Tool; R/B tool; TIH; M/U test std assy; spaced out and test BOPs on #40 DP. 8 of 11 subsea BOP tests complete at midnight.

12/17/2011: Finished testing BOPs; function tested BOPs; R/D BOP test std assy; TIH and wash/ream tight spots with drilling assy to TD. Drilled ahead to 19;845' - midnight depth.
","WAR_START_DT":"2011-12-11","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":225,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"12/18/2011: Drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole section to 20; 190'; troubleshoot communication loss to power drive and attempt to drill ahead w/o success due to drill string stalling on bottom; circ hole clean; TOH with drig assy to 13;464' - midnight depth.

12/19/2011: Cont TOH with drlg assy to surface; R/B drig assy (noticed two(2) pieces of ARC tool missing); service rig and function BSR/CSR; P/U mill/junk basket fishing assy and TIH to 7;463' at midnight.

12/20/2011: Tripped in the well with the 17-1/2" mill/boot basket fishing Bottom Hole Assembly from 7;463' to 20;190'; milled up the two(2) Antenna Shield split key pieces missing from the Schlumberger ARC from 20;190' to 20;197' and tripped out of the well with the 18" mill/boot basket fishing Bottom Hole Assembly from 20;197' to 9;300'.

12/21/2011: Continued to trip out of the well with the 17-1/2" mill/boot basket fishing Bottom Hole Assembly from 9;300' to 337'. Laid down the 17-1/2" mill/boot basket fishing Bottom Hole Assembly and inspected for pieces of the milled up fish. Picked up and ran in the well with the 18-1/8" x 21" Rotary Steerable Drilling Bottom Hole Assembly from surface to 175'. Surface activated and tested the 21" AndeReamer successfully. Continued to run in the well with the 18-1/8" x 21" Rotary Steerable Drilling Bottom Hole Assembly from 175' to 10;269'. Function tested the BOPs and diverter. Continued to run in the well with the 18-1/8" x 21" Rotary Steerable Drilling Bottom Hole Assembly from 10;269' to 18;269'.

12/22/2011: Continued to trip in hole with 18 1/8" x 21" BHA to 17;491'. Broke circulation and downlinked Schlumberger PowerDrive/MWD/LWD tools. Continued to trip in hole to 19;777'. Washed down from 19;777' to 20;090'. Reamed from 20;090' to 20;188'; unable to drill ahead due to pressure drop in drill string. Pulled off bottom from 20;188' to 20;080' and troubleshoot the DCL's circulation system. System checked out OK. Decision was made to pull out of the well to inspect the drill string and Bottom Hole Assembly for signs of a washout. Pulled out of the well from 20;080' to 4;382'.

12/23/2011: Continued to pull out of hole with 18-1/8" x 21" BHA from 4;382' to 1;051'. Made up BHA to MDDM and circulated through the BHA while observing stand pipe pressure results. Pulled out of the well to 9-1/2" drill collars and observed a stress fracture in the drill collar connection box. Held a pre-job safety meeting and continued pulling out of the well with 18-1/8" x 21" BHA; utilized a fishing overshot to handle the damaged drill collar connection box. Changed out components between BHA #5 and BHA #6 that we did not have replacements for. Run in the well with the replacement 18-1/8" x 21" rotary steerable drilling BHA #6 to 175' and activated the 21" AnderReamer. 03/09/2012: Troubleshot MDDM dolly extend and retract function. TOH from 27;848' to surface and layed out 9-7/8" EZSV setting tool. Cleaned rig floor and performed rig maintenance. R/U Schlumberger wireline equipment. P/U and RIH with IBC/CBL/CCL/GR logging tool string to 24;816'.

03/10/2012: POOH with IBC/CBL/CCL/GR logging tools and R/D Schlumberger E-line. M/U and TIH with 9-7/8" polish mill to BOPs; slip and cut drill line; cont TIH with 9-7/8" polish mill to top of 9-7/8" liner; polished and cleaned liner top as per Halliburton procedures; closed UPRs and marked DP for space out; and pumped 50-bbl; 14.0 ppg high viscosity sweep.
","WAR_START_DT":"2012-03-04","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":237,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"03/11/2012: TOH with polish mill assembly. TIH with BOP test and LDS seat protector running and retrieving tool assembly. Tested BOPs as per testing program.

03/13/2012: TOH with LDS and retrieval tool. Slipped and cut drilling line and serviced rig floor equipment. R/D drilling equipment and R/U Frank's casing equipment. TIH with 9-7/8" and 10-3/4" tieback casing to 14;000'.

03/14/2012: Ran in the well the 9-7/8" x 10-3/4" tieback casing string from 14;000' to 17;824'; made up the 10-3/4" casing hanger to the 9-7/8" x 10-3/4" tieback casing string; ran in the well the 9-7/8" x 10-3/4" tieback casing string from 17;824' to 24;820' on 6-5/8" 57# drill pipe landing string; made up the cement head stand to the 6-5/8" 57# drill pipe landing string; ran in the well from 24;820' to 24;870' to confirm the proper space out of the tieback seal assembly and 10-3/4" casing hanger landout on the 18-3/4" High Pressure Wellhead Housing (HPWH). Picked up from 24;870' to 24;820' and circulated and conditioned the wellbore fluid for cementing operations.

03/15/2012: Held PJSM and rigged up cement lines and started to pump 10-3/4" x 9-7/8" production cement job. Set 10-3/4" tieback hanger. Set 10-3/4" seal assembly on HPWH and test. Release Dril-Quip hanger running tool and jet wellhead clean. Retest 10-3/4" seal assembly on HPWH - good. Lay down Blackhawk cmt head; circulate riser out; POOH with 10-3/4" hanger landing string.

03/16/2012: Ran in the well with the Lead Impression Tool; landed out the Lead Impression Tool in the 18-3/4" HPWH; pressured up on the work string and took lead impressions of the position of the 10-3/4" casing hanger in the 18-3/4" HPWH. Pulled out of the well with the Lead Impression Tool; examined lead impressions and determined that the 10-3/4" casing hanger in the 18-3/4" HPWH was in the correct position and picked up and ran in the well with the 10-3/4" casing hanger lockdown sleeve and running tool and pulled out of the well with the 10-3/4" casing hanger lockdown sleeve and running tool to change out the 6-5/8" 27# drill pipe to 6-5/8" 34# drill pipe.

03/17/2012: Finished RIH with 10-3/4" casing hanger LDS tool. Set 10-3/4" lockdown sleeve and tested - good. Spaced out across BOPs and function tested BOPs and Diverter. Continued to POOH with the 10-3/4" casing hanger LDS RT from 11;671' to 4;664' and laid down LDS RT. Continued TOH on 5-7/8" DP from 4;664' to surface. Slip and cut drill line and performed 10-3/4" x 9-7/8" casing test. RIH with 9-7/8" EZSV from surface to 6500'.
","WAR_START_DT":"2012-03-11","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":238,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"03/18/2012: Finished RIH with the 9-7/8" EZSV bridge plug to a setting depth of 17;020'. 03/19/2012: Continued to run in the well with the back-up 9-7/8" EZSV bridge plug to a setting depth of 17;020'; set and tested the 9-7/8" EZSV bridge plug; set a 500' cement plug on top of the 9-7/8" EZSV bridge plug and POOH to 10;667'.

03/20/2012: Finished pulling out of the well with the 9-7/8" EZSV running tool to 8;500'; circulated and conditioned the 14.0 ppg SBM in the well; set a 500' cement plug from 8;500' to 8;000'; pulled out of the well from 8;500' to 7;139'; pressure tested the Lower Variable Bore Test Ram in the Blowout Preventer - 250 psi low/ 8000 psi high for 5 minutes on each test. Performed a good "negative" pressure test equivalent to a seawater gradient and started displacement of the well from 7;139' to surface from 14.0 ppg SBM to seawater.

03/21/2012: Finished the displacement of the well from SBM to seawater; spotted corrosion inhibitor/biocide below the wellhead; pulled out of the well with the 9-7/8" EZSV bridge plug running tool; cleaned and cleared the drill floor and started to rig up to pull the diverter; unlatch the BOP from the wellhead and pull riser and BOP to the surface.

03/22/2012: Finished rigging up of the riser handling equipment; pulled the diverter; rigged up the marine riser landing joint; unlatched the BOP from the wellhead; rigged down the drape hoses; pulled one(1) joint of marine riser and shut down marine riser pulling operations to troubleshoot problems with the Forward cranes.

03/23/2012: Continued to troubleshoot problems with the Starboard Forward crane; problems were resolved; continued to pull and lay down marine riser joints from 6;794' to 1;694'.

03/24/2012: Finished pulling marine riser and setting the BOP on the subsea BOP cart on the spider beams in the moonpool. Moved the BOP from the moonpool to in front of the Subsea module; rigged down the marine riser handling equipment on the drill floor; cleaned and cleared the drill floor and started between well maintenance and inspection projects.
","WAR_START_DT":"2012-03-18","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":239,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"02/10/2013: Continue performing between well planned maintenance and inspections. Locked Subsea Production Tree (SSPT) connector to Jack PS005 Wellhead and pressure tested gasket to 13;000 psi for 15 minutes via ROV; test was successful. Continued working on BOPs and pre-deployment checklist. 

NOTE: Mr. Matt Spear (CVX) notified Mr. Bobby Nelson and Mr. Josh Ladner of BSEE of the intent to latch BOP onto PS005 and test BOP on 02/10/2013.

02/11/2013: Continued performing between well planned maintenance and inspections. Finished soaking yellow and blue pods on BOP; completed deployment checklist on BOP; installing IWOCS jewelry on LMRP. Picked up BOP off beams and lowered into position in moonpool. 

02/12/2013: Finished installing IWOCS jewelry onto BOPE. Splashed BOPs. Pressure tested riser lines. Ran BOPs on marine riser from 194' to 5;294' (70 total joints run).

02/13/2013: Finished pressure testing riser lines. Continued to run BOPs on marine riser from 5;294' to 6;419' (~500' above sea floor); prepared motor vessel Alyssa Chouest for ROV operations. Ran BOPs to 6;794'. Installed riser test cap and prepared to test riser lines.

NOTE: Mr. Kevin Corbin (CVX) received verbal approval from Mr. Bobby Nelson on 02/13/2013 at 10:46 hrs to land; latch and conduct initial subsea BOP testing on the PS005 well utilizing ROV on support vessel.

02/14/2013: Finished pressure testing riser lines @ 6;794. Landed and latched BOP onto SSPT. Performed pull and slump test; unlocked slip joint and laid out landing joint. Installed diverter and performed Emergency Response Analysis offset test. Pressure tested Upper Blind Shear Rams (UBSR) and connector. Conducted Deadman and Lower Blind Shear Rams (LBSR) test. Performed ROV intervention test on UBSRs and pressure tested. Flow tested diverter. Tripped in hole with BOP test assembly to 4;624'. Ran IWOCS UTA offline and tested choke manifold. 

02/15/2013: Tripped in hole with 9" Cleanout BHA and BOP Weight Set Test Tool (WSTT) Assembly to 7;727'. Circulated bottoms up and slacked off to land out BOP test tool in SSPT to 7;031'. Performed accumulator draw down test; tested connector against test tool and annular. Finished testing BOPs with IPT as per BOP Test Plan. Function tested BOPs; functioned diverter. Short tripped out of hole with WSTT Assembly to 786'.

NOTE: Received approval from Mr. Bobby Nelson for the Jack PS005 Completion APM on 02/15/2013 at 2:13 PM to commence with completion operations and is valid only for steps 1 through step 20 of the completion procedure. To continue past this point; a RPM is required with commingling approval documentation.

02/16/2013: Continued to trip out of hole with WSTT from 786' to 529' and racked back WSTT. Tripped back in the hole with 9" HES Cleanout BHA from 529' to 5;129'. Attempted to function UBSR without success. Troubleshot UBSRs. Received CVX/BSEE approval to proceed with operations as per APM. Displaced riser from seawater to 14.0 ppg SBM. Performed choke drill. Washed and reamed surface cement plug from 7;921' to 8;048'.

02/27/2013: Pulled LMRP on marine riser from 4;694' to surface. Troubleshot and conducted repairs on the LMRP.

03/01/2013: Ran LMRP on marine riser from 944' to 6;644' (joints #13 - #88).

Note: On 03/18/13; Kevin Corbin notified Mr. Bobby Nelson and Josh Ladner (BSEE Houma District) that we completed BOP software upgrades and testing and planned to splash the LMRP on March 19th; with planned latch-up on March 21st.

03/19/2013: Completed final preparations and splashed the LMRP at 04:45 hrs. Ran LMRP on marine riser from surface to 2;969'. Observed the Yellow pod annular preventer subsea regulator was not functioning properly. Decision made to pull riser from 2;969' to surface. Pulled from 2;969' to 869'.

Adjusted riser tensioners and set-down weight as per Transocean riser analysis. Pressure tested down choke and kill lines against FSV's to 11;300 psi. Laid out marine riser landing joint.
