04/19/2013: Ran BOP stack and LMRP on marine riser from 3;644' to 6;794'. Pressure tested choke; kill; boost and rigid conduit lines. Waited on weather due to wind conditions (38 knots sustained; gusting to 44 knots). Pick up termination joint; slip joint and install drape hoses.

04/20/2013: Picked up and ran the termination and slip joints. Installed drape hoses in moon pool. Pressure tested the choke; kill and boost lines. Made up and ran the 16' HW riser pup and landing joints. Installed storm loops and made up tensioner SDC ring to the fluid bearing. Installed IWOCS UTA stand-off arm in moon pool. Moved over PS005 and latched up the BOP stack to the SSPT at 09:30 hrs. Unlocked and scoped out the slip joint and laid out the landing joint. Installed diverter. Performed ERA offset test. Rigged down riser handling equipment. Picked up BOP test assy and RIH to 554'. Performed diverter flow test. Continued to run in hole with BOP test assy from 554' to 5;039'.
","WAR_START_DT":"2013-04-14","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":249,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"04/21/2013: Trip in hole from 5;039' to 5;297' with BOP test assembly on 5-7/8" drill pipe. Performed BOP Deadman and ROV Intervention Tests. Trip in hole from 5;297' to 7;227'. Located tool joint on annular and spaced out for testing BOPs. Tested BOPs as per the SureTec IPT test program. Landed out Boll Weevil tool and tested blind shear rams. Pull out of hole from 7;656' to 7;000'. 

04/22/2013: Trip out of hole from 7;000' to 554' and laid out the BOP test assembly. Trip in hole from 554' to 7;994' with Halliburton 10-3/4" RTTS overshot assembly. Displaced riser from seawater to 14.1 ppg CaBr2. Retrieved RTTS and monitored wellbore - static. Pulled out of hole with RTTS to 6;935'; and circulate riser out.

04/23/2013: Finished circulating riser volume. Pulled out of hole with 10-3/4" RTTS. Circulated bottoms up due to debris found on RTTS and swabbing of assembly #8 downhole.

04/24/2013: POOH with CleanWell BHA to assembly #8 and inspect/clean at 15;132'. Run in hole with riser brushes and jetting tool to 28;643'. Picked up to 28;641'. Reversed out well. Jetted BOP stack. Functioned VBRs on stack and jet the same. Circulated CaBr2 to specification.

04/25/2013: Finished circulating and filtering CaBr2 to 29 NTUs and trace of solids. Trip out of hole from 28;520' to 8;704' with Halliburton CleanWell assemblies on 5-7/8" CTM57 DP.

04/26/2013: Finished trip out of hole with Halliburton CleanWell assemblies on 5-7/8" DP. Boosted riser clean. Performed planned rig maintenance; changing out the upper; middle and lower IBOPs on the primary MDDM and pressure tested same.

04/27/2013: Run in hole and set Halliburton Sump Packer. Pull out of hole and rig down wireline equipment. Pressure/Function test BSRs. Rig up TCP Equipment. Make up TCP Guns; 3-1/2" DP and DST Tools.
","WAR_START_DT":"2013-04-21","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":250,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"04/28/2013: Tripped in hole with TCP guns on 5-7/8" DP. Located sump packer 28;480' dpm (drill pipe measure depth). Made up perforation head stand. Held PJSM on rig up surface iron. Rigged up surface iron.

04/29/2013: Tested surface lines. Set TCP packer on depth. Fired TCP guns across 28;455' to 27;105' DPM. Monitored well for losses. Reversed out 1.5 DP volumes. Pulled out of hole above perforation zones and monitored well. Pulled out of hole from 28;476' dpm to 13;409' with TCP assembly.

04/30/2013: TOH with TCP assembly from 13;409' to surface. Lay down DST tools; 3-1/2" DP and 100% spent perforating gun assembly. Performed TOI recommended maintenance.

05/01/2013: Finished performing 30 and 90 day Preventive Maintenances on primary drawworks; MDDM; PRS; and rotary table. Functioned upper and lower blind shear rams from Toolpusher's panel Blue and Yellow pods. Rigged up handling tools for 4" Hydril 511 Washpipe. P/U and M/U deburr assembly and RIH to 22;226'. Fluid loss rate ~8 bph.

05/02/2013: Continued RIH with HES deburr assembly to top of perforation at 27;118'. Held PJSM; washed and reamed through perforations. Engaged wash pipe in sump packer; activated VacTech and circulated bottoms up. POOH one stand above sump packer and monitored wellbore. RIH and engaged sump packer - no fill noted. POOH from 28;614' to 26;961'. Began testing BOPs.

05/03/2013: Pressure tested BOPs on 5-7/8" 34# drill pipe. Function BOPs and Diverter on 6-5/8" drill pipe. Pressure tested BOPs on 6-5/8" StimTech. 

05/04/2013: Continued with BOPE testing. Tested Middle/Lower MDDM IBOP valves and choke manifold valves to 250/9;800 psi for 5/5 min. Monitored well with approximately 7 BPH losses noted. R/D chicksans and double dutch test assembly. POOH with deburr assembly from 26;973' to surface.
","WAR_START_DT":"2013-04-28","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":251,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"05/05/2013: Slipped and cut 149' of drill line. Re-calibrated and functioned drawworks crown and floor saver and performed brake test (good test). Rig up ESTMZ Handling Tools. Pick up; made up and run in hole with ESTMZ assembly.

05/06/2013: Picked up and trip in hole with Zone 1 - 6 gravel pack assembly from 2;217' to 2;410'. Installed RA tags in pin end of isolation packers. Rigged up test cap and pressure tested lower zone assemblies (1-6) and sleeve integrity to 250 psi for 5 minutes on chart. Good test on all tests. Run in hole to retrieve service tool assembly. Picked up and made up VCH packer.

05/07/2013: Tripped in hole with ESTMZ gravel pack assembly on 5-7/8" workstring from 1;600' to 6;620'. Functioned BSRs; continued trip in hole from 6;620' to 20;181'; made up and trip in hole with 6-5/8" in Stim-Tech joints from 20;181' to 21;617'. Continue trip in hole on 5-7/8" workstring from 21;617' to 24;823'.

05/08/2013: Tripped in hole with ESTMZ assembly from 24;823' to 28;554' (Mule shoe depth). Made up side entry stand. Held PJSM; rigged up chiksans; slacked off and tagged sump packer with no-go at 28;480'. Double checked measurements. Set and tested VCH packer. Set isolation packers. Rigged down chiksans and side entry stand. Swapped out links to 16' links. Picked up Frac Head and rigged up frac surface lines and equipment. Pressure and function tested lines and equipment. Held PJSM; pickled workstring. Began flushing lines from frac boat to rig floor.

05/09/2013: Finished testing surface lines. Performed zone one acid job and mini-Frac test. Transferred frac fluid from C-Hero to Blue Dolphin. Performed step down test and zone one main Frac Pac treatment. Reversed out proppant. Rigged down Frac Head and chicksans. Attempted to close mechanical and Frac sleeves.

05/10/2013: Rigged down Frac Head and 4" chiksans. Attempted to shift close FCS and MCS; no success; losses @ 30 bph. Trouble shot ESTMZ gravel pack shifting assembly; losses @ 40 to 90 bph. Pumped and spotted 20 bbls - 30 ppb Calcium Carbonate OptiBridge pill. Monitored well - losses @ 30 to 70 bph. Pumped and spotted 30 bbls - 32 ppb Calcium Carbonate OptiBridge pill. Monitored well losses at 30 bph.

05/11/2013: Monitored well 15' above seal dump position; ~30 bbl/hr loss rate. TOH to just below zone 2 FCS; 60/90 bbl/hr loss rate. TIH to 15' above seal dump position. Monitored well while mixing 50 bbls; 40 ppb Opti-Bridge LCM pill. Loss rate @ 78 bph. R/U cement hose and chiksans. Pumped 50 bbl - 40 ppb Opti-Bridge LCM pill and displaced to service tool XO; closed annular and squeezed pill into formation at 200 psi max pressure. Opened well and monitored loss rate 6 bph. TOH with ESTMZ gravel pack shifter assy to 28;297'. Monitored well 6 bph losses; cont TOH to 26;732'. Installed PS-30s - loss rate 18 bph. Pumped 40 bbl slug. Cont TOH to 24;565'; loss rate increased to 40 bph. Discussed options with CVX management. Decision to reduce bottom hole pressure 0.2 ppg (290 psi) utilizing riser cap. Performed test down kill line with 35 bbls 11.0 ppg CaBr2 fluid to 290 psi. Monitored well on mini strip tank - losing 9 bph. TOH with ESTMZ shifter assy utilizing 0.2 ppg riser cap to reduce losses. Midnight depth 22;764'.
","WAR_START_DT":"2013-05-05","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":252,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"05/12/2013: Trip out of hole to surface with ESTMZ shifter tool assembly; inspected and layed out tool assembly (noted washouts in the crossover weldment; ShurMac; multi acting ball check and perforation pup). Began slip and cut drill line.

05/13/2013: Finished slip and cut drill line; rigged down washpipe handling equipment; trip in hole to 7;500' and pressure tested BOPs on 5-7/8" 34# DP from Toolpusher's panel on Blue Pod. Tested upper/middle rams and associated valves to 250/8;000 psi; annular 250/3;500 psi; utilizing IPT SureTec system (9 of 14 tests completed at midnight). Monitored losses on trip tank utilizing drill water riser cap (-290 psi = 0.2 ppg).

05/14/2013: Complete testing BOPs on 6 5/8" Stim-Tech. Function test BOPs and diverter from Toolpusher's panel. Boost drill water riser cap out of riser with BOP closed. Replace riser cap with clean 8.34 ppg drill water (325 bbls) while monitoring losses. Average losses: 16 - 18 BPH.

05/15/2013: Monitored well with 8.3 ppg drill water riser cap to reduce losses. Trip out of hole from 7;582' to surface with BOP test joints and mule shoe assembly on 5-7/8" CTM57 drill pipe. Trip in the hole from surface to 1;309' with Halliburton mule shoe; Gravel Pack seal assembly; 4" wash pipe (10 stands plus single) and VCH locator assemblies. Trip in the hole with Gravel Pack test assembly from 1;309' to 8;566'.

05/16/2013: Tripped in hole with ESTMZ seal test assembly from 8;566' to 8;819'. Reversed out drill water riser cap from drill pipe. Continue to trip in hole from 8;819' to 28;298'; land out packer locator. Integrity tested zones 2-6 with pressuring up the backside and tested zone 1 with the drill pipe (good tests). Spot and bullheaded 50 bbls of 100 ppg 15.0 ppg pill into formation at 1.2 BPM; 780 psi and allow pressure bleed to 60 psi. Pull out of hole from 28;217' to 26;806' and monitor well. Losses recorded at 4.5 bbls per hour. Conducted flow check. Boosted light cap from riser to 14.1 ppg.

05/17/2013: Boosted 8.3 ppg drill water from upper riser. Monitored well with CaBr2 loss rate at 4.0 bph. Pumped 40-bbl 14.6-ppg CaBr2 slug. Tripped out of hole from 26;866' to surface with ESTMZ seal test assembly. Monitored well with CaBr2 loss rate at 12-14 bph. Slip and cut drill line. 

05/18/2013: Troubleshot problems with ship's emergency generator. Monitored well on trip tank with CaBr2 losses to the well at ~14 bph. 
","WAR_START_DT":"2013-05-12","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":253,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"05/19/2013: Troubleshot problems with ship's emergency generator. Monitored well on trip tank with CaBr2 losses to the well at ~14 bph.

05/20/2013: Performed PM's and general housekeeping on the rig floor and in the mud module while waiting on parts for emergency generator repairs. Monitored well on trip tank with CaBr2 losses to the well at ~12 bph.

05/21/2013: Received parts for emergency generator. Rig Engineers began work to rebuild water pumps and heat exchanger for emergency generator. Monitored well on trip tank with CaBr2 losses to the well at ~12 bph.

05/22/2013: Continued maintenance to emergency generator and cooling unit. Monitored well on trip tank with CaBr2 losses to well at ~14 bph. 

05/23/2013: Continued maintenance to emergency generator and cooling unit. Monitored well on trip tank with CaBr2 losses to well at ~14 bph. 

05/24/2013: Tested surface equipment with 14.1 ppg CaBr. RIH with BOP test assembly to 7;582' and tested BOPs on 5-7/8" DP and 6-5/8" Stim Tech joints to 250/8;000 psi. While attempting to test on 6-5/8" Stim Tech joints; determined test ram elastomers were below operating temperature and broke circulation to increase temperature at HPWH. Monitored well on trip tank with CaBr2 losses to well at ~16 bph.

05/25/2013: Finished testing BOPs to 250/8;000 psi on 6-5/8" Stim Tech joints. TOH with BOP test assembly. P/U and RIH with ESTMZ service tool to 20;148'. Monitored well on trip tank with CaBr2 losses to well at ~17 bph.
","WAR_START_DT":"2013-05-19","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":254,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"05/26/2013: RIH with ESTMZ from zone #6 to zone #2; shifting and testing MCS with 1;500 psi down the DP per Halliburton. Picked up from 28;256' to 28;230' to place the Halliburton GP service tool in dump seals position (DP and annulus in communication with zone #1). Monitored well on trip tank with CaBr2 losses to zone #1 at ~24 bph while waiting on Frac Head from shorebase.

05/27/2013: Received Frac Head and tested - good. Performed Injection Test with SLB Dowell. Made up Frac Head & Iron; opened MCS; for Zone #2. Flush and Test Frac Lines. Performed acid treatment; Mini-Frac Test and Main Frac Pack. While pumping; observed losses stop and increase in active system on backside. Stopped Frac job at stage 9. Determined possible communication to between service tool and backside. Worked pipe up and down to get to reverse out position. Bled off pressure below annular and service tool freed up. Pulled up to Reverse out position. Pressure up to 1000 psi and used rig pumps to Reverse out - Unsuccessful. Continue to troubleshoot.

05/28/2013: Held PJSM with drill crew on well control and troubleshoot Frac Zone #2. Troubleshoot Frac Zone #2; monitor wellbore on TT to establish loss rate. PU with service tool dump seals. Loss rate at 30 bph. Close MCS for Zone #2 - loss rate 24 bph. Mobilize Boots & Coots coiled tubing equipment/ Crews to DCL. Continue to monitor wellbore losses and reciprocating drillpipe every 30 minutes. Losses slowed to ~5 bph; and pipe began taking weight (25k) while slacking off. Attempted to break down bridge by bull heading; no success. TOH to locate mule shoe above the top of the VCH pkr. R/D Frac Head and transfer to AFT rotary. POOH 10 stands from 28;236' to 26;983' with 50-100k overpull for first 3 stands; then pipe began to pull free. Closed annular and circulated riser while monitoring well on mini trip tank. TOH to 26;886'. Worked pipe while rigging up surface iron to reverse out. Filled and tested lines to 11k. Pressured up down work string to 10k and established circulation; circulated ~3 mins; shut down and lined up to reverse out work string.

05/29/2013: Reversed out proppant from work string until clean 14.1 ppg CaBr2 fluid was at gumbo box (675 bbls total). Rigged down surface iron. CBU at 15 bpm with clean 14.1 ppg CaBr2 fluid while filtering fluid. TOH with service tool assy from 26;886' to 1;539'; midnight depth.

05/30/2013: Rigged up WFT and 4" wash pipe equip. TOH with service tool assemblies and 4" wash pipe from 1;539' to surface. R/B 4" wash pipe and L/D HES assemblies. Cleaned and cleared rig floor of tools and equip. Changed out primary MDDM dies and saver sub. Slip and cut drill line; performed planned rig maintenance. M/U HES 4" cleanout BHA assembly to 1;059'. TIH with cleanout assembly to 7;811'; midnight depth.

05/31/2013: Held pre-job safety meeting on tripping operations. Cont TIH with 4" HES cleanout assembly from 7;811' to 12;245'. Function tested BOP on 5-7/8" DP from Driller's panel on Yellow pod. Functioned diverter (43 secs) and all related valves from Driller's panel. Cont TIH with 4" HES cleanout assembly from 12;245' to 26;500' (~500' above VCH Pkr); wash down to VCH packer.

06/01/2013: Continued washing down and reversing out every stand from 27;370' to 28;040'. Pulled up to 27;500'; pumped and spotted hi-vis pill; washed down to 28;040'. Reversed out work string until fluid was clean. Pumped slug and TOH from 28;040' to 20;985'.
","WAR_START_DT":"2013-05-26","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":255,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"06/02/2013: Continued washing down and reversing out every stand from 27;370' to 28;040'. Pulled up to 27;500'; pumped and spotted high viscosity pill; washed down to 28;040'. Reversed out work string until fluid was clean. Pumped slug and trip out the hole from 28;040' to 20;985'.

06/03/2013: Continued tripping out of the hole with Halliburton 4" cleanout assembly from 20;985' to 19;645'. Pulled manual rotary bushings and installed PS-30s. Continue tripping out the hole with Halliburton 4" cleanout assembly from 19;645' to surface. Slip and cut drill line; serviced primary traveling equip; make up Halliburton 4" wash pipe and service tool assembly to 1;222'. Trip into the hole with Halliburton assembly from 1;222' to 7;594'.

06/04/2013: Finished acid treatment on Zone #3. Pumped mini-frac and main frac pack on Zone #3. Reversed out excess proppant. Closed mechanical circulation sleeve and tested. Laid down and serviced frac head. Pulled up to Zone #4. Rigged up frac head. Blue Dolphin frac boat finished preparing fluids for zone #4. Opened mechanical circulation sleeve and rigged up 4" chiksans. Flushed and tested frac lines and popoffs. Performed acid treatment on Zone #4. Pumped main frac on zone #4. Reversing out excess proppant at midnight.

06/05/2013: Finished reversing out excess proppants; picked up and closed mechanical circulation sleeve; tested mechanical circulation sleeve down drill pipe to 1;500 psi; good test. Rig down chiksans and Supreme frac head. Trip out of the hole from 27;727' (mule shoe depth) to 27;486' (mule shoe depth). Positioned tool to weight down circulation position and tested to 1;500 psi down drill string. Finished servicing frac head; pick up and make up frac head. Stand by while Blue Dolphin frac boat transferred fluid and sand preparing for zone #5 frac job. Opened mechanical circulation sleeve; rig up chiksans; flushed and tested lines/popoffs. Performed acid job on zone #5. Performed frac ops on zone #5. Reversed out excess proppants. Picked up and closed mechanical circulation sleeve; tested mechanical circulation sleeve down drill pipe to 1;500 psi; good test. Rig down chiksans and Supreme frac head; trip out the hole from 27;468' (mule shoe depth) to 27;245' (mule shoe depth); servicing Supreme frac head at midnight.

06/06/2013: Pick up Supreme frac head. Monitor well with service tool in dump seal position while Blue Dolphin frac boat received fluid from M/V Virgie and prepared fluids and sand for zone #6 frac job. Opened mechanical circulation sleeve in zone #6; rig up chiksans; flushed and tested lines/popoffs. Performed acid job on zone #6. Perform mini frac job. Perform main frac ops. Reversed out excess proppants; closed mechanical circulation sleeve and tested. Trip out of hole 1 std and began testing BOP on 6-5/8" Stim-Tech; 3 out of 14 tests completed at midnight; losing 3 bph.

06/07/2013: Finished testing BOPs on 6-5/8" Stim-Tech and 5-7/8" DP. Function tested BOP and diverter. TOH with HES frac service tool assembly from 26;875' to 7;847'.

06/08/2013: Continued tripping out of the hole with Halliburton 4" wash pipe and service tool assembly from 7;847' to 1;222'. Pulled PS-30s and installed manual bushings. Rigged up Weatherford equipment. Tripped out of the hole with Halliburton 4" wash pipe and service tool assembly from 1;222' to surface; racking back 4" and laying out assembly. Performed planned rig maintenance. Pick up Halliburton 4" cleanout assembly to 1;608'. Continue tripping into the hole with Halliburton 4" cleanout on 5-7/8" drill pipe to 17;505'.
","WAR_START_DT":"2013-06-02","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":256,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"06/09/2013: Trip into the hole with Halliburton 4" cleanout assembly from 17;505' to 28;596' on 5-7/8" drill pipe. P/U and M/U 6-5/8" Stim-Tech from 21;265' to 27;400'. Monitored well on trip tank; 3-1/2 bph losses. Wash down and reverse out with 14.1 ppg CaBr2 from 27;400' to 28;596' as needed to clean debris/sand. 

06/10/2013: Finished reversing out with 14.1 ppg CaBr2. Pulled up below zone #1 mechanical circulation sleeve (28;212') and monitored well on trip tank; 9.1 bph losses. Trip into the hole from 28;212' to 28;596' to check fill; no fill noted. Pull out the hole above VCH packer (26;762') and monitored well on trip tank; 10 bph losses. Trip out of the hole with 4" cleanout assembly to surface and rack back.

06/11/2013: Slipped and cut drill line and performed preventive maintenance on forward MDDM; monitored well on trip tank; 10 bph losses. Picked up and trip into the hole with Halliburton Production Isolation Assembly; FS-1 valve and Polish Bore Receptacle (PBR) from surface to 20;111' on 5-7/8" drill pipe. 

06/12/2013: Trip into the hole from 20;111' to 28;535'; opened Production Sleeves across zones #6 through #1 and monitored losses; total 14.1 CaBr2 losses after checking the 6 zones; 600 bbls. Set and tested Production Isolation Assembly; top of the Isolation PBR at 26;885'. Monitored well on trip tank; well static. Trip out the hole with Running Tool from 28;513' to 8;656'. 

06/13/2013: Trip out the hole with the Isolation Assembly Running Tool and lay down. Performed pressure test to UBSR/LBSR against FS-1 valve at 250/ 1;000 psi for 5 min and function test. Performed services and maintenance on forward MDDM. Picked up and ran TNT Packer Assembly and Production PBR from surface to 17;769'. Monitored well on trip tank; well static.

06/14/2013: Finished run in the hole with TNT Packer Assembly and Production PBR to 26;885'. Sting into Isolation PBR and land out at 26;898'; set (5;000 psi) and tested (4;000 psi) TNT Packer; top of the Production PBR at 26;577'. Pulled out of the hole with Hydraulic Setting Tool to surface and lay down. Slip and cut drill line. Monitored well on active system with proper volumes noted.

06/15/2013: Slipped and cut drill line and performed preventive maintenance on forward MDDM (replace a roller). Picked up and ran into the hole Halliburton CleanWell and BPRRT 9-5/8" Test Mandrel assembly to 7;389'; jetted SSPT and HPWH per Halliburton instruction. Set BPRRT in the Cameron SSPT and tested 9-5/8" Fixed Ram against BPRRT to 250/ 8;000 psi for 5 min. Retrieved Bore Protector; and jetted HPWH; SSPT and BOP stack. Pulled out of the hole with Bore Protector; and laid down CleanWell and Cameron BPRRT. Rigged up Weatherford Tubular Handling Equipment. 
","WAR_START_DT":"2013-06-09","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":257,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"06/16/2013: Picked up Seal Assembly and R-Nipple. Made up Down Hole Pressure; Temperature Gauges; and Chemical Injection Mandrel Assemblies on Seal Assembly. Tested and ran Jewelry on 4-1/2" tubing in the hole from 268' to 1;364'. Monitored well on trip tank; proper displacement noted.

06/17/2013: Continued running in hole with 4-1/2" production tubing from 1;364' to 17;263'; function tested LBSR/UBSR at 6;531'; before Production Tubing Assembly pass across BOP Stack. Performed power checks on DHPTG as per program. Monitored well on trip tank; proper displacement noted.

06/18/2013: Picked and made up SCSSV; DCIM and a 4-1/2" timed (290°) pup joint. Terminated and tested SCSSV and DCIM. Continued running in hole with 4-1/2" production tubing from 17;263' to 18;036'. Changed out handling equipment and ran in hole with 6" VIT production tubing from 18;036' to 18;464'. Picked SSTT to center mouse hole. Continued running in hole with 6" VIT production tubing from 18;464' to 19;380'. Monitored well on trip tank; proper displacement noted.

06/19/2013: Continued running in hole with 6" VIT production tubing from 19;380' to 19;609'. Changed out handling equipment and made up 5-1/2" pup joint. Made up tubing hanger and a 6" timed (270°) pup joint; terminated and tested control injection and gauges lines. Released Tubing Hanger Running Tool. Transfer SSTT to Forward MDDM. Monitored well on trip tank; proper displacement noted.

06/20/2013: Latched and locked SSTT to tubing hanger. Ran in the hole from 19;609' to 19;750'. Changed out handling equipment and bails. Picked up junk basket and continue running in the hole production tubing with 7-5/8" landing string from 19;750' to 26;534'. Monitored well on trip tank; proper displacement noted.

06/21/2013: Stung into Production PBR. Pulled up above Production PBR and displaced with packer fluid. Picked up the SFT on the Aft rotary and performed transfer to center mouse hole. Rigged up CCTLF and performed function test. Tested SFT control lines; performed transfer to Forward MDDM and made up to CCTLF and landing string. Monitored well on trip tank using the Expro SSTT bore pressure gauge; well static. 

06/22/2013: Made up SFT and torpedo packers. Landed out tubing hanger and attempted to lock it; unsuccessful. Rigged down CCTLF and rigged up Weatherford handling equipment. Pulled out of the hole the Landing String; SSTT; and Tubing Hanger Running Tools from 26;626' to 26;439'. Monitored well on trip tank using the Expro SSTT bore pressure gauge; well static. 
","WAR_START_DT":"2013-06-16","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":258,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"06/23/2013: Pulled out of hole with SSTT and tubing hanger on 7-5/8" landing string from 26;439' to 19;630' and inspected/troubleshot SSTT/ THRT. Diagnose tool and observed THRT setting sleeve stroking down but not up. Rigged up to change out tubing hanger.

06/24/2013: Changed out tubing hanger. Tested control lines on tubing hanger. Circulate wellbore while waiting for backup SSTT/ tubing hanger running tool to arrive. Began deck testing SSTT/ tubing hanger running tool. 

06/25/2013: Deck tested SSTT/ tubing hanger running tool. Transfer SSTT to AFT rotary. Made up SSTT to riser control module. Test SSTT with riser control module. 

06/26/2013: Latched and locked subsea test tree to tubing hanger. Tripped into the hole with subsea test tree. Rig down elevators and bails. Rigged up 22' bails; thread compensator; and Weatherford elevators dressed for 7-5/8" landing string. Picked up junk basket and tripped into the hole with 7-5/8" landing string at 23;734'.

06/27/2013: Continued to trip into the hole with 4-1/2" x 6" production tubing on 7-5/8" Landing String from 23;734' to 26;579'. Rigged down Weatherford elevators and TDSC compensator. Made up Land Out stand with MDDM crossover to landing string. Displaced Tubing-by-Casing annulus with 1100 bbls of 14.1 ppg CaBr2 Inhibited Packer Fluid at 10 bpm. Displaced 1100 bbls of CaBr2 Inhibited Packer Fluid with 527 bbls of CaBr2. Landed the landing string on the Weatherford 500 spider. Rigged up CCTLF and Surface Flow Tree.

06/28/2013: Moved Surface Flow Tree from center mousehole to forward rotary and made up to landing string. Made up torpedo packers; landed tubing hanger. Locked and tested tubing hanger between 9-5/8" pipe rams and TH upper seals to 7;800 psi surface; per Cameron procedure. Tested tubing by casing annulus to 5;100 psi surface.

06/29/2013: Rig up slickline equipment and test lubricator. Test SSTT Retainer valve; Landing String; and Surface Flow Tree against closed FS1 valve to 5;350 psi for 5 min. Retrieved Isolation Sleeve from SSPT on slickline; laid down slickline retrieval tool string. Rigged down lubricator and installed night cap. Test surface lines and prepare to displace landing string with base oil.
","WAR_START_DT":"2013-06-23","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":259,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"06/30/2013: Displace 7-5/8" landing string with 6.6 ppg base oil. Cycle and open FS-1 valve; bullhead base oil. Perform negative test on SCSSV and rig up slickline. Run and set lower crown plug on slickline; pull out of the hole with slickline. Test plug to 10;500 psi. Run upper crown plug on slickline.

07/01/2013: First attempt to set upper crown plug was unsuccessful. Retrieve upper crown plug with slickline pulling tool. Re-dress and re-run upper crown plug. Second attempt to set crown plug was successful. POOH with slickline. Test upper crown plug through Expro SFT.

07/02/2013: Pressure test between UCP and LCP to 12;900 psi for 15 min. Displaced kill line with base oil. Displaced riser; boost and CL to seawater. Lowered well annulus pressure to seawater hydrostatic. Flushed SSPT and bullheaded 50 bbls of base oil down KL; thru SSPT down tubing. Performed negative test on SCSSV to seawater gradient. Displaced kill line to seawater. Unlatched THRT and displaced LS to seawater.

07/03/2013: Laid out CCTLF with primary MDDM. P/U and set CCTLF dolly on forward deck. R/U Weatherford power tongs stand compensator system and service loops. Finish R/U WFT equipment on secondary to breakout and L/O Expro SFT. Transfer flowhead to secondary rotary; B/O single and pup and L/O on Aft rotary. TOH with SSTT on 7-5/8" landing string.

07/04/2013: Finish POOH with LS and SSTT from 3;697' to surface. Transfer SSTT/ THRT to center mouse hole. Vented and flushed tree and transferred from center mouse hole to Aft deck. R/D WFT handling equipment from primary MDDM. R/D Expro control lines and umbilical sheaves reel and beams.

07/05/2013: R/D Expro umbilical equipment. R/D WFT handling equipment and R/U riser running bails and running tool and associated equipment. Pull and L/O diverter. Unlatch BOPs at 14:30 hrs. L/O LJ and Heavy wall pup jt. Service and change pkr element in slip-joint. Offline: TIH with DP to set Cameron Tertiary cap and retrieve HFL/EFL skid from the seafloor. POOH with skid from 7;240' to surface and secured skid to BOP cart in moonpool.
","WAR_START_DT":"2013-06-30","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":260,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"01/16/2015:
. Received approval from BSEE to perform the PS005 SCSSV Xylene Soak Procedure.
. Rigged up Baker equipment and pressure tested tie in.
. Began displacing xylene down the LDHI injection line to displace LDHI through PS005
  to the Jack South Flowline PFL-01.

01/17/2015:
. Completed injection of 3 tanks (1;650 gallons) of xylene through LDHI Injection
  tubing.
. Began spotting xylene above the SCSSV. 
. Completed injection of the 4th tank of xylene into the chemical injection mandrel
  above the PS005 SCSSV.
","WAR_START_DT":"2015-01-16","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":261,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"01/18/2015: 
. Completed pumping the xylene at 7:03 p.m. (2750 gallons) and initiated 36 hour soak
  period.
. Cycling the SCSSV at 6 hour intervals.
. Displacing the xylene in the LDHI injection tubing to the injection mandrel above
  the SCSSV.

01/19/2015: 
. Continue 36 hour soak period with 6 hourly cycles.
. Displacing the xylene in the LDHI injection tubing to the injection mandrel above
  the SCSSV.

01/20/2015:
. Completed 36 hour soak period and injection tubing displacement.
. Two soft tests (no flow) were unsuccessful.
. Ramped well to 8;000 blpd and performed a hard close on the SCSSV.
. Calculated leak rate 1;657 cc/min (wellhead pressure built back-up to shut-in
  pressure before end of the test).
. Shut-in and secured well at 09:06 p.m.

","WAR_START_DT":"2015-01-18","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":262,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"01/30/2015: Terry Hollier; Micah Charpentier; and Bruce Crabtree with the BSSE Houma Distict arrived at 10:00 hrs. Reviewed WR 758 PS005 Well Bullheading procedure; P&IDs and performed a walk through of the temporary pump equipment. Terry Hollier gave a verbal approval to commence as planned. Inspectors departed facility at 13:00 hrs.

01/31/2015: Procedure review with operations team. Perform safety device testing on topsides. Started attempting to perform line test on temporary equipment. Halliburton pump unable to achieve low enough pump rates to avoid causing PSVs to relieve. Operations made decision to start 72 hour flow test at 23:30 hrs.
","WAR_START_DT":"2015-01-30","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":263,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"02/01/2015: R/U Greene's pressure testing pump to temporary surface equipment. Start testing lines; PSVs leaking; attempted to adjust set point without any success. Change PSVs and continue to test temporary surface iron to 12;000 psig on chart recorder. Test ok with new PSV setting at 12;350 psig. Perform annulus bleed on well; which requires a shut in for short period starting at 20:30 hrs. 

02/02/2015: Process trip briefly shuts well in at 12:30 hrs. Reset PSVs to 12;100 psig as per operations request. Tested PSVs on pump #1 and #2 to 12;000 psig. Attempted to flow test pump #2 to 11;000 psig and PSV relieved at 7;300 psig. Attempted to flow test pump #1; pump unable to ramp up to 11;000 psig. Inspected manual choke and found seat broken. Made decision to change vendor for PSVs and manual chokes. Had a total of 6 PSVs fail; both manual chokes and 1 of 2 check valves.

02/03/2015: Change PSVs on pump #1 and #2. Tested PSVs. Pump #1 relieved at 11;700 psig and pump #2 at 12;000 psig. Tested pump #1 to 11;200 psig and #2 to 11;250 psig. Change manual chokes on both pumps and flow tested each to 11;000 psig. Laura Hogge received verbal approval from BSEE (Amy Wilson) to flow well additional 24 hours. Jules Guste notified Chris Martens with Houma District BSSE of new set points on PSVs and that the actual pump pressure during bullheading operations would not exceed 11;200 psig.

02/04/2015: Held pre-job safety meeting. Shut well in at 13:00 hrs. Flush temporary surface lines with diesel. Set pump kickouts. Equalize pressure across cortec valve by pressuring up to 7580 psi with pumps. Start pumping diesel and ramp up in 1/2 bbl increments. Bullhead a total of 300 bbls fluid at a max rate of 3 bpm with 8;400 psig at discharge of pumps and 11;156 psig at subsea tree. Shut down pumps and isolate well. Flush surface lines with seawater. Test SCSSV - failed test. Open well at 17:00 hrs.  

02/05/2015: Shut well in at 15:30 hrs. Test SCSSV - test failed. 
","WAR_START_DT":"2015-02-01","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":264,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"02/22/2015: TIH with BOP on marine riser. Made up termination/flex joint and slip joint. Tested choke and kill to 250 low/ 11;300 psi high for 5 mins each - good test. Tested boost and rigid conduit to 5;000 psi for 5 mins - good test. Installed drape hoses and jewelry. Laid out landing joint and installed diverter.

02/23/2015: Continued to rig down riser handling equipment. Rigged up drill pipe handling equipment. TIH from surface to 7;020' with riser cleanout assembly and cleaned riser. Washed BOPs from 7;020' to 6;925'. TOH to surface with riser cleaning assembly. Inspected assembly at surface and observed some debris on brushes. Flushed riser and TIH from surface to 4;081' with riser cleaning assembly to perform second cleaning run.

02/24/2015: Continued to TIH with riser cleaning assembly from 4;081' to 6;925'. TOH to surface and inspected assembly. RIH with ring gasket removal assembly. Remove ring gasket from BOP. TOH with ring gasket removal assembly. Slip and cut drill line. Perform rig maintenance.

Note: On 02/24/2015 at 09:08 hrs; Mr. Chris Gerlitz (Chevron) notified Mr. Larry Johnson (BSEE) that the expected latch up to the Jack PS005 well would be delayed until Wednesday; February 25.

02/25/2015: Performed rig maintenance. Made up BOP Land Assist Tool (BLAT) and verified function. Wait on weather. Landed BLAT in telescopic joint and locked in place. Moved rig from 1;000' to PS005 well center. Attempted to latch BOPs - unable due to damaged gasket. Removed damaged gasket.

02/26/2015; Changed out gasket. Latched BOPs to PS005 XT. Performed slump test - good test. Released BLAT tool and L/D. Performed ROV intervention test - unsuccessful. Troubleshoot and retest ROV intervention test on LBSR to 1;000 psi - good test. LBSR pressure test to 250 psi/ 11;300 psi - good test. UBSR pressure test to 250 psi/ 11;300 psi - good test. TIH with Tubing Hanger BOP Test Tool (THBOPTT) to 137'. 

02/27/2015: TIH from 137' to 7;032' and land out THBOPTT. R/U to test BOPs. Performed BOP pressure test (Driller's panel; Yellow Pod) on 5-7/8" 34# DP to 250/11;300 psi against VBRs (fixed ram against 9-5/8" test mandrel); pressure tested annular to 250/6;300 - all tests good. Function tested BOPs (Driller's panel; Yellow Pod; and Toolpusher's panel; Blue Pod) - good tests. Performed accumulator draw down test - good test. Pressure tested and function tested choke line outer failsafe valves - good test. TOH with the THBOPTT from 7;032' to surface. Waiting on current and weather conditions to subside within operating procedures to perform DMAS test.

02/28/2015: Waited on current and weather conditions to subside within operating procedures to perform DMAS test.

","WAR_START_DT":"2015-02-22","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":265,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"03/01/2015: Waited on current and weather conditions to perform Deadman/Autoshear (DMAS) test. Performed DMAS. Displaced surface equipment with drill water. Stopped operations due to handrail going overboard in moon pool; Jack ESD functioned and FPU notified. ROVs performed bottom scan - no damage observed. Handrail not found. Continued with displacement of choke/kill/boost and riser from seawater to 14.1 ppg CaBr2. 

03/02/2015: Displaced riser to 14.1 ppg CaBr2. Flow checked - well static. Rigged up tooling on the ROV as per program and deployed and installed the hydraulic flying leads (HFL) and electric flying leads (EFL) to the XT and umbilical termination assembly (UTA). Equalized annulus to 14.1 ppg CaBr2 hydrostatic in riser through XT up kill line to mini strip tank (20 bbls of 14.1 ppg CaBr2 to equalize). Monitored annulus on mini trip tank; static.

03/03/2015; Spot 25 bbls of 14.3 ppg CaBr2 high viscosity pill above upper crown plug. Transferred subsea test tree (SSTT) to forward rotary and TIH to 124'. Rig up 7-5/8" landing string handling equipment and SSTT Umbilical. TIH with SSTT on 7-5/8" landing string from 124' to 5;769'.

03/04/2015: TIH with SSTT from 5;769' to 6;930'. Make up soft landing joint and soft land SSTT with 45k down at 7;034'. POOH and lay down soft landing joint. Rig down 7-5/8" landing string running equipment. Rig up compensated coil tubing lift frame (CCTLF) and function test. Transfer surface flow tree (SFT) to CCTLF and connect bails to elevators.

03/05/2015: Make up SFT to landing string; rig up lines and install torpedo packers. Soft land tubing hanger running tool (THRT) on tubing hanger (TH) and attempt to hard land with no success. Washed to TH profile pumping 4 BPM 3 times. Latch THRT with success while boosting high viscosity pill out of hole. Test SFT and lines to 10;000 psi. Test THRT seals and 9-5/8" rams to 8;000 psi. Negative test SSTT ball valves and retainer valves to 500 psi with 8;000 psi below. All tests successful. Waited on weather to subside to rig up slickline.

03/06/2015: Waited on weather until conditions improved. Connected chiksans to SFT and tested. Negative tested LMV; UMV; and KWV with a 7;500 psi differential. Tested 9-5/8" rams to 250 psi low/ 8;000 psi high. All tests successful. Rigged up slickline Triple Wireline Valve; 6-3/8" and 2-1/2" lubricator assembly to SFT; terminate slickline to rope socket.

03/07/2015: Rigged up and tested slickline assembly; good test. Run in hole with slickline bailers and bailed on top of UCP. Negative test LBV; UBV and RV in SSTT with 8;000 psi below and bleeding off topside to 500 psi; good tests. Positive test RV to 7;600 psi; good test. RIH with slickline LCP pulling assembly to above RV. Bullheaded 440 bbls 14.1 ppg CaBr2 at 4 BPM to kill well. Filled well with 14.1 ppg CaBr2 while monitoring losses.
","WAR_START_DT":"2015-03-01","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":266,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"03/08/2015: Monitored losses after bullheading well kill fluid and adjusted completion fluid weight to 12.5 ppg CaBr2 to mitigate loss rate to the formation while maintaining well control. Bullheaded 14.1 ppg HEC pill down the kill line and circulated 14.1 CaBr2 to place HEC in tubing. Performed slickline operations to pull LCP and install the wear sleeve in the tubing hanger. RIH with no-go gauge on slickline to the top of SCSSV to 9;462' WLM; and perform SCSSV flapper checker run on slickline to 6;900'. Started bullheading 14.1 ppg HEC pill. 

Note: Total losses during the last 24 hours: 3;022 bbls (HEC pill pumped in last 24 hours = 287 bbls).

03/09/2015: Continued bullheading 14.1 ppg HEC pill. RIH with SCSSV flapper checker assembly to SCSSV no-go at 9;462' and POOH with assembly - verified with positive indication SCSSV flapper valve fully opened. RIH with Gauge Ring on slickline to 26;782'. Bullheaded 14.1 ppg HEC pill down the kill line. RIH with RPT lock and plug housing on slickline from surface to 26;400'. Bullheaded 14.1 ppg HEC pill and circulated 14.1 CaBr2 to place HEC in tubing. Monitored losses to the formation. Continued to RIH with RPT lock and plug housing to 26;785'. Attempted to set plug with no success. POOH with RPT lock and plug housing to surface. 

Note: Total losses during the last 24 hours: 2;207 bbls and Total losses to well: 5;229 bbls (HEC pill pumped in last 24 hours = 270 bbls; total HEC pumped to well = 557 bbls).

03/10/2015: Sheared RPT lock and plug assembly on deck indicating tool is working as designed. Re-dressed and RIH with RPT lock and plug assembly on slickline to 26;785'. Set and released from plug. POOH with tool string to surface and installed RPT Prong. RIH with RPT Prong with slickline to 26;785' and released from Prong. Monitored for losses to the formation - no losses recorded after Prong was set. POOH to surface with slickline. Pressure tested RPT plug with 14.1 ppg CaBr2 to 5;000 psi - good test. RIH with junk basket; released and POOH with running tool. 

Note: Total losses during the last 24 hours: 0 bbls and Total losses to well: 7;286 bbls (HEC pill pumped last 24 hours = 0 bbls; total HEC pumped to well = 557 bbls).

03/11/2015: RIH with SCSSV Hold Open Sleeve assembly from surface to 9;464' (SLM); set; and POOH with Hold Open Sleeve running tool. RIH with Wear Sleeve retrieval tool to 7;024' (SLM); latched in and POOH to surface. RIH with Isolation Sleeve assembly from surface to 7;024' (SLM); unable to set; and POOH. Reverse circulated 1.5x landing string volume to clear potential debris from setting area. RIH with Isolation Sleeve assembly #2 and successfully set at 7;027' (SLM). Pressure tested integrity of Isolation Sleeve to 5;000 psi for 15 minutes - good test. POOH with Isolation Sleeve running tool. 

03/12/2015: Rigged down slickline equipment. Closed the annular and opened the 9-5/8" rams to strip through annular with tubing hanger out of wellhead. Released TH from SSPT. Performed stack sweep to remove possible trapped gas beneath annular. Damaged control lines on SSTT while closing annular. Troubleshoot SSTT and prepared to pull SSTT. Discussed forward plan with management. 

03/13/2015: Tested latch mandrel on SSTT. Waited on MOC to be approved. Pulled tubing hanger above wellhead. Observed overpull while coming up with tubing string from 26;657' to 26;615' and pumped out of the hole. Rig down SFT and CCTLF. Continued to work seal assembly out of PBR. Picked up from 26;615' to 26;544 with SSTT and upper completions on 7-5/8" landing string. Rigged down DP handling equipment.

03/14/2015: POOH with 7-5/8" landing string; SSTT; TH with upper completion from 26;544' to 20;641'. CaBr2 started to u-tube up the landing string. Pumped 14.5 ppg Spike fluid to slug pipe. Boosted the riser and pumped 14.1 ppg CaBr2. Pumped additional 14.5 ppg Spike fluid to slug pipe. Closed upper ball valve on SSTT to stop string from u-tubing. Pulled out of hole wet from 20;641' to 19;866' on 7-5/8" landing string with SSTT and upper completion.
","WAR_START_DT":"2015-03-08","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":267,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"03/15/2015: Reversed out 14.1 CaBr2 packer fluid from 19;866' to stop u-tubing. Circulated 14.1 ppg CaBr2 and POOH from 19;866' until SSTT at surface and inspected for damage. Identified leaks on control lines. Transferred SSTT to Aft rotary. 

03/16/2015: Rigged up control line sheave and spliced into control line spoolers. L/D SSTT and tubing hanger. Continue POOH with 6" VIT production tubing from 19;418' to 18;036' and rigged up 4-1/2"" handling equipment. POOH with 4-1/2" tubing from 18;036' to17;165' to SCSSV. Capped SCSSV lines with new fitting and secured back to SCSSV stand. L/D SCSSV on Fwd rotary. Continued POOH with 4-1/2" tubing from 17;165' to 16;895'. Note: NORM rep checking reading while pulling tubing with no anomalies observed.

03/17/2015: Continued POOH with 4-1/2" tubing from 16;895' to 3;549'. Note: NORM rep checking reading while pulling tubing with no anomalies observed.

03/18/2015: Boosted light fluid out of the wellbore. Continued to TOH with 4-1/2" tubing to seal assembly. Rigged down the control line sheaves and continued to TOH with 4-1/2" seal assembly and laid out. TIH with jetting assembly from surface to 6;833'.

03/19/2015: Jetted SSPT with jetting assembly while ROV assisted flushing production tree. Circulated bottoms up. Spaced out across BOPs with 5-7/8" TFM test stand. Performed BOP pressure test (Toolpusher's panel; Blue Pod) on 5-7/8" 34# DP to 250/8;000 psi against VBRs and 9-5/8" fixed rams (fixed ram against 9-5/8" test mandrel). Pressure tested Annular to 250/4;300 psi per IPT SureTec Version 3.1 - all tests good. Function tested BOPs on 5-7/8" DP (Driller's panel; Yellow Pod; and Toolpusher's panel; Blue Pod) - good tests. Performed Diverter function test (Toolpusher's panel). Rigged down BOP testing equipment. TIH from 6;963' to 7;209' and jetted production tree. TOH from 7;220' to 5;073'.

03/20/2015: Continued to trip out of hole from 5;073' to 198'. Laid out and inspected jetting assembly. Picked up and tripped in hole from surface with jetting assembly #2 on 5-7/8" TFM pipe to 7;043'. Performed jetting operations working drill string over interval 7;028' to 7032' while flushing SSPT via IWOCS. Boosted the riser to clear light fluid from wellbore. Continued jetting operations while waiting on ROV support and boosting wellbore as ROV flushed production tree lines. 

03/21/2015: Circulated bottoms up. TOH from 7;033' to 197' and laid out jetting assembly. TIH with diverter assembly on 5-7/8" DP to 3;405'. Picked up SSTT and M/U to tubing hanger. RIH with 7-5/8" landing string. RIH with tubing hanger on 7-5/8" landing string from surface to 3;693'.
","WAR_START_DT":"2015-03-15","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":268,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"03/22/2015: Continued to TIH from 3;693' to 10;418'. Locked and tested tubing hanger. Note: Performed MODU ESD Lamp Test and MODU ESD Weekly Drill.

03/23/2015: Unlatched tubing hanger. POOH with tubing hanger from 10;418' to 2;525'. 

03/24/2015: Continued to TOH with 5-7/8" TFM pipe from 2;525' to surface. Functioned UBSR/LBSR from Driller's panel on Blue Pod - successful test. P/U tubing seal assemblies. P/U and test downhole pressure/temperature gauge; and chemical injection mandrels - good test. Seals at 396'.

Note: BSEE visit from Clint Campos; Paul Reeves and James Richard.

03/25/2015: Completed testing of downhole pressure/temperature gauge and chemical injection mandrels. TIH with production tubing from 396' to 12;627'.

03/26/2015: Continued to TIH with production tubing from 12;627' to 15;477'. Terminate control lines and tested SCSSV and chemical injection mandrel - successful test. Continue to TIH with production tubing to 18;928'

03/27/2015: Finished TIH with production tubing from 18;928' to 19;616'. P/U and M/U tubing hanger. Terminated and tested control lines - successful test. Latched SSTT to tubing hanger and tested same - successful test. 

03/28/2015: Continued to TIH with SSTT from 19;616' to 19;773'. TIH on 7-5/8" landing string to 26;594'. 
","WAR_START_DT":"2015-03-22","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":269,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"03/29/2015: Soft landed tubing hanger with the end of tubing at mule shoe 26;662'. P/U string to 26;577' to displace the tubing by casing annulus. S/O from 26;577 to 26;622'. Note: Perform MODU ESD Lamp Test and Weekly ESD Drill.

03/30/2015: Tested production equipment - all tests successful.

03/31/2015: Continued testing production equipment - all tests successful. Rigged up wireline valve and lubricator. Performed pressure test on Halliburton lubricator to 250/10;000 psi for 5 minutes - good test.

04/01/2015: Completed testing lubricator to 250/10;000 psi for 5 minutes - good test. RIH with slickline and retrieved isolation sleeve. RIH with slickline and set wear sleeve in production tree. Performed bailer operations. 

04/02/2015: RIH with slickline and retrieve junk basket.

04/03/2015: Rigged down slickline unit and rigged up braided wireline unit. Made up and tested lubricator to 250/10;000 psi for 5 min - good test. 

04/04/2015: Troubleshoot packoff issues with braided wireline system.
","WAR_START_DT":"2015-03-29","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":270,"API12":608124005000,"TEXT_REMARK":"04/05/2015: RIH with RB Prong retrieval tool to latch onto RB Prong at 26;785' and POOH. RIH with 3" bailer from surface to 26;785' and bailed over top of RPT housing. 

04/06/2015: POOH with 3" bailer assembly to surface. Recovered 1.2 lbs of debris from bailer run. RIH with RPT Lock and Plug retrieval tool from surface to 26;785'. Pulled RPT Lock and Plug free. Bullhead 75 bbls of base oil into formation while pulling RPT Lock and Plug from 26;785' to surface. Losing at 180 bph. Began performing negative test on SCSSV by bullheading 314 bbls of 6.6 ppg base oil down landing string. Pressure stabilized at 2;802 psi. Bled down to 200 psi with 3 bbls bled back. Observed a 1 psi/min decrease in pressure. Continued monitoring to achieve a 60 minute straight line test.

04/07/2015: Continued negative test on SCSSV. Test good. RIH and retrieved wear bushing. RIH and set LCP at 7;034'. POOH with LCP running tool to surface. Tested top of LCP to 10;800 psi for 15 minutes (13;400 psi subsea). Displaced riser from 14.1 ppg CaBr2 to 8.6 ppg seawater.

04/08/2015: RIH with UCP and set at 7;031' and test top to 10;800 psi and between upper and lower to 13;000 psi subsea with IWOC; good tests. Bullhead 166 bbls 6.6 ppg base oil down kill line. Bled pressure on annulus under tubing hanger to riser margin seawater equivalent. Pumped an additional 50 bbls of 6.6 ppg base oil. Performed negative test by bleeding back pressure from 4;308 psi in 500 psi increments to 690 psi and held 60 min straight line; good negative test. 

04/09/2015: Displaced kill line with 8.6 ppg seawater. Function tested 9-5/8" casing rams and tested to 250/11;500 psi; Test good. ROV stabbed "LPR close" and functioned with hot stab; tested 250/1;000 psi; test good. Stroked in CCTLF and unlatched from tubing hanger. Flushed SSPT with 25 gal of Methanol and displaced landing string with 8.6 ppg seawater. Removed torpedo packers and transferred SFT to AFT rotary. 

Note: On 04/09/2015 at 07:06 hrs; Mr. Chris Gerlitz (Chevron) notified Mr. Bobby Nelson and Mr. Josh Ladner (BSEE) via email that Chevron is conducting final suspension operations on the Jack PS005 workover and will be latching up to Jack PS004 completion on Saturday; April 11th; and completing initial subsea testing as per APM approved on 04/08/2015.

04/10/2015: POOH with 7-5/8" landing string and SSTT from 6;992' to surface. Transferred SSTT to center mousehole. 

Note: On 04/10/2015 at 20:54 hrs; Mr. Kevin Corbin (Chevron) emailed Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) requesting verbal approval to remove the lock out of the riser connector unlock functions - note lock out the stab retracts will remain; to avoid risk of accidental function. 

04/11/2015: Transferred SSTT from FWD rotary to center mousehole. Positioned rig to 290° and installed BLAT tool into slip joint. Transferred weight from tensioners to BLAT tool and unlatch from Jack PS005 SSPT. P/U 25' and move rig to Jack PS004.

On 04/11/2015 at 11:17 hrs; Mr. Kevin Corbin (Chevron) received approval from Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) via email that Chevron may proceed with revised procedure to remove the lock out of the riser connector unlock functions.","WAR_START_DT":"2015-04-05","WELL_NAME":"PS005"},{"   ":271,"API12":608124011500,"TEXT_REMARK":"01/13/2017: Completed between well maintenance. R/U forward to run 36" conductor. RIH with 36" conductor on forward. R/D 36" running tool and equipment on forward. RIH with 30" assembly inside 36" conductor on forward. P/U 36" conductor and jet in assembly on forward. Lowered to moonpool and installed slope indicators and ROV valves on low pressure wellhead.

01/14/2017: TIH with 36" jet in assembly for PS007 on forward to 500' above mud line.  Picked up remaining 36" conductor and ran same on aft for PS008. TIH with 36" jet in assembly for PS008 on aft from surface to 500' above mud line. Moved rig from PS007 DOZ over PS007 location and began jetting 36" conductor on forward rotary.  Jetted 36" conductor to 7;258' (211' of 311' casing jetted Below Mud Line). 
Note: Well sequences were split between PS007 and PS008 as per the permits and the rig move report submitted to BSEE.
","WAR_START_DT":"2017-01-13","WELL_NAME":"PS007"},{"   ":272,"API12":608124011500,"TEXT_REMARK":"01/15/2017: Jetted 36" casing from 7;258' to 7;358' and let soak for 1 hour. Released from low pressure wellhead running tool and TOH from 7;358' to 7;036'. Washed low pressure wellhead and took survey; .38 degrees @ 6;998'. TOH from 7;036' to 6;878'. ROV installed temporary abondement cap on PS007 low pressure wellhead and surveyed sea floor; no indications of broaching.

01/16/2017: Transited DCL to Jack PS007 DOZ. TOH from 6;878' to surface with 36" jetting assemblies. TIH with 23" x 22" casing from surface to 138' on aft rotary.

01/17/2017: TIH with 23" x 22" casing on aft from 138' to 3;537'. Removed running tool and TIH with inner string to 3;308'. Made up lockdown tool to inner string and high pressure wellhead. 02/27/2017: Continue between well maintenance. ROV performed bottom survey. Subsea finished stump test.

Note: Mr. Scott Dieffenbaugher (Chevron) provided 72 hr written notification to Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) that the Pacific Sharav will be performing initial latch up testing for Jack PS007 on February 27; 2017. 

02/28/2017: Complete between well maintenance. Run BOP on marine riser from surface to 193' MD.

03/01/2017: Continue running BOP on marine riser from 193' MD to 2;803' MD. Failed to test choke and kill lines to 250-350 psi low and 15;000 psi high due to numerous leaks on surface valves while on high pressure test. Repair valves and retest choke and kill to 250-350 psi low and 15;000 psi high with seawater. Please see "Significant Events" for further detail.

03/02/2017: Finish running BOP on riser from 2;803' MD to 6;888' MD. Test choke and kill lines to 250-350 psi low and 15;000 psi high test with seawater. Test mud boost and rigid conduit lines to 5;000 psi test. ROV tether winch failed while ROV was subsea. While recovering the ROV to surface; the ROV lost communication at 790' MD. When the ROV recovered to surface; the tether was found parted.

03/03/2017: Reterminate ROV tether and deploy. Transit from Jack PS007 DOZ to well center and confirmed wellhead depth. Transit to DOZ and install telescopic joint. Test riser auxiliary lines; rigid conduit lines and boost lines to 5;000 psi with seawater. Leak observed on choke line gooseneck. Repaired gooseneck and tested to 15;000 psi.

03/04/2017: Complete testing on riser auxiliary lines. Lower telescopic joint to share load with tensioners. Transit from Jack PS007 DOZ to well center. Land BOP on Jack PS007 High Pressure Well Head (HPWH) and perform slump test. Latch up and perform overpull test. Conducted flow-through test on the diverter. Trip in hole (TIH) with BOPTT BHA from surface to 7;732' MD and landed BOPTT in wellhead. Perform EHBS test. Perform casing test with 8.6 ppg seawater to 2;200 psi. Performed function test on diverter from primary panel. Perform Emergency Hydraulic Backup System (EHBS) test from Primary Panel; Blue Pod. Function test Blind Shear Ram (BSR) from Primary Panel; Blue Pod; and from Secondary Panel; Yellow Pod. Function test Casing Shear Ram (CSR) from Primary Panel; Blue Pod; and from Secondary Panel; Yellow Pod.

Note: On 03/04/2017; Mr. Harry Wilson (Chevron) received written notification from Mr. Justin Ledet (BSEE) that Chevron may continue with operations with the failed subsea analog gauge.

03/20/2017: Drill from 24;588' MD/ 21;660' TVD to 24;653' MD/ 21;724' TVD with 12.0 ppg surface MW (12.3 ppge DH). Observe gradual decrease in standpipe pressure (SPP) and turbine speed over last 2 stands drilled down. Pick up off bottom and troubleshoot decreasing parameters. Attempt to drill ahead and unable to keep Telescope in sync. Pump out of hole in search of washout from 24;653' MD/ 21;722' TVD to 24;149' MD/ 21;234' TVD. Decision made to de-activate reamer and activate Churchill circulating sub. Observe parameters and verify washout in BHA below circulation sub. Circulate hole clean through circulation sub while rotating and reciprocating drill string. Observe Main Top Drive Motor B allowing coupling to shift out of gear. Continue to circulate without rotation while troubleshooting the Main Top Drive. Flow check well; well static. Trip out of hole (TOH) on elevators from 24;149' MD/ 21;234' TVD to 22;175' MD/ 19;587' TVD and observe 100k overpull. TIH 3 stands while pumping and circulate without rotation while troubleshooting Main Top Drive Motor B.

03/21/2017: Continue circulating bottoms up from 22;600' MD/ 19;896' TVD with 12.0 ppg surface MW (12.3 ppge DH). Observe parameter changes indicating a complete washout and loss of BHA. Flow check well; well static. TOH from 22;600' MD/ 19;896' TVD to surface and observe loss of BHA below wear sleeve running tool (WSRT); leaving 467' of BHA left in well. Begin removing Top Drive Motor B from Aux and prepare to remove Main Top Drive Motor B.
 
03/22/2017: Remove Main Top Drive Motor B and install Aux Motor B in the Main Top Drive. Perform rotation and torque testing on Main Top Drive with newly installed Motor B. Monitor well on trip tank; well static.

03/24/2017: Circulate hole clean with 12.0 ppg surface MW (12.3 ppge DH) while racking back one stand every 1.5 hrs from 22;067' MD/ 19;511' TVD to 21;900' MD/ 19;395' TVD. Latch SDC ring and transfer BOP and riser weight to tensioners. Lay down landing joint and install diverter.

09/12/2017: Trip in hole with riser brush assembly. Flush riser with seawater. Trip out of hole with riser brush assembly. Make up Boll Weevil test tool and Nu-Tec assembly and trip in hole to 6;671'. Make up BLAT and engage slip joint profile. Land and latch BOP to SSPT. Set Boll Weevil test tool in SSPT and release from Nu-Tec tool. ROV hook up EFL/HFL to SSPT.

09/13/2017: Performed Deadman test subsea per TOI procedure with 8.6 ppg seawater (failed test). Confirmed activation of UBSR by testing against BWTT/UIC/LIC to 250-350/ 11;500 psi for 5 minutes; pressure would not hold. Re-test on UBSR; pressured up to 11;500 psi (good test). Performed Deadman test subsea per TOI procedure (good test). Confirmed activation of UBSR by testing against BWTT/UIC/LIC to 250-350/ 11;500 psi for 5 minutes (good test). Test LBSR and associated valves to 250-350/ 11;500 psi for 5 minutes each (good test). Trip in hole to 7;856' and make up Nu-Tec tool. Performed surface accumulator drawdown test per TOI procedure (good test). Performed ROV intervention test per TOI procedure. Attempted to confirm closure of MVBRs by testing against test rams to 250-350 psi (failed test). Pressure tested BOPs on 5-7/8" drill pipe from Driller's Panel; Yellow Pod. All tests performed against SSTVs using 8.6 ppg seawater. Tested annular and associated valves to 250-350/ 6;300 psi for 5 minutes each. Tested VBRs and associated valves to 250-350/ 11;500 psi for 5 minutes each. Tested upper/lower MDDM valves along with assocated valves to 250-350/ 11;500 psi for 5 minutes each. Middle IBOP on MDDM failed test. Test Kelly hose to 250-350/ 7;000 psi for 5 minutes each. Performed ROV Intervention test per TOI procedure. Confirmed closure of MVBRs by testing against test rams to 250-350/ 11;500 psi for 5 minutes each (good test). Re-test UVBRs and associated valves to 250-350/ 11;500 psi for 5 minutes each. Function test BOPs on Blue Pod from Toolpusher's Panel (good test). Function Diverter from Driller's Panel (good test). Trip out of hole with Boll Weevil test tool and Nu-Tec assembly from 7;641' to surface. Function tested BSRs from Driller's Panel; Yellow Pod; and from Toolpusher's Panel; Blue Pod. Change out Middle MDDM IBOP and pressure test upper MDDM IBOP and middle MDDM IBOP to 250-350/ 11;500 psi for 5 minutes each.

Note: On 09/13/2017 at 14:43 hrs; Mr. Blake Maddoux (Chevron) received approval from Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) of the RPM which was submitted to address two BOP faults (see Significant Events). 

09/14/2017: Trip in hole with Archer Packer retrieval tool to 7;853'. Displace riser to 14.1 ppg CaBr2. Engage and release 10-3/4" Archer Packer at 7;983'. Trip out of hole with 10-3/4" Archer packer from 7;983' to surface.

09/15/2017: Circulate and condition riser. Trip in hole with Archer Packer retrieval tool to 17;766'. Circulate and condition 14.1 ppg CaBr2. Engage 9-7/8" Archer Packer at 17;883' and release. Trip out of hole with 9-7/8" Archer Packer to surface. Test BSRs and associated valves to 250-350/ 7500 psi for 5 minutes with 14.1 ppg CaBr2. Test casing to 7;500 psi for 30 minutes.

09/16/2017: Test UBSRs and LBSRs with associated valves to 250-350/ 7500 psi for 5 minutes with 14.1 ppg CaBr2. Test casing to 7;500 psi for 30 minutes. Trip in hole with displacement assemblies from surface to 26;910' and wash to 27;003'. Circulate and condition 14.1 ppg CaBr2. Continue to trip in the hole from 27;003' to 29;840'.

Zone 3: 29;735' - 29;842' MD IES / 26;881' - 26;986' TVD - IES
Zone 2: 30;453' - 30;560' MD IES / 27;583' - 27;688' TVD - IES
Zone 1: 30;693' - 30;800' MD IES / 27;818' - 27;923' TVD - IES

09/20/2017: Circulated across firing head post firing TCP assembly; established initial loss rate of 32 bph which slowed to 18 bph. Opened bypass and reversed out 1;098 bbls. Unseated packer and tripped out of hole from 30;800' to 29;725'. Flow check well for 30 minutes; loss rate 3 bph. Trip out of hole with TCP assembly from 29;725' to 9;070'. Circulated through choke and kill lines; no gas observed. Trip out of hole from 9;070' to 1;140' with TCP assembly.

09/21/2017: Pull out of hole; laying down spent TCP gun assembly from 1;440' to surface. Pick up Deburr assembly and run in hole to 168'. Continue to trip in hole with Deburr assembly to 29;685'. Activate vacuum tool and deburr perforations from 29;675' to 30;976'. Tag no go on sump packer at 30;813' MD. Circulate bottoms up.

09/22/2017: Continue circulating bottoms up. Short trip Deburr assembly from 30;976' to 29;590' MD. Flow check well; 1-2 bph losses. Trip in hole from 29;590' to 39;976' with Deburr assembly; with no fill noted. Trip out of hole from 30;976' to 26;956'; vacuum and wash from 26;956' to 26;900'. Trip out of hole from 26;956' to 8;845'. Pressure tested BOP on 5-7/8" drill pipe from Toolpusher's Panel; Blue Pod. Tested Annular and associated valves to 250-350/ 4;300 psi; VBRs and associated valves to 250-350/7;500 psi. Tested upper/lower MDDM valves along with associated valves to 250-350/ 7;500 psi; and Kelly hose to 250-350/ 7;000 psi. During pressure testing of the BOP/choke manifold; valve #1 on choke manifold was observed to not hold pressure. The valve was greased and the test was successful; with no other complications observed. All tests performed with 14.1 ppg CaBr2. Monitor well throughout testing; losses at 2-4 bph.

09/23/2017: Complete BOP pressure testing from Toolpusher's Panel; Blue Pod. Test VBRs and associated valves to 250-350/ 7;500 psi. Function test BOP on Driller's Panel; Yellow Pod. Function diverter from Toolpusher's Panel. All tests successful. Trip out of hole with Deburr assembly from 8;845' to surface. Make up and trip in hole with single trip multiple zone gravel pack assembly to 1;862'. 
","WAR_START_DT":"2017-09-17","WELL_NAME":"PS007"},{"   ":302,"API12":608124011504,"TEXT_REMARK":"09/24/2017: Trip in hole with single trip multiple zone gravel pack assembly from 1;862' to 2;583'. Latch into the suspension tool; shear out and trip out with service tool fishing assembly. Pressure test service service tool to 250 psi for 5 minutes (good test). Make up VCH packer and extension sub to 1;279'. Trip in hole with single trip multiple zone gravel pack assembly from 1;279' to 18;133'.

09/25/2017: Trip in hole with gravel pack assembly from 18;133' to 30;813'. Sting into sump packer at 30;813' DPM with 5 klbs down. Slack off to 30;912' mule shoe depth setting 20 klbs down on sump packer. Pick up 56 klbs overpull to snap out of sump packer; no indication of release. Slacked back down to 20 klbs down on sump packer. Set VCH packer with 2;500 psi at 29;637' DPM and verify packer set with "push/pull" test. Release running tool. Pressure test back side against VCH packer to 1;500 psi for 5 minutes (good test). Set isolation packers pressuring up the backside to 4;300 psi. Make up frac head and surface lines and test to 5;000 psi (good test). Mark service tool positions. 

09/26/2017: Pickle workstring to 500' from crossover and reverse out. Obtain reverse rates with rig pumps at 4; 8; 10 and 12 bpm. Verify and mark tool positions. Verify MCS/FCS sleeves are open. Test frac lines to 13;500 psi (good test). Pumped acid job with frac boat; initially 180 bph losses stabilized at 30 bph in final reverse position. Pumped 102 bbls of 6.6 ppg base oil down kill line with 1;840 psi. Performed mini-frac at 30 bpm with 75 bbls of 9.5 ppg NaCl crosslinked gel. Performed main frac pack on Zone 1. Pumped 660;639 lbs of proppant and screened out. Stripped to reverse position and reversed out 212;755 lbs of proppant with total of 1;089 bbls. Stripped up to contingency reverse position with good indication of FCS closing. Perform system test with 1;500 psi for 5 minutes (good test). Open annular and confirm free travel in work string; observed losses of 284 bph during reverse circulation. MCS shifted open during verification of free travel; re-closed MCS. Reversed out 2 drill pipe volumes of 1;400 bbls. 

09/27/2017: Lay down frac head and positioned service tool for Zone 2 frac operations. Pick up frac head; flushed and tested lines to 13;500 psi. Pump acid job with frac boat. Performed minifrac at 15 bpm with 75 bbls of 9.5 ppg NaCl crosslinked gel. Pumped main frac for Zone 2 in WDC position. Pumped 417;713 lbs of proppant and screened out. Stripped to final reverse position and reversed out 127;797 lbs of proppant. Due to pressure considerations and loss of fluid while reversing out; stripped to contingency reverse position after reversing out 95 bbls. Pumped a total of 1;008 bbls. Perform system test to 2;000 psi for 5 minutes (good test). Confirmed free travel and reversed out 2 drill pipe volumes of 1;400 bbls. Lay down frac head.

09/28/2017: Tested frac sleeves to 500 psi for 5 minutes (good test). Pulled up to locate Zone 3 indicator nipple with 15 klbs down; position service tool for frac operations. Test frac head to 13;500 psi (good test). Pumped Zone 3 acid job with frac boat. Performed mini-frac at 15 bpm with 75 bbls of 9.5 pg NaCl crosslinked gel. Pumped Zone 3 main frac in WDC position. Pumped total of 406;425 bbls of proppant and screened out. Stripped up to final reverse position and reversed out 216;128 lbs of proppant. Due to losing tubing pressure; stripped up to contingency reverse position after reversing out 540 bbls. Reversed out total of 974 bbls. Confirmed free travel; and reversed addition 2 drill pipe volumes of 1;377 bbls. Lay down frac head. Trip out of hole from 29;919' to 29;519'. Tested frac sleeves at 500 psi for 5 minutes (good test). 

09/29/2017: Pumped base oil out of kill line. Trip out of hole with service tool from 29;519' to surface. Function test UBSRs/LBSRs from Driller's Panel; Yellow Pod; and from Toolpusher's Panel; Blue Pod. Pick up isolation assemblies for zones 1; 2 and 3 and trip in hole to 1;411'.

09/30/2017: Trip in hole with isolation assembly from 1;411' to 29;548'. Performed BOP function test on 5-7/8" drill pipe from Driller's Panel; Blue Pod; and from Toolpusher's Panel; Yellow Pod. Functioned diverter from Driller's Panel. Trip in hole with isolation assembly from 29;548' to 30;910'; opening production sleeves across zones 3 through 1. Estimated loss rate of ~500 bph with all zones open. Sting seals into VCH seal bore and losses stopped. Slack off 30 klbs down and pick up 30 klbs to confirm latch. Pressure tested VCH seals and FS2-HI assembly to 1;000 psi with 14.1 ppg CaBr for 5 minutes (good test). Dropped brass diverter ball; then pressured up to 2;500 psi to release running tool. Trip out of hole from 29;500' to 17;997'.
","WAR_START_DT":"2017-09-24","WELL_NAME":"PS007"},{"   ":303,"API12":608124011504,"TEXT_REMARK":"10/01/2017: Trip out of hole from 17;997' to surface and lay down isolation assembly setting tool. Pressure tested UBSR and LBSR against FS2-HI valve at 1;000 psi for 5 minutes with 14.1 ppg CaBr (good tests). Pick up and trip in hole with TNT packer assembly to 18;119'. 

10/02/2017: Trip in hole with TNT packer assembly from 18;119' to 29;517'; landing anchor latch in isolation assembly with 30 klbs. Confirmed TNT latched with 30 klbs overpull. Pressured up on annulus to 1;000 psi and tested short seal assembly for 5 minutes (good test). Set TNT packer with total of 90 klbs down and 5;000 psi. TNT packer depth at 29;314' MD DPM. Pick up 30' above TNT PBR. Pressure tested TNT permanent packer and casing to 5;000 psi for 30 minutes with 14.1 ppg CaBr (good test). Trip out of hole to 240' and lay down TNT packer running tool. 

10/03/2017: Trip out of hole and lay down 2-7/8" inner string. Pick up bore protector running & retrieving tool assembly to 7;702'. Pressure tested BOPs on 5-7/8" drill pipe from Driller's Panel; Yellow Pod; with 14.1 ppg CaBr. Tested annular and associated valves to 250-350/ 4;300 psi for 5 minutes each. Tested VBRs and associated valves to 250-350/ 7;500 psi for 5 minutes each. Tested upper; middle and lower MDDM valves with associated valves to 250-350/ 7;500 psi for 5 minutes each. Tested Kelly hose to 250-350/ 7;000 psi for 5 minutes each. All tests good. Function tested BOPs from Toolpusher's Panel; Blue Pod (good test). Trip out of hole to 7;568'. Functioned diverter from Toolpusher's Panel (good test). Jet production tree with 8 bpm. Trip in hole and engage bore protector at 7;015' with 20 klbs down. Pressure tested 9-5/8" rams on 9-5/8" test mandrel against bore protector running & retrieving tool from Driller's Panel; Yellow Pod; at 250-350/7;500 psi for 5 minutes each (good test). Function tested SSTV from Toolpusher's Panel; Blue Pod (good test). Pull bore protector from production tree profile with 37 klbs overpull and pull above BOP stack. Trip out of hole to 7;568' and jet production tree at 8 bpm. Trip out of hole with bore protector running & retrieving tool assembly from 7;389' to 4;214'.

10/04/2017: Trip out of hole with bore protector running & retrieving tool assembly from 4;214' to surface. Trip in hole with bore protector running & retrieving tool with bore protector to 1;204'; then tripped out of hole to surface. Wait on weather for Tropical Storm Nate.

10/05/2017: Decision made to secure well for Tropical Storm Nate. Displaced choke line to seawater. Close LBSR and test against FS2-HI valve to 1;000 psi for 5 minutes with 14.1 ppg CaBr (good test). Closed UBSR. Displace kill; boost and riser to seawater. Rig up to pull riser; unlock and pull diverter. 

Note: On 10/05/2017 at 10:13 hrs; Mr. Blake Maddoux (Chevron) received approval from Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) to proceed with the proposed temporary isolation procedure.

10/06/2017: Make up landing joint and unlatch LMRP from Driller's Panel; Blue Pod. Removed SDC ring from slip joint. Lay down slip joint; termination joint; flex joint and riser pups. Pull LMRP on marine riser from 6;860' to 1;309'. 

Note: On 10/06/2017 at 16:09 hrs; Mr. Blake Maddoux (Chevron) notified Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) that depending on weather conditions; the Discoverer Clear Leader plans to latch up to Jack PS007 BP04 well approximately 72 hours from now.

10/07/2017: Pull LMRP on marine riser from 1;309' to surface. Wait on weather for Tropical Storm Nate.
","WAR_START_DT":"2017-10-01","WELL_NAME":"PS007"},{"   ":304,"API12":608124011504,"TEXT_REMARK":"10/08/2017: Run LMRP on riser to 5;137' MD.

Note: On 10/08/2017 at 10:23 hrs; Mr. Blake Maddoux (Chevron) received from Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) the approval for well re-entry provided the following take place: pressure test riser connector/gasket; pressure test choke/kill stabs at
LMRP/BOP; deadman test; full function test both pods/panels/remote panels; and verify acoustic pod communication (if equipped).

10/09/2017: Run LMRP on riser to 6;713' MD; land and latch LMRP on BOP. Tested BOP choke and kill stabs and associated valves to 250-350/ 11;500 psi (good test). Install diverter and function test from Driller's Panel; Blue Pod (good test). Noted that LMRP connector gasket retainer pins did not retract. Displace seawater in riser with 14.1 ppg CaBr.

10/10/2017: Continue displacing riser from seawater to 14.1 ppg CaBr. Monitor well for pressure; well static. Displace seawater from choke line to 14.1 ppg CaBr. Perform Deadman test and confirmed activation of UBSR by testing against FS-2HI valve and associated valves to 250-350/ 1;000 psi for 5 minutes (good test). Trip in hole with jetting assembly on 5-7/8" drill pipe from surface to 7;671' MD. Function tested BOPs from Driller's Panel; Yellow Pod (good test). Pressure tested BOPs on 5-7/8" drill pipe from Toolpusher's Panel; Blue Pod; against SSTVs using 14.1 ppg CaBr. Tested annular and associated valves with LMRP connector to 250-350/ 4;300 psi for 5 minutes (good tests). Tested VBRs and associated valves to 250-350/ 7;500 psi for 5 minutes each (good tests). Tested upper; middle and lower MDDM valves along with associated valves to 250-350/ 7;500 psi for 5 minutes each test (good tests). For pressure test #18 in the choke manifold; could not hold pressure during high test. Greased valves and performed test to 250-350/ 7;500 psi (good test). Test Kelly hose to 250-350/ 7;000 psi for 5 minutes (good test). Trip out of hole from 7;671' to 7;570' MD. Function diverter from Driller's Panel (good test). Jet production tree and circulated bottoms up with 14.1 ppg CaBr. Trip out of hole to 3;261' MD.

10/11/2017: Continue to trip out of hole with jetting assembly to surface. Function UBSR and LBSR from Driller's Panel; Blue Pod; and from Toolpusher's Panel; Yellow Pod. Pick up and run seal stem and 4-1/2" tubing for upper completion. Install CIM and DHPTG and terminate lines as needed. Continue running 4-1/2" tubing to 7;283' MD.

10/12/2017: Continue running 4-1/2" tubing to 19;724' MD. Made up SCSSV; CIM and associated clamps. Continued running 4-1/2" tubing to 20;083' MD.

10/13/2017: Continue running 4-1/2" tubing to 20;730' MD. Run 6" VIT to 22;231' MD. Made up 5-1/2" tubing joints; pick up tubing hanger assembly and make up to tubing string. Cut; terminate and test control lines to tubing hanger. Pick up Land & Lock and engage tubing hanger running tool to hanger. Trip in hole with 7-5/8" drill pipe from 22;231' to 22;312' MD.

10/14/2017: Installed junk basket. Trip in hole with tubing string to 29;195' on 7-5/8" drill pipe. Made up MDDM to soft land stand and soft land tubing hanger at 7;018' with proper seal engagement. Trip out of hole from 29;275' to 29;195'. Spot 1;234 bbls of 14.1 ppg CaBr inhibited packer fluid. Rig up compensated coiled tubing lift frame.
","WAR_START_DT":"2017-10-08","WELL_NAME":"PS007"},{"   ":305,"API12":608124011504,"TEXT_REMARK":"10/15/2017: Make up surface flow tree to string. Slack off from 29;230' to 29;275' MD installing torpedo packers on landing string. Land out tubing hanger at 7;018' MD and locked tubing hanger with 6;500 psi with IWOCS. Tested tubing hanger upper seals to 12;800 psi subsea for 30 minutes (good test). Tested SCSSV1 and SCSSV2 stabs and control lines to 10;000 psi for 15 minutes (good test). Tested tubing hanger lockdown to 12;800 psi subsea (good test). Tested gallery seal cavity to 13;457 psi subsea for 30 minutes (good test). Tested production bore to 12;800 psi subsea for 30 minutes (good test). Tested tubing by casing annulus below hanger to 5;000 psi surface for 30 minutes (good test). ROV engage DHPT electrical penetrators. Re-tested gallery seal to 13;457 psi subsea for 30 minutes (good test). Test lubricator and surface flow tree to 10;000 psi for 15 minutes; test check valve in kill line surface lines for 5 minutes (good tests). Test tubing string against FS-2HI to 5;000 psi for 15 minutes. Closed SCSSV and bled pressure to 200 psi for negative test.

Note: On 10/15/2017 at 15:33 hrs; Mr. Blake Maddoux (Chevron) was granted approval from Mr. Justin Ledet (BSEE) for a 4 day extension for the casing/BSR pressure tests.

10/16/2017: Monitor negative test on SCSSV for 30 minutes (good test). Run in hole with slickline and retrieve isolation sleeve. Displace kill line and landing string with 6.6 ppg base oil. Make up slickline toolstring with lower crown plug (LCP). Run in hole with slickline to 7;016' slickline measured depth. Pressure up landing string to 3;000 psi and jarred down 25 times to set LCP. Sheared off and pulled out of hole with slickline. Displaced riser to seawater while setting LCP. Test LCP from above at 12;800 psi subsea (good test). Test LCP from below to 7;700 psi surface for 60 minutes against FS-2HI valve (good test). Line up tree and open FS-2HI valve cycling pressure from 5;500 psi to 1;500 psi surface. Observe pressure increase from 1;500 psi to 1;800 psi after FS-2HI valve opened. Bullhead 45 bbls of 6.6 ppg base oil and closed SCSSV. Started negative test bleed cycles to 800 psi. Closed tree valves and trend pressures. 

10/17/2017: Opened tree valves; pumped additional 10 bbls 6.6 ppg base oil with SCSSV closed. Cycle SCSSV. Bleed pressure to 0 psi while monitoring trend. Close in well at cement unit and monitor pressures on tree and at cement unit for 30 minutes (good test). Make up upper crown plug (UCP) to slickline tool. Reinstall lubricator and test connector to 10;400 psi for 5 minutes (good test). Run in hole with UCP and set at 7;011' slickline measured depth. Pressure test UCP from above to 12;800 psi subsea for 15 minutes (good test). 

10/18/2017: Pressure test between LCP and UCP to 12;800 psi subsea for 30 minutes (good test). Displace base oil with seawater up kill line. Unlatch tubing hanger running tool. Displace landing string from base oil to seawater. Trip out of hole from 6;937' to surface with tubing hanger running tool and umbilical on 7-5/8" landing string.

10/19/2017: Rig up riser handling equipment. Remove diverter from housing; pick up landing joint. Make up to and unlock slip joint. Unlatch BOP and transit to Jack DOZ. 

10/20/2017: Pull BOP stack on marine riser to surface.
