","WAR_START_DT":"2017-10-15","WELL_NAME":"PS007"},{"   ":306,"API12":608124011504,"TEXT_REMARK":"03/04/2018: Run BOP on marine riser from 1;394' to 6;789'. Install termination joint and slip joint. Install drape hoses. Rig down riser yoke. Test choke; kill; boost and rigid conduit lines. Make up split dual cylinder (SDC) ring and transfer weight to tensioners. Scope out slip joint. Make up diverter.

03/05/2018: Install diverter. Rig down riser handling equipment and rig up drill pipe handling equipment. Make up riser brush and jet sub assemblies. Trip in hole from surface to 6;640'; reciprocating each stand. Repair remote operated vehicle (ROV). Slip and cut drill line while making repairs. Service rig. Trip in hole from 6;640' to 7;018'. Jet and function BOP.

03/06/2018: Jet BOP. Pump out of hole from 7;018' to surface. Engage BOP landing assist tool (BLAT). Transit rig from safe handling zone (SHZ) to well center. Land and latch BOP on PS007. Perform slump and overpull test. Perform Deadman test and test blind shear rams (BSRs) to 300/11;500 psi. Trip in hole with tubing hanger BOP test tool (THBOPTT) assembly from surface and land THBOPTT in profile at 7;026'. Perform initial latch-up testing as per test plan. 

03/07/2018: Perform BOP pressure tests from Primary Panel on Yellow Pod. Test rams to 300 psi/ 9;500 psi. Test Annular to 300 psi/ 6;600 psi. All tests performed with 8.6 ppg seawater on 5-7/8" drillpipe. Perform ROV intervention and accumulator drawdown tests. Function test BOP from Secondary Panel on Blue Pod. Function test Diverter from Primary panel . Pull out of hole with THBOPTT from 7;026' to surface. Displace riser from seawater to 14.1 ppg CaBr2. Transfer subsea test tree (SSTT) from center mouse hole (CMH) to forward rotary. Lower through rotary.

03/08/2018: Install Weatherford (WFT) spider. Trip in hole with SSTT on landing string from 122' to 6;933'. Rig up compensated coil tubing lift frame (CCTLF). Transfer surface flow tree (SFT) from CMH to forward. Pick up and position SSTT above BOP. Wait on equipment. 

03/09/2018: Wait on equipment. Transfer and make up SFT to string. Rig down WFT spiders.

03/10/2018: Install torpedo packers. Rig up and test surface iron. Dummy land tubing hanger. Pick up 2 ft and spot base oil to underbalance well by 300 psi. Soft land tubing hanger. Attempt to latch tubing hanger per One Subsea (OSS) with no success. Latch tubing hanger on third attempt and observe issues with SSTT. Consult onshore support. Decision made to unlatch and pull out of hole with SSTT to replace riser control module (RCM). Unlatch hanger and reverse out base oil. Slack off and scope in CCTLF. Rig down and transfer SFT to center mousehole.
","WAR_START_DT":"2018-03-04","WELL_NAME":"PS007"},{"   ":307,"API12":608124011504,"TEXT_REMARK":"03/11/2018: Transfer surface flow tree (SFT) to center mousehole. Rig down and lay out compensated coil tubing lift frame (CCTLF). Pull out of the hole with subsea test tree (SSTT) on landing string. Troubleshoot and transfer SSTT to center mousehole. Trip in hole with one subsea (OSS) tubing hanger (TH) jet assembly from surface to 1;600'.

03/12/2018: Trip in hole with OSS TH jet assembly from surface to 6;946'. Obtain baseline parameters. Function test BOP from Secondary Panel on Yellow Pod and from Primary Panel on Blue Pod. Jet tubing hanger at 7;026' and circulate bottoms up through choke and kill lines. Open annular and circulate one riser volume with 14.1 ppg CaBr2. Pull out of the hole with OSS TH jet assembly from 7;026' to surface. Trip in hole with OSS TH jet assembly and re-jet TH. Pull out of hole from 7;026' to 6;311'.

03/13/2018: Pull out of hole with OSS jet tool and junk basket to surface. Run in hole with OSS jet tool and junk basket from surface to 7;026' and jet tubing hanger. Run in hole with OSS jet tool and junk basket from surface to 7;026'. Close annular and "reverse" circulate at 7.5 bpm with 1;080 psi. Circulate 2 hydroxyethyl cellulose (HEC) 15 bbl sweeps through kill line at 12 bpm with 1;390 psi. Pull out of hole with OSS jet tool and junk basket from 7;026' to surface. 

03/14/2018: Land OSS jetting tool in TH profile. Reverse circulate 14.1 ppg CaBr2 at 7.5 bpm with 1;100 psi. Pump and reverse out two 15 bbl HEC sweeps. Continue reverse two drill string volumes. Jet TH profile. Pull out of hole with OSS jetting tool and junk basket form 7;026' to surface. Transfer Expro SSTT from center mousehole to Forward rotary. Install junk basket stand and install Weatherford 7-5/8" landing string handling equipment. Run in hole with Expro SSTT on 7-5/8" landing string from surface to 3;178'.

03/15/2018: Trip in hole with Expro SSTT on 7-5/8" landing string from 3;178' to 6;927'. Pick up and rig up CCTLF. Transfer SFT from center mouse hole to CCTLF. Install torpedo packers and soft land tubing hanger running tool (THRT) on soft land piston at 7;026' with a 68 psi pressure spike. Pressure test surface iron and surface flow tree. Spot 139 bbls of 6.6 ppg base oil in landing string. Land and lock THRT as per OSS procedure. Test 9-5/8" rams against upper TH seals to 12;787 psi subsea. Test Surface Flow head to 10;000 psi. Pressure test landing string to 12;945 psi subsea.

03/16/2018: Rig up Halliburton slickline equipment and lubricator. Make up and pick up into lubricator 3" bailer assembly. Test lubricator to 10;000 psi for 15 mins - good test. Run in hole with 3" bailer assembly and recover 4 lbs of debris. Make up and run 1.5" bailer assembly and recover 8 oz of debris. Make up and run pulling tool and retrieve upper crown plug (UCP) to surface. Pressure test Expro SSTT lower ball valve to 12;800 psi subsea - good test. Pressure test Expro SSTT Upper ball valve to 12;800 psi subsea.

03/17/2018: Test Expro SSTT upper ball valve to 12;800 psi subsea - good test. Bullhead 50 bbl HEC pill followed by 418 bbls of 14.1 ppg CaBr2. Close production tree crossover (XOV) valve; monitor well on UWPT; DHPT and RCM gauges - well stable. Run in hole with Downhole Power Unit (DPU) pulling assembly and retrieve lower crown plug (LCP) at 7;028'. Pull out of hole LCP from 7;028' to surface. Lay out DPU pulling assembly. Make up and run in hole with TH wear sleeve on wireline to 7;028' and set. Pull out of hole with TH wear sleeve setting assembly from 7;028' to surface. Make up and run in hole with 3.4" gauge ring. Tag nipple profile at 29;421' MD - confirm 3 times. Pull out of hole with 3.4" gauge ring from 29;442' to surface. Make up 3.313" RPT Lock Plug assembly and run in hole to 6;800'. Bullhead 50 bbl HEC pill followed by 325 bbls of 14.1 ppg CaBr2.
","WAR_START_DT":"2018-03-11","WELL_NAME":"PS007"},{"   ":308,"API12":608124011504,"TEXT_REMARK":"03/18/2018: Continue displace 50 bbls hydroxyethyl cellulose (HEC) from tubing with 14.1 ppg CaBr2. Run in hole with 3.313" RPT Lock Plug from surface to 29;421' and attempt to set as per Halliburton. Pull out of hole with RPT setting tool and found RPT Lock Plug still on tool. Make up second 3.313" RPT Lock Plug and run in hole to 29;421' and attempt to set as per Halliburton. Unsuccessful set after 82 cycles on. Pull out of hole with Lock Plug. Make several attempts to work through obstruction at 29;161'; with no success. Shear off Lock Plug and pull out of hole with setting tool form 29;161' to surface. Pump 50 bbls HEC pill and displace with 420 bbls of 14.1 ppg CaBr2 (470 bbls total bbls pumped). Test lubricator to 10;000 psi for 15 mins utilizing IPT - good test. Run in hole with Halliburton pulling tool from surface to 15;000'.

03/19/2018: Run in hole (RIH) with Halliburton pulling tool. Engage RPT plug lock housing at 29;454'. Pull out of hole to surface. Run in hole with 3.30" gauge from surface to 29;596' (tag top of FS2-HI valve). Pull out of hole from 29;596' to surface. Pump 50 bbls HEC pill and displace with 415 bbls of 14.1 ppg CaBr2 (465 total bbls pumped). Wait on Halliburton replacement wheel assembly to be delivered to rig.

03/20/2018: Wait on replacement wheel assembly. Repair Halliburton Slickline unit. Run in hole with third 3.313" Lock Plug assembly and set at 29;421'. Pull out of hole with setting tool. Rig up and run in hole with 3.313" Prong assembly from surface to Lock Plug at 29;421'. Engage plug housing with Prong; apply 500 psi on landing string and verify set. Pull out of hole with Prong running tool. Close retainer valve when running tool above 6;800'; line up on mini trip tank and confirm well static (no losses) while continue pull out of hole with Prong running tool.

03/21/2018: Pull out of hole with junk basket setting tool. Run in hole and retrieve tubing hanger (TH) wear sleeve. Pull out of hole with wear sleeve. Run in hole and install TH isolation sleeve. Pull out of hole with isolation sleeve setting tool. Test isolation sleeve lockdown to 1;850 psi - good test. Test isolation sleeve production bore to 7;650 psi - test failed. Rig up and run isolation sleeve retrieval tool. Pull out of hole with isolation sleeve. Rig up new isolation sleeve and run in hole with same. Pull out of hole with running tool and test isolation sleeve per OSS; good test. Begin rigging down slickline equipment.

03/22/2018: Rig down slickline lubricator and pressure control equipment (PCE). Strip up and unseat TH. Sweep BOP. Open annular. Pick up TH above lower blind shear ram (LBSR). Rig down surface flow tree (SFT) and transfer to AFT. Lay down compensated coiled tubing lifting frame (CCTLF) and rig up landing string handling equipment. Pull out of hole with upper completion on landing string. Displace packer fluid with 14.1 ppg CaBr2. Shut down displacement to transfer contaminated fluid from Port sand trap and processing pits to cuttings boxes - greater than expected contaminated interface returns.

03/23/2018: Pull out of hole with TH on landing string. Release tubing hanger running tool (THRT) and subsea test tree (SSTT) from TH. Transfer SSTT to center mousehole (CMH). Install tubing hanger handling and test tool (THHTT) to TH and rig up handling equipment. Rig up sheave cluster for downhole lines.

03/24/2018: Rig up sheave cluster for downhole control lines. Cut downhole lines and connect to spooling units. Rig up Weatherford 6" handling equipment. Pull 13 stands of 6" vacuum insulated tubing (VIT). Rig up Weatherford 4-1/2" handling equipment; 6 stands of 4-1/2" tubing and rack back same. Lay out surface controlled subsurface safety valve (SCSSV) to main deck. Pick-up and install new SCSSV/ chemical injection unit (CIM) assembly. Terminate and test SCSSV control lines to 10;000 psi for 15 mins utilizing IPT. Verify opening and closing pressures on both A and B circuits. Terminate and test CIM control line to 10;000 psi for 15 mins utilizing IPT.
","WAR_START_DT":"2018-03-18","WELL_NAME":"PS007"},{"   ":309,"API12":608124011504,"TEXT_REMARK":"03/25/2018: Continue run in hole with 6" vacuum insulated tubing (VIT). Rig down tubing handling equipment. Pick up hanger and terminate control lines.

03/26/2018: Continue test downhole control lines at splice sub. Secure all control lines in splice sub. Test surface controlled subsurface safety valve (SCSSV) control lines (internal) to 10;000 psi for 15 mins utilizing IPT - good test. Rig down Weatherford tubing handling equipment from Forward. Rig up 30 ft 500T bails and 350T side door elevators. Transfer subsea test tree (SSTT) from center mousehole and make up tubing hanger running tool (THRT) to tubing hanger (TH). Pressure test SSTT control lines SV1; SV2 and utility stab to 9;000 psi with 1% drop for 15 minutes trend and chart with OSS. Function test and apply and maintain pressure to THRT. Make up junk basket stand to RCM handling pup. Install Weatherford RCS-500 landing string slips. Function test Weatherford slips and rig up auto clamp system on Expro umbilical. Trip in hole with Expro SSTT on 7-5/8" landing string from 22;379' to 29;180'. Displace 14.1 ppg CaBr2 with 14.1 ppg CaBr2 inhibited packer fluid (850 bbls of 1;808 bbls).

03/27/2018: Finish spotting 1;808 bbls of 14.1 ppg CaBr2 packer fluid. Rig up and function test coiled tubing lifting frame (CCTLF). Transfer and make up Expro surface flow tree (SFT) to string. Rig down Weatherford spiders. Install torpedo packers. Soft landing tubing hanger and slack off upper completion weight of 830k. Lock tubing hanger. Unlock CCTLF and engage passive heave compensation. Test tubing hanger. Pressure test SCSSV1 and SCSSV2 lines with installation workover control system (IWOCS). Pressure test tubing hanger seal test (THST) seal gallery. Pressure test production gallery seals with IWOCS. Pressure test casing by tubing annulus. Power down subsea production tree (XT). ROV engage XP downhole pressure and temperature (DHPT). Establish communications with DHPT. Finish rigging up slickline pressure control equipment and GS tool string. Pressure test surface iron and slickline equipment.

03/28/2018: Pressure test lubricator and all surface iron to 10;500 psi - good test. Close bypass valve on Concentric manifold and tested same to 10;500 psi - good test. Pressure tested down tubing string testing SFT body; landing string and production tubing to 5;000 psi - good test. Applied 2;400 psi down tubing string; closed SCSSV and bled surface pressure to 200 psi; negative testing SCSSV - good test. Suspend operations due to weather.

03/29/2018: Wait on weather. Evaluate inclement weather conditions. Pressure test slickline pressure control equipment. Attempt to run in hole with GS pulling tool and observe twist on slickline drum. Troubleshoot line issues.

03/30/2018: Troubleshoot slickline unit. Run in hole with tubing hanger isolation pulling tool. Tag sleeve at 7;026'. Retrieve tubing hanger isolation sleeve and recover to surface. Reverse out missing tubing hanger seals. Run in hole and set tubing hanger wear sleeve. Run in hole with junk basket pulling tool. Tag junk basket at 29;450' SLM. Retrieve junk basket and recover to surface. Run in hole with RPT prong pulling tool. Tag prong at 29;450' SLM. Attempt to pull prong and shear pins in pulling tool. Pull out of hole with pulling tool from 29;450' to 6;500'.

03/31/2018: Pull out of hole with 3.5" RS pulling tool to surface. No prong recovered. Run in hole with RS pulling tool and tag prong at 29;455' SLM. Retrieve RPT plug prong and recover to surface. Run in hole with plug pulling tool. Tag plug at 29;457'. Retrieve RPT plug and recover to surface. Run in hole with tubing hanger wear sleeve pulling tool. Tag sleeve at 7;026'. Retrieve tubing hanger wear sleeve and recover to surface. Displace riser from 14.1 ppg CaBr2 to seawater. Bleed off tubing by casing annulus. Bullhead 34 bbls of base oil down tubing string. Close SCSSV. Run in hole and set lower crown plug (LCP) in profile at 7;027'. Pressure test LCP from above.
","WAR_START_DT":"2018-03-25","WELL_NAME":"PS007"},{"   ":310,"API12":608124011504,"TEXT_REMARK":"04/01/2018: Negative test lower crown plug (LCP) with no flow for 30 min. Close suface controlled subsurface safety valve (SCSSV) and perform negative test on SCSSV. Run in hole and set upper crown plug (UCP) in tubing hanger profile at 7;030'. Pressure test UCP from above and below. Close annular; open 9-5/8" fixed ram; and displace kill line with seawater. Rig down slickline equipment. Troubleshoot and repair compensated coiled tubing lifting frame (CCTLF). Displace riser with seawater. Rig down slickline equipment. Slack off and scope in CCTLF. Unlatch tubing hanger running tool (THRT) and displace landing string with seawater.

04/02/2018: Remove control lines from surface flow tree (SFT) and rig down surface iron. Break out SFT and lay out CCTLF. Pull out of the hole with subsea test tree (SSTT) to surface. Rig down Weatherford landing string handling equipment and rig up 30' bails to modular derrick drilling machine (MDDM). Transfer SSTT to center mousehole. Trip in hole with BOP lift assist tool (BLAT) assembly and engage profile at 149'. Position rig to unlatch heading. Perform ROV Connector Unlock and All Stabs Retract/Connector Unlock (ASR/CU) function test.

04/03/2018: Perform Wellhead Connector Unlock function test with ROV. Recover and repair ROV thermal fault. Repeat wellhead unlock function with ROV. Unlatched BOP at 08:00 hrs. Move rig 42' off location and install tertiary cap on tree.

","WAR_START_DT":"2018-04-01","WELL_NAME":"PS007"},{"   ":311,"API12":608124011606,"TEXT_REMARK":"    --- Depths are as per the DIN's RKB ---

08/26/2018: Opened FFV (full function valve) and circulated BU. Flow checked well with BU at 3;000'; 2;000' and 1;000' below BOP before bringing BU up the riser - well static. TOH 5 stands wet with Baker GTV packer from 24;340' to 23;582'. Slugged pipe. TOH from 23;582' to surface. Service rig. TIH with Baker cut & pull assembly from surface to 3;887'

08/27/2018: TIH with Baker casing cut & pull assembly to 25;327' while filling pipe every 20 stands. Land marine swivel in WH. Cut casing at 25;381'. Rotated for 4 hours without any clear indication of casing cut. Pulled up and engaged spear at 24;677'. Pulled fish free; hoisted into 14" shoe at 24;880'. Opened FFV; slug pipe and begin hoisting fish to surface.

08/28/2018: Continue TOH with 9 5/8" fish. Recovered 751.89 ft; including expandable liner top. 

08/29/2018: R/D WFD equipment; TIH with cement stinger to 26;580'. Spot pill and pull up to 25;880'. Circulate bottoms up. Pump balanced cement kick-off plug; 152 bbls/ 854 cu ft of 17.0 ppg cement. Pull out of cement plug and circulate 2x DP volumes. Cement plug placed from 24;680' to 25;880' MD (pumped 10% excess).

08/30/2018: Circulated 2x DP volumes; slug pipe and TOH with cement stinger to 13;605'. Function tested BOPs on 6-5/8" DP from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod and from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod. Function tested diverter from Toolpusher's Panel. TOH with cement stinger to surface. Slip & cut drill line. TIH with 12-1/4" directional BHA to 12;926'.

08/31/2018:  TIH with 12-1/4" BHA to 24;312'. Washed down and tagged bypass plug at 24;539'. Reamed down to 24;567' and performed Choke Drill. Drilled firm cement from 24;680' to 24;910' and initiate kick-off for BP06. 

    --- All depths from this point forward will be as per the DCQ's RKB ---

08/31/2018: Initiated BP06 kick off at 24;919' and confirmed kick off at 24;928' MD/ 24;417' TVD.  Drilled to 24;975'. Pulled inside 14" shoe and circulate B/U with 13.8 ppg. Performed FIT to 709 psi / 14.3 ppg surface / 14.7 ppg downhole EMW. Drilled 12-1/4" BP06 hole section to 25;001' MD.

09/01/2018: Drilled 12-1/4" BP06 hole section from 25;001' to 26;396' MD/ 25;839' TVD.
","WAR_START_DT":"2018-08-26","WELL_NAME":"PS008"},{"   ":312,"API12":608124011606,"TEXT_REMARK":"No Wireline Logs Run 09/02/2018: Drilled 12-1/4" hole section from 26;396' to 27;290' with 13.8 ppg surface/ 14.1 ppg downhole SBM. Drilling suspended due to tropical storm activity. Pump sweep and circulate surface to surface. Flow check well - static. TOH wet from 27;290' to 26;320'.

09/03/2018: TOH wet from 26;320' to 24;845'. Pumped slug and TOH with 12-1/4" drilling BHA to 17;384'. Circulated slug above the BOPs. TIH with BOP/NuTec test assembly to 24;445'. Pressure test BOPs on 5-7/8" DP with 13.8 ppg surface/ 14.1 ppg downhole SBM to 300/ 8;400 psi from Driller's Panel; Blue Pod. Test annulars to 300/ 4;600 psi. During the course of pressure testing BOPs; HPHT sensor below the test rams increased from 1;989 psi to 2s144 psi (155 psi). Line up and monitor well on Mini Strip Tank; 0.5 bph gain observed. Well shut in at 20:08 hrs. Build 400 bbls of 17.7 ppg SBM and prepare to spot riser cap.

09/04/2018: Continue building 400 bbl 17.7 ppg riser cap. Spot 20 bbls (1;000 ft) of 17.7 ppg riser cap down the choke line; monitor well on Mini Strip tank. Well static. Spot 1;000 ft of 17.7 ppg riser cap 2;000 ft above BOP. Function test BOPs on 5-7/8" DP from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod and from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod. TOH from 24;439' to 17;348' with BOPTT. TIH with 12-1/4" drilling assembly from 17;348' to 27;212'. Displace riser cap with 13.8 ppg surface/ 1412 ppg downhole SBM. Weight up mud system to 13.9 ppg surface/ 14.2 ppg downhole SBM. Pump 13.9 ppg SBM down the drill string; circulate bottoms up to 3;000 ft below BOP. Close lower annular and displace wellbore with 13.9 ppg SBM; taking returns up the choke and kill line.  

09/05/2018: Circulated B/U to 3;000 ft below BOPs. Closed the LAP and circulated B/U to surface via choke/kill lines; max gas 128 units. Opened LAP and washed down to bottom. Circulated B/U. Flow checked well and TOH to 14" shoe. Flow checked well; pumped slug and monitored well until TT stabilized. TOH with 12-1/4" BHA from 24;889' to 6;648'. Slip and cut drill line and function test Upper and Lower BSRs from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod and from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod.

09/06/2018: Slip and cut drill line. Function test diverter on 6-5/8" DP from Driller's Panel. TIH with 12-1/4" BHA from 6;648' to 27;290'. Downlink to MWD. Drill 12-1/4"hHole section from 27;290' to 27;985' with a 13.9 ppg surface/ 14.2 ppg downhole SBM.

09/07/2018: Drilled 12-1/4" hole section from 27;985' to 28;159 with a 13.9 ppg SBM. Circulate bottoms up. Continued drilling 12-1/4" hole section to TD of 28;671' MD/ 27;998' TVD. Downlinked to MWD and pumped 100 bbl sweep and circulate out of hole. Perform swab test and circulate bottoms up.

09/08/2018: Continued circulate B/U after performing SIT. TOH wet from 28;671' to 28;043'. Pumped slug; dropped drift and continued TOH to 24;880'. Flow checked inside 14" liner shoe and continued TOH to 8;251'. Flow checked well and TOH to 894'. Downlinked to turn off MWD battery and TOH with 12-1/4" BHA to surface. R/U casing handing equipment. RIH with 9-7/8" liner to 1;636'.
","WAR_START_DT":"2018-09-02","WELL_NAME":"PS008"},{"   ":313,"API12":608124011606,"TEXT_REMARK":"09/09/2018: TIH with 9-7/8" liner from 1;636' to 4;019'. R/D WFD casing equipment. R/U DP equipment. P/U HES VersaFlex liner hanger. Verify 8 shear pins (94k) installed. R/D casing slips and install LSS 1;250 DP slips. TIH with 9-7/8" liner on LS to 28;670'. Convert Diverter sub and M/U cement head. Spot 9-7/8" shoe on depth at 28;670' MD/ 27;997' TVD. Circulate 710 bbls (1 LS volume + 100 bbls). Staging pumps up to 3.5 bbm with 1;240 psi. No losses observed.

09/10/2018: Continue circulating LS volume + 100 bbls. Cement 9-7/8" liner per program with 100% returns; bumped plug with 500 psi over FCP; bled off and confirmed floats holding. Cement in place at 08:57 hrs. Total volume of 15.8 ppg Class H cement was 156 bbls; leaving 39 bbls in the shoe track. 657 cu ft placed in annulus with TOC at 26;331' MD. Attempt to set 9-7/8" VersaFlex liner hanger with pressure to deploy liner hanger flapper. Did not observe pressure drop internal bypass not activated. Drop 2.75" activation ball and set liner hanger at 24;587' MD/ 24;084' TVD . L/D cmt head and pull two stands above PBR. Pump Nerf balls and circulate 1.5x string volume. Function test BOP on 6-5/8" DP from Driller's Control Panel on Yellow Pod and from Toolpusher's Control Panel on Blue Pod. Perform full Diverter function test on 6-5/8" DP from Toolpusher's Control Panel. Pump slug and TOH to 22;376'.

09/11/2018: POOH with 9-7/8" liner hanger running tool from 22;376' to surface. Slip and cut drill line. TIH with DQ MPT (WBRT) with tail pipe and diverter sub from surface to 7;633' (div depth) landing out WBRT on WB at 7;045' with 20k down and engaged WB. TOH with WBRT to spaceout jet sub at profile. Wash and jet profile. TOH with WB on DQ MPT from 7;115' to surface. Performed planned maintenance. Functioned UBSR using Acoustic from bridge. Function tested UBSRs and LBSRs from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod and from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod. Performed casing pressure test to 2;700 psi for 30 mins-  good test. Performed Upper and Lower BSR test to 250-350 psi/ 2;700 psi for 5 mins each from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod.

09/12/2018: Rigged up to run 9-7/8" x 10-3/4" tieback. Run 9-7/8" x 10-3/4" tieback from surface to 16;168'. 

09/13/2018: Continue to RIH with 9-7/8" x 10-3/4" tieback from 16;168' to 17;577'. Change out casing running equipment to DP elevators. PU Dril-quip hanger assembly and install OES flowback tool. TIH with 9-7/8" x 10-3/4" tieback on 6-5/8" landing string from 17;577' to 24;577'. Set 9-7/8" x 10-3/4" tieback at 24;599' MD/ 24;095' TVD. Make up cement stand and soft land hanger at 24;605' with 17 ft of seal engagement. Pick up out of seals and circulate and condition mud to spec prior to cement job.

09/14/2018: Performed cement job on 9-7/8" x 10-3/4" tie-back. No losses were observed during the cement job. Total volume of 15.5 ppg Class H cement was 794 bbs; leaving 31.5 bbls in the shoe track. 4;281 cu ft placed in annulus with TOC at 8;200' MD. Sting SA into PBR. Set and test 10-3/4" liner hanger at 7;047' MD/TVD. Handed off cement head to Aux racker. Installed single with nerf balls and circulated same to surface. TOH with hanger running tool from 7;005' to surface. Noticed Seal Assembly was retrieved with running tool.

09/15/2018: Continued to change out 6-5/8" saver sub with 5-7/8" TFM saver sub. Install 1;000 ton bails and BX-5 elevators. Change out handling equipment to 5-7/8" while continuing to reconfigure MPT Mill/Flush Tool. TIH with Mill/Flush Tool with 950 ft of tailpipe from surface to 8;050'. Took baseline parameters and slacked off to tagged SA profile. Milled top of 9-7/8" x 10-3/4" tieback hanger assy. Unable to get back down to orginal depth with Mill and Flush tool (lost ~10"). Troubleshoot issue. Pump 100 bbl Hi-Vis sweep and circulated surface to surface. Attempt multiple iterations to get back to original Mill and Flush depth. Pumped 100 bbl Hi-Vis weighted sweep and circulate surface to surface. TOH from 8;046 to 953'.
","WAR_START_DT":"2018-09-09","WELL_NAME":"PS008"},{"   ":314,"API12":608124011606,"TEXT_REMARK":"9/16/2018: Re-dress Dril-Quip MPT with new Mill & Flush Tool. TIH from 953' to 8;046' MD. Took baseline parameters. Slacked off to 8;084'; landing out in SA profile at 7;048'. Cleaned off top of 9-7/8" x 10-3/4" tieback hanger assembly. Pumped 100 bbls 13.9 ppg hi-vis sweep and circulated to surface. Pumped slug and TOH to 953'. Made up seal assembly stand and TIH to 8;046'. Took P/U and S/Os. Slacked off and set seal assembly in 9-7/8" x 10-3/4" tieback hanger assembly at 7;048' with 50k down. With weight down; tested SA to 9;400 psi. Trip out of hole with seal assembly running tool from 8;046' to surface. RIH with 8-1/2" cleanout BHA from surface to 1;078'.

Note: Upon further analysis of of returns of mill and flush run #1; no cement in returns. Returns were a mixture of spacer; contaminated mud and LCM.

09/17/2018: TIH with 8-1/2" cleanout BHA and WBRT from surface to 8;356'; installing WB in WH at 7;045'. Short trip to surface to lay out WBRT. TIH to 6;574'. Slip and cut drill line and performed planned maintenance. TIH with cleanout assemby from 6;574' to 13;791'. Rig up double-dutch and begin BOP testing.

09/18/2018: Completed BOP pressure tests on 5-7/8" DP from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod with 13.9 ppg surface/ 14.2 ppg downhole SBM. Rams tested to 250-350 psi/ 8;400 psi. Annulars tested to 250-350 psi/ 4;600 psi. Function tested BOP on 5-7/8" DP from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod. Rigged down BOP test assembly. Function tested Diverter from Driller's Panel and from Driller's Chair. TIH from 13;791' to 24;028'. Performed choke drill. Wash down and tag cement at 24;263'. Drilled out tieback from 24;263' to 24;626'. Polished tieback gap. Circulated bottoms up. TOH to above tieback shoe track. TIH to below tieback gap with no drag. TIH and tagged up with 20 klbs down at 24;697'. Drilled from 24;697' to 24;803'.

Note: BSEE Inspectors Joshua Naquin and Clint Campo arrived on ship at 09:00 hrs. Monthly Inspection completed with no INCs. Departed ship at 13:30 hrs.

09/19/2018: Drilled cement from 24;803' to 24;876'. TIH from 24;946' to 25;355'; tagged with 30k down. Washed down from 25;355' to 28;436 ' and tagged upper float collar. Drill out shoe track from 28;436' to 28;632'.

09/20/2018: Continued to drill out shoe track from 28;632' to 28;660'. Short tripped shoe track from 28;660' to 28;420. Pumped 100 bbl sweep and circulated until sweep was 5;000' above tieback. TOH from 28;662' to 24;697'. Washed tieback gap. Picked up to 24;563' and circulated 1.5x BU. TOH from 24;563' to 149'.

09/21/2018: TOH from 149' to surface. Rig up Baker wireline. RIH with plugged packer from surface to 28;649' and set packer. POOH with plugged packer setting tool from 28;649' to surface. Pressure tested casing to 8;050 psi with 13.9 ppg surface/ 14.2 downhole SBM.P/U and TIH with Cleanwell displacement BHA to 10;823'.

09/22/2018: TIH with displacement assembly from 10;823' to 28;499'. Made up side entry and reversed out slug. Circulated and conditioned mud. Perform successful inflow test to 2;350 psi. Circulate and condition mud in preparation for displacement. Displaced boost; choke and kill lines from 13.9 ppg SBM to 14.0 ppg CaBr2.

","WAR_START_DT":"2018-09-16","WELL_NAME":"PS008"},{"   ":315,"API12":608124011606,"TEXT_REMARK":"09/23/2018: Continued displacing well from 13.9 ppg SBM to 14.0 ppg CaBr2. Performed online line cleaning Phase 2b and 3. Cleaned surface equipment and lines in preparation for completion operations.

09/24/2018: Reversed out 2;800 bbls at 16 bpm (4;800 psi). R/D SES. Jetted the BOP/ HPWH. Boosted riser and circulated one riser volume. Circulated CaBr2 to spec. Function tested the BOPs on 5-7/8" DP from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod and from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod. Performed diverter function test from Toolpusher's Panel. TOH with Cleanwell displacement BHA from 28;634' to 27;962'.

Note: On 09/24/2018 at 18:10 hrs; Mr. Bill Sanders (BSEE) provided Mr. Matt Hensgens (Chevron) with approval to proceed with setting the Baker GT deeper to account for the pressure differential.

09/25/2018: TOH with displacement assembly to surface. Functioned UBSR/LBSR from the Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod and from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod. Slip and cut drill line; service RF equipment. P/U and TIH with Baker GT packer to 17;533'. Set GT packer at 17;533' MD/ 17;500' TVD. Pressure tested packer to 1;000 psi from below and 1;000 psi from above. Spot 50 bbl Hi-Vis pill on top of packer.  

09/26/2018: Spot 50 bbl Hi-Vis pill on top of suspension packer. TOH with Baker GT packer RT to 8;096. TIH with Cleanwell Vali-Tech/MPT to 15;313'. Washed WB & pulled with 70K overpull. TOH to 8;107'. M/U LIT & function same. TIH with LIT to 15;310'. Slacked off & landed LIT at 7;044'. Obtained LIT impressions. TOH to 8;262'. Removed LIT blocks & inspect. Removed metal from Mag-Tech. Assisted Dril-Quip with adjustments on LDS & performed final checks. TIH with LDS to 14;304'.

09/27/2018: Installed Lock Down Sleeve (LDS) at 7;047'. TOH to 8;290'. Displaced well from ~8;000' from 14.0 ppg CaBr2 to seawater. TOH with Baker GT running tool to surface. P/U and RIH BLAT tool. Engaged BLAT profile and transferred weight from tensioners to top drive. Unlatched BOP at 17:00 hrs. Ended WR 758 Jack PS008 BP06 drilling operations at 17:00 hrs.

ROV removed BOP gasket and cleaned WH. Obtain LDS measurements. Move off to DOZ. Deploy UDB with AHC crane to 6;948'. Move vessel from DOZ to UDB landing position. Lowered UDB from 6;948' and land on sea floor. Prep Subsea XT to be lifted from boat.

09/28/2018: Deploy XT to 1;000' WD and confirm ring gasket. Lower XT to 500' AML in DOZ. Transited per approach corridor and placed XT above WH. Lowered XT and landed out on WH. Oriented XT and locked/tested XT connector to 14;700 psi. Positioned rig and placed BOP over XT. Landed BOP on XT. Transferred weight from BLAT tool to riser tensioners and released BLAT. Closed LBSRs and performed WH connector test to 1;000 psi. TIH with GT running tool and tail pipe to 7;411'. M/U BWTT and TIH to 10;228'.

09/29/2018: TOH to 689'. M/U BWTT and TIH to 7;830'. Land out BWTT. Pressure tested BOPs on 5-7/8" DP from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod; using 8.6 ppg seawater. Pressure tested choke manifold and all surface safety valves to 300/10;000 psi for 5 min; pipe rams and associated valves to 300/10;000 psi for 5 min; kelly hose to 300/6;500 psi for 5 min and annulars to 300/6;500 psi for 5 min. Pressure tested BOP WH connector to 300/11;500 psi for 5 min. Function tested BOPs from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod and from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod. Functioned diverter from Driller's panel.
","WAR_START_DT":"2018-09-23","WELL_NAME":"PS008"},{"   ":316,"API12":608124011606,"TEXT_REMARK":"09/30/2018: TIH with GT packer retrieving tool to 17;507. Rev out HEC pill and circulated until fluid clean. Washed down; latch and unseat GT Packer. TOH from 17;517' to surface. Slipped and cut DL while pressure testing Casing/UBSR/LBSR from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod with 14.0 ppg CaBr2 to 7;500 psi. Function tested USBR/LSBR from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod and from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod R/U wireline equipment. RIH with HLB sump packer on wireline to 28;610'. Correlate and set HLB Sump packer at 28;586'. POOH with sump packer setting tool to 11;461'.

10/01/2018: POOH with sump packer tool string on e-line. Laid out DPU/wireline tool string assemblies. R/D wireline equipment and capstan. Rig up TCP handling equipment. RIH with TCP gun assembly to 6;459'. Performed additional test per internal requirements; tested casing and UBSR/LBSR to 300/7;900 psi. TIH with TCP gun assembly to 27;401'.

10/02/2018: TIH with TCP assemblies to 28;565'. S/O and locate sump packer at 28;595' DPM with 20k down (+9 ft correction from IES). Snapped out of the sump packer with 30k overpull. P/U 11.44 ft to place guns on depth. R/U surface lines and test. Set TCP Positest packer. Closed LAP and pressured up backside to 500 psi. Established baseline circulating pressures at 2.5 bpm through TCP manifold. Executed e-Fire sequence. Perforated Zone 1 from 28;529' to 28;571' MD (27;893' - 27;903' TVD). Perforated Zone 2 from 28;321' to 28;385' MD (27;666' - 27;726' TVD). Monitored pressures with choke closed. Opened choke and established initial loss rate of 120 bph and increasing. Average loss rate 432 bph over 3 hrs. Closed IRDV and opened circulating port. Spot 50 bbls of Tek-plug in drill string to 10 bbls from circulating port. Attempted to cycle IRDV with no success. Shut down and monitored well while building 2 x 25 bbl TBC-Brinadd sized salt pills.

10/03/2018: Pumped 130 bbls before returns were observed. IRDV ball valve functioned to the open position. Established loss rate at 521 bph. Boosted riser at 15 bpm. Unseated packer with ~70k overpull. Loss rate increased to 644 bph once packer was unseated. TOH; placing guns above top perfs. Set Positest packer. Pumped 25 bbl TBC-Brinadd salt pill. Loss rate at ~340 bph. Pump 2nd 25 bbl TBC-Brinadd salt pill. Loss rate ~330 bph. Build Barablend 949 N-Seal pill. Pumped 25 bbl Barblend 949 N-Seal pill. Loss rate at ~260 bph. Shut down and build 2nd Barablend 949 N-Seal pill. Pumped 50 bbl Barblend 949 N-Seal pill. Loss rate at ~252 bph. Shut down and build 50 bbl TekPlug with Baracarb. Filled string = 87 bbls.

10/04/2018: Pumped 50 bbl TekPlug with Baracarb - loss rate at ~300-320 bph. Build 2nd 38 bbl TekPlug with Baracarb. Filled the string with 106 bbls and established loss rate at 368 bph. Pumped 38 bbl TekPlug pill. Spot pill in place; pumping at 6 bpm circulating across top of string through TCP manifold/flowmeters - loss rate ~306 bph. Build next pill. Filled string every 2 hrs and recorded volume to fill string = ~120 bbls. Pumped 50 bbl Carb/N-Seal/Barolift FLC pill - loss rate at ~280 bph. Build next pill. Top filled string every 2 hours and recorded volume to fill string = 76 bbls. Established loss rate at 315 bph. Filled string with 103 bbls and pumped 50 bbl Carb/N-Seal/Barolift FLC pill - loss rate at 215 bph.

10/05/2018: Monitor well while building pill. Pump 50 bbl Barablend 657 with Baraflake C pill and displace down to perfs; with losses reducing from ~400 bph to 0 bph. Pick up string to open by-pass. Monitor both drill pipe and backside; with both static. Reverse circulate; staging pumps to 2.0 bpm with 300 psi - no losses. Continued circulating until gas levels decreased.

10/06/2018: Finish reverse circulating two drill pipe volumes. Unseat packer with 120k lbs of overpull. Pump spike fluid. TOH to 27;535'. Function test BOPs from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod and from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod. Function diverter from Toolpusher's Panel. Reverse slug from drill pipe. Circulate bottoms up to ~3;000 ft from BOP. Circulate remainder of bottoms up through C&K lines. Flush across BOP and boost riser volume. Flow check - static. TOH with spent TCP gun assemblies from 27;535' to 8;465'. Closed annular and opened C&K lines. Circulated 1.5x bottoms up through C&K lines - no losses recorded while circulating. Flow checked well - static. TOH with TCP guns to 6;196'.
","WAR_START_DT":"2018-09-30","WELL_NAME":"PS008"},{"   ":317,"API12":608124011606,"TEXT_REMARK":"10/07/2018: TOH with spent TCP guns from 6;196' to 886'. Pre-job safety meeting; change out slips. TOH with spent TCP guns from 886' to surface (93.37 ft of guns left in hole). Discuss plan forward with office. Rig service. Make up Cleanwell Deburr BHA and TIH to 26;150'.

10/08/2018: TIH from 26;150' to 27;950' with Cleanwell Deburr BHA. Obtain baseline parameters. TIH from 27;950' to 28;220' and tag TOF. Reverse out 1.5 DP volumes. Wash down to 28;226' and re-establish TOF. Perform several passes with and without pumps; confirmed solid TOF at 28;226'. Reverse out 1.5 DP volumes. TOH from 28;225' to 18;460'.

10/09/2018: Continue TOH with with Cleanwell Deburr BHA from 18;460' to surface. Slip and cut drill line. Make up 8-1/2" Rock Bit to CWT Assy 1 (Deburr Mill) and TIH to 9;782'. Space out 5-7/8" 34# test stands across BOPs. Begin pressure test BOPs (19 of 22 online tests completed). 

10/10/2018: Completed pressure testing BOPs on 5-7/8" DP from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod; using 14.0 ppg CaBr2r. Pressure tested choke manifold and all surface safety valves to 300/10;000 psi for 5 min; pipe rams and associated valves to 300/8;000 psi for 5 min; kelly hose to 300/7;000 psi for 5 min and annulars to 300/4;500 psi for 5 min. Function tested BOPs from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod and from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod. Rig down testing surface line and rack back DD stand. Function test Diverter from Driller's Panel. TIH with 8-1/2" Rock Bit and 9-7/8" Drill Tech Assy from 9;782' to 28.225'. Tag top of fish with 8k down; picked up and broke circulation; re-tagged fish at 28;225 with 8k down. Weight did not wash off. Picked up 2 ft off fish and reversed out 1;300 bbls (2x DP volumes) at 2.8 bpm with 300 psi on WH gauge (fluid within spec). Flow check; spiked pipe and TOH to 24;632' (bottom of tieback gap). 

10/11/2018: Bit Depth 24;629' (tieback gap). R/U SES and reverse out 870 bbls (1.5 DP volumes) at 2.8 bpm with 300 psi (37 NTUs at bottoms up; <.025 solids). TOH from 24;629' to surface. TOI performed planned maintanence on rig floor equiment. Continued PMs while developing final plans and contingencies for fishing operations. ETA of fishing equipment is 07:30 hrs.

10/12/2018: Developing final plans and contingencies for fish recovery operations while performing PMs and housekeeping on rig floor. 

NOTE: On 10/12/2018 at 08:48 hrs; Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) provided Mr. Matt Hensgens (Chevron) with approval to proceed with fishing operations and noted that "in the event this is successful and the RPM is no longer needed; the permit can be revised at that time".

10/13/2018: Developing final plans and contingencies for fish recovery operations while performing PMs and housekeeping on rig floor. 
","WAR_START_DT":"2018-10-07","WELL_NAME":"PS008"},{"   ":318,"API12":608124011606,"TEXT_REMARK":"10/14/2018: Continue finalizing operational plans and loss contingencies for fish recovery operations. Performing PMs; housekeeping on rig floor. Function tested UBSR/LBSR from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod and from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod. 

10/15/2018: Continue finalizing operational plans and loss contingencies for fish recovery operations. Performing PMs; housekeeping on rig floor. Pick up and TIH with 8-1/8" Baker Wash Pipe assembly from surface to 5;696'. Rigged up OES flow back tool. Continued TIH with 8-1/8" Baker Wash Pipe assembly from 5;696' to 15;720'.

10/16/2018: Function tested BOP from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod and from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod. Also function tested BOP using Well Control Button from Driller's Console. Functioned Diverter from Toolpusher's Panel. Diverter closed in 35 sec. Also functioned Diverter from Driller's Console using Diverter Button. TIH with Baker 8-1/8" Wash Pipe assembly from 15;720' to 28;085'. Established baseline parameters. TIH one stand and P/U SES. S/O and tagged TOF at 28;225'. P/U 10 ft and spotted 20 bbls of HEC pill in annulus. Began washing over fish from 28;225' and stalled out at 28;239'. P/U to 10 ft above TOF. Reversed out sweep at 6 bpm. Observed Barablend 657 and Baraflake brought up with HEC sweep. Pumped 20 bbls of HEC sweep down the string and spotted in annulus. Washed over fish from 28;239' to 28;245'.  

10/17/2018: Reversed out sweep at 6 bpm. Observed Barablend 657 and Baraflake brought up with HEC sweep. Pumped 20 bbls of HEC sweep down the string and spotted in annulus. Continue washing/reaming from 28;245' to 28;249'. P/U 10 ft above TOF. Reversed out sweep at 6 bpm. Observed Barablend 657 and Baraflake brought up with HEC sweep. Continue washing/reaming from 28;249' to 28;281'. P/U 10 ft above TOF. Reversed out sweep from surface/surface at 6 bpm. Observed Barablend 657 and Baraflake brought up with HEC sweep. Washed and reamed over fish from 28;281' to top of centralizer on fish at 28;289'.

10/18/2018: Reversed out sweep at 6 bpm with 1;500 psi. Observed small amounts of Barablend 657 and Baraflake. Washed down while rotating and unable to pass over top of fish. P/U and made multiple attempts; with varying parameters; to pass over top of fish with no success. TOH to surface. Observed damage on ocean wave wash over shoe.

10/19/2018: Slipped and cut drill line. P/U and TIH with overshot fishing assembly to 430'. Decision made to recover fish from Wash Over assembly. B/O and L/D overshot fishing assembly. Waited on fishing magnet to arrive. ETA for fishing magnet - 15:00 hrs on 10/20/2018.

10/20/2018: Wait on 8" fishing magnet for BHA; while performing PMs and housekeeping on rig floor. M/U 8" fishing magnet and TIH to 20;939'. 
","WAR_START_DT":"2018-10-14","WELL_NAME":"PS008"},{"   ":319,"API12":608124011606,"TEXT_REMARK":"10/21/2018: TIH with 8" magnet from 20;939' to 28;225'. Tagged top of fish at 28;225' with 6 klbs down. TOH with 8" fishing magnet assembly and recovered metal shavings that did not appear to be from ocean wave shoe. TIH with overshot and fishing assembly to 23;033'.

10/22/2018: TIH with overshot from 23;033' to 28;181'. Took baseline parameters. Made up SES and washed down over top of fish. Observed positive pressure indication as overshot swallowed fish. Shut off pumps and set down 10 klbs down onto fish at 28;236' overshot depth. Picked up to 20 klbs of overpull. Observed overpull fall off - fish free. Continued picking up to next connection with 1-2 klbs of drag. Flow checked well - well static. TOH with overshot and fish to surface. Fish at surface and secured in rotary.

10/23/2018: L/D 93' of TCP fish. All fish recovered. Slip and cut drill line. TIH with Posi-set packer to 7;255'. Function test BOP on 5-7/8" DP from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod and from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod. Function test the Diverter from Driller's Panel. TIH with Posi-Test packer to 28;189'. R/U surface lines and set packer. Opened packer bypass and pumped 92 bbls of DW. Closed packer bypass and performed negative test to 13.3 ppg EMW. 

10/24/2018: Finalize inflow test; reverse out 121 bbls of DW/interface. TOH to 7;166'. M/U double SES and pressure tested BOPs on 5-7/8" DP with 14.0 ppg CaBr2 from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod. Pressure tested surface equipment and safety valves to 300/ 10;000 psi; pipe rams to 300/ 8;000 psi; kelly hose to 300/ 7;000 psi and annulars to 300/4;500 psi for 5 mins. Function tested BOPs from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod and from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod. Function tested BOPs from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod and from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod. Function test Diverter in auto sequence from Toolpusher's Panel. TOH with Posi-Test packer to surface. TIH with mule shoe to 4;186'.

10/25/2018: TIH with 5-7/8" mule shoe to 28;120'. Performed pit management. Closed LAP. Displaced well to 13.3 ppg taking returns up C/K lines holding BHP constant. Monitored well on stripping tank for 30 mins - well static. Displaced riser to 13.3 ppg CaBr2. Opened LAP and flow check well - static.

10/26/2018: Washed down to 28;339' with loss rate increasing to 115 bph. Picked up above perfs and flow checked - static loss rate at ~100 bph. Pumped 50 bbl N-Seal/BaraCarb LCM pill and spot same. Monitored well static. TOH to 27;675'. Staged pumps up to 18 bpm with no losses. TIH to 28;299'. Washed and reamed to 28;415' (21 ft below bottom perf of top interval). While washing; losses gradually increased to 120 bph. TOH to 28;299'. Pumped 50 bbl Barablend/Baracarb LCM pill and spot same. Static loss rate at 42 bph. Pumped 50 bbl Barablend/Baracarb/Baraflake C LCM pill and spot same. Well static. 

10/27/2018: Spot 50 bbls of Barablend 657/Baracarb/Baraflake C pill; No losses recorded with LCM in place. TOH from 28;168' to 27;630'. Circulate B/U; pumping 16 bpm - no losses recorded. Cleaned filter unit and HPDU. Changed out shaker screens. Screened out calcium carbonate LCM at surface and filtered pits. Continued circulating B/U and build Tek-plug. Washed down from 28;343' to 28;586' (top of sump packer). Observed SPP increase while stinging into sump packer. Slacked off 2 ft into sump packer. TOH from 28;595'; at 28;482' observed 70k O/P. Continued to pump out of hole to 28;168'. Flow checked well (loss rate 110 bph). Pumped 50 bbl Tek-plug pill and spot in place. Flow check well on trip tank (initial loss rate at 42 bph; increasing to 67 bph). 

","WAR_START_DT":"2018-10-21","WELL_NAME":"PS008"},{"   ":320,"API12":608124011606,"TEXT_REMARK":"10/28/2018: Spot 50 bbl Tek-Plug; 66 bph static loss rate with Tek-Plug past perfs. Pump 50 bbls of Barablend 657-Baracarb-Baraflake C - LCM pill; 6 bph static loss rate with LCM past perfs. Pump 50 bbl HEC pill; stage pumps to 10 bpm; dynamic loss rate 70 bph/ static loss rate 35 bph. TIH to 28;329'; no fill. Fire reported in galley; shut down and secure well. Pump 50 bbls of Barablend 657-Baracarb-Baraflake C - LCM pill. While displacing pill; wash down to 28;362'; no fill/ no drag observed. Spot pill in place at 28;329' with dynamic loss rate of 150 bph. Monitor well. Initial loss rate 25 bph; with 7 bbls LCM to formation; well static. TOH to 27;793'. Circulate B/U at 10-14 bph with 60 - 0 bph loss rate. Observed formation sand in samples caught between upper and lower perfs. Observed hydrocarbon film; divert 258 bbls contaminated brine.N

Note: On 10/28/2018 at 19:24 hrs; Mr. Bill Sanders (BSEE) provided Mr. Matt Hensgens (Chevron) a 24 hour extension on BSR function testing due to losses.

10/29/2018: Monitor well at 27;810'; well static. TOH with 5-7/8" mule shoe from 27;810' to surface. Slip and cut drill line. Service rig. P/U 4" wash pipe and fluted No-Go assembly. Boost riser and circulate pits across shakers while waiting on 8.3" string stabilizer. Function UBSR/LBSR from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod and from Toolpusher's Panen on Yellow Pod.

Note: BSEE Inspectors Christopher Treland and Clint Campo arrived on ship at 10:00 hrs. Monthly Inspection completed with no INCs. Departed ship at 13:50 hrs.

10/30/2018: Boosted riser at 12 - 15 bpm with no losses while waiting on string mill to arrive on location. P/U 4" wash pipe - Deburr assembly and TIH to 103'. TIH with Deburr assembly to 3;407'. Continue TIH with Deburr assembly to 28;051'. Pump 30 bbl HEC sweep and circulate surface to surface.

On 10/30/2018 at 08:18 hrs; Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) provided Mr. Matt Hensgens (Chevron) a 7 day extension for the requirement to evaluate casing during prolonged operations and a 72 hr BSR pressure test extension due to the risk of performing such a test with unstable formation exposed.

10/31/2018: Function tested BOPs on 5-7/8" DP from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod and from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod. Function tested Diverter on 5-7/8" DP from Driller's Panel. Established circulation and washed down to 28;320' (10 ft above upper perfs). Pumped 30 bbl HEC sweep and circulate from surface to surface. Established circulation and washed down from 28;320' to 28;643'; 48 ft below top of sump packer

11/01/2018: Continue circulating 30 bbl HEC sweeps surface to surface. A total of three 30 bbl sweeps circulated out with increased cuttings load on each sweep. TOH to above upper perforations (28;309') with no drag. Static loss rate 24 bph. TIH with no pump to 28;644' (mule shoe depth); confirming 48 ft of rathole below sump packer. Pump 35 bbl HEC pill and circulate surface to surface. Pump 20 bbl HEC sweep and 70 bbl HEC sweep with 0.25 lb/bbl Barralift and circulate surface to surface.

11/02/2018: Continued circulating surface to surface (20 bbls HEC/ 70 bbls HEC with 0.25 lbs/bbl Barralift). Loss rate at 60-70 bph while circulating. 80% increase in LCM solids once sweep was at surface. Monitored well on TT - static loss rate 25 bph. Landed out No-Go at 28;586' (sump packer); confirming no fill. TOH to 28;286' (above upper perfs) with no drag. Monitored well on TT for 30 mins - 30 bph loss rate. TOH with Deburr assembly to surface. R/U ESTMZ handing equipment. Functioned USBR/LSBR from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod and from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod. Boosted HEC sweep from BOPs to surface. P/U ESTMZ service tool assembly.

Note: On 11/02/2018 at 07:18 hrs ; Mr. Colin Davis (BSEE) approved Mr. JP Yearwood's (Chevron) request for a 48 hour extension on the BSR testing in order to run the completion assembly and provide mechanical isolation of the Wilcox 2 formation; whichever comes first.

11/03/2018: M/U and RIH with Zone #1 - Zone #2 GP Assemblies. Pressure tested Zone #1 - #2 assemblies and isolation packer sleeve integrity to 250 psi/ 5 mins. RIH with ratch-latch retrieval suspension tool on 4-1/2" fishing string (inner string) and retrieved ratch-latch and suspension tool. Pressure tested to 250 psi/ 5 mins to ensure FCS/MCS sleeve integrity. L/D sump test space out pups and performed 2 circulation tests. L/D pups and performed RIH pressure test to 250 psi/5 min. P/U VCH packer and RIH with same. P/U gauge bundle carrier and RIH with ESTMZ assemblies on 5-7/8" DP to 14;285'; average loss rate 25 bph.
","WAR_START_DT":"2018-10-28","WELL_NAME":"PS008"},{"   ":321,"API12":608124011606,"TEXT_REMARK":"11/04/2018: TIH with ESTMZ assembly from 14;285' to 28;266'. Remove excess pipe dope from string. Sting into sump packer at 28;586' IES. Set 20k down mule shoe depth of 28;620' IES; no fill. Average loss rate for trip 27 bph. Overpull 20k to confirm latched into sump packer. Set VCH packer at 28;134' IES. Perform push/pull test; confirming VCH set. Release Heavy Hang Weight Tool (HHWT). Position intermediate seals in Packer Test position and confirm running tool free. Pressure test VCH packer to 1;500 psi for 5 min - good test. In Run position; set Isolation packer at 28;398' IES. Confirm Zone 1 Weight Down Squeeze position. Establish Reverse position. In Reverse position; pump 50 bbl HEC sweep and circulate surface to surface the long way at 15 bpm with no losses. Confirm Weight Down Squeeze position with 1;500 psi down the work string and 500 psi on the back side. Space out and R/U Frac head.

NOTE: DPM = IES + 9 ft.

Note: On 11/04/2018 at 13:25 hours; Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) provided Mr. J.P. Yearwood (Chevron) an additional 48 hour extension for casing evaluation and an additional 96 hour extension for BSR pressure testing.

11/05/2018: R/U Frac head and control lines. Pressure test Frac head and surface lines to 8;000 psi. Reverse out one system volume (1;825 bbls). Pickle workstring and reverse out same. Obtain reverse out parameters through full open choke. L/D primary Frac head; unsuccessful pressure test on upper crown valve. P/U back-up Frac head; unsuccessful pressure test on upper middle and lower plug valves. Rebuild and retest primary Frac head on deck offline. L/D back-up Frac head and P/U original primary Frac head. Pressure test Frac head and surface lines to 14;000 psi - no test. L/D Frac head. Wait on Concentric Frac head; ETA to location 18:00 hours on 11/06.

11/06/2018: Wait on Concentric Frac head to arrive on location.

11/07/2018: Wait on Concentric Frac head to arrive on location. Offload and deck tested Frac head. Staged Frac head to rig floor and made up to string. Rigged up lines to Frac head. Tested Frac head. R/U Frac hose from boat. Line up to pump down DP with MPs. P/U and S/O to open Zone #1 FCS/ MCS. Slacked off to "WDS" position. Confirmed tool position and sleeves open. P/U to Reverse position. Lined up and flushed/filled lines with seawater from Frac boat. Offline; functioned boat pop-off and annulus side pop-off. Frac boat pumped 2x surface line volumes of 10.5 ppg NaBr linear gel to displace SW from lines. Pump acid and displace with 10.5 ppg NaBr. S/O and put tool in WDS position. Bullhead acid into perfs. Shut down and redesigned Frac job. Pump Frac job from Blue Dolphin. Stripped up to Reverse position and reversed out; establishing returns. Increased pump speed to 12 bpm while allowing DPP to level off at ICP (4;600 psi). Continued to maintain CP constant at 2;700 psi as DPP dropped as per schedule. Once 13.3 ppg CaBr observed at surface; swapped to active system; then staged down pumps to 6 bpm maintaining CP/DPP at or above BCP of 1;500 psi. After 792 bbls reveresed out; shut down and lined up pumps on HPDU. Continued reversing out 2 additional DP volumes through HPDU. 

Note: As per Alternative Compliance #9 in the permit: BOP/BSR/Diverter Function Tests and Pressure Test will not be conducted when completion tubulars for Frac Operations are across the BOP. Testing of such BOPE will be conducted once operationally feasible.

11/08/2018: Continued reversing out 2 additional DP volumes through HPDU. Shut down; trapping BCP on the DP and casing. Allowed SITP to stabilize. Stripped up to dump seals and closed MCS. Performed test against system to 500 psi over SITP. Opened LAP and flow checked well - static. Rigged down Frac iron. Laid out Frac head. TOH to 28;428' and made up to TDX (service tool in neutral position). Performed Full System test to 500 psi with the cement unit. TOH 1 stand and slacked off to set ShurMac on lower indicating nipple at Zone 2 with 20k down at 28;378' DPM. Lined up cement unit to pump down the DP. With cement unit; tested seals against MCS on the service tool to 1;500 psi. Rigged up Frac head and iron. Tested to 14;000 psi with Baker frac boat. Performed Zone 2 acid/frac job. Stripped up to Reverse position and reversed out;  establishing returns. Once 13.3 ppg CaBr observed at surface; swapped to active system; then staged down pumps maintaining CP/DPP at or above BCP. Shut down trapping BCP of 1;500 psi on the DP/casing. Strip up to dump seals. Did not see indications of seals dumping. Continued to strip up to close MCS. Applied 500 psi to backside; did not see communication between annulus and DP. Applied 4;500 psi down back side with no reaction on DP observed. Bled off pressure and stripped back down to Reverse position. Lined up pumps on HPDU and continued reversing out. Flow check well on trip tank. Well static. Slacked off with 20k down; isolating MCS from annulus. With annular open; applied 500 psi down DP for 5 mins testing MCS - good test; MCS confirmed closed. Rigged down Frac iron and control lines.

NOTE: On 11/08/2018 at 15:12 hours; Mr. Adriano Garcia (BSEE) provided Mr. Matt Hensgens (Chevron) an additional 72 hour extension for casing evaluation. 

Note: As per Alternative Compliance #9 in the permit: BOP/BSR/Diverter Function Tests and Pressure Test will not be conducted when completion tubulars for Frac Operations are across the BOP. Testing of such BOPE will be conducted once operationally feasible.

11/09/2018: Continued rigging down Frac head and laid down same. TOH to 28;114' (30 ft above VCH packer); closed annular; and performed Full System test to 1;500 psi. Performed pit management for displacement. Displaced well from 13.3 ppg CaBr to 14.0 ppg CaBr. TOH from 28;114' to 6;248' while testing choke and kill manifold offline. Slip and cut drill line. 

Note: As per Alternative Compliance #9 in the permit: BOP/BSR/Diverter Function Tests and Pressure Test will not be conducted when completion tubulars for Frac Operations are across the BOP. Testing of such BOPE will be conducted once operationally feasible.

11/10/2018: With service tool mule shoe at 6;248'; continue with slip and cut drill line; made repairs to BlockTilt cylinder on Main Block. P/U and TIH with ValiTech/MagTech to 6;586'. While pumping slug; swivel packing started leaking. Changed out same to new ceramic style swivel packing and tested. P/U PBL - Jet Sub and TIH from 6;586' to 13;635'. Jet WH/XT/BOPs at 18 bpm and sweep to surface; recoverd ~5 gals of solids. M/U Double Dutch stand and test BOPs; as per IPT test plan; on 5-7/8" DP from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod with 14.0 ppg CaBr2. Surface equipment and  safety valves tested to 250-350/ 10;000 psi; Pipe rams and associated valves tested to 250-350/ 8;000 psi; Annulars to 250-350/ 4;500 psi. 

Note: As per Alternative Compliance #9 in the permit: BOP/BSR/Diverter Function Tests and Pressure Test will not be conducted when completion tubulars for Frac Operations are across the BOP. Testing of such BOPE will be conducted once operationally feasible.
","WAR_START_DT":"2018-11-04","WELL_NAME":"PS008"},{"   ":322,"API12":608124011606,"TEXT_REMARK":"11/11/2018: Continue BOP pressure testing on 5-7/8" DP using 14.0 ppg CaBr2 from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod. Pressure tested surface equipment and safety valves to 250-350 /10;000 psi; pipe rams to 250-350/ 8;000 psi; kelly hose to 250-350/ 7;000 psi and annulars to 250-350/ 4;500 psi for 5 mins. Function tested BOPs on 5-7/8" DP from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod and from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod. Performed Diverter function test in auto sequence from Toolpusher's Panel diverting to Port. Performed Diverter function test from Driller's Chair with Diverter button. Short trip to lay out jet sub and inspect MagTech and ValiTech for fill (3-1/2" of fill); TIH 2 stands and pick up BWTT and Nu-Tech assy. TIH and land out BWTT in XT; released from Nu-Tech tool and TOH 2 stands. Pressure tested UBSR/LBSR to 250-350/ 8;000 psi using 14.0 ppg CaBr2 for 5 min from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod as per IPT test plan. Function tested UBSR/LBSR from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod and from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod. Flushed grease from Choke/Kill manifold. Re-engage Nu-Tech and BWTT. Unseated BWTT from XT. Swept BOP and riser with 50 bbl HEC Hi-Vis at 18 bpm down kill line. TOH to 4;646' (midnight depth).

Note: On 11/11/2018 at 11:47 hours; Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) provided Matt Hensgens(Chevron) with an additional 24 hour extension for casing evaluation and permission to proceed with operations with acoustic system isolated due to system leak.

11/12/2018: Continue TOH from 4;626' to surface; laying down BWTT/Nu-Tech and ESTMZ Service Tool assemblies. Rig up WL and RIH with 60 arm casing caliper to 11;850' WLM and lost comms with the tool. POOH and reestablished comms at 1;200'. Continued POOH to surface; troubleshot and swapped out Baker's crossover to Weatherford's tools. RIH from surface to 28;034' and log up to 10;801'.

Note: On 11/12/2018 at 15:35 hours; Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) provided Matt Hensgens(Chevron) with an additional 24 hour extension for casing evaluation.

11/13/2018: Continue POOH with 60 arm casing caliper evaluation tool. R/D E/L equipment. Performed planned rig maintenance. P/U TCP BHA and TIH to 12;000'.

Note: On 11/13/2018 at 18:48 hrs; Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE) granted approval to proceed with permitted well operations after reviewing casing integrity evaluation results and requested revised permit to reflect a derating of casing due to wear.

11/14/2018: Continue TIH with TCP guns from 12;000' to 28;100'. Tagged lower zone VCH packer at 28;138'. P/U and place TCP guns on depth; R/U surface iron and test. Set packer and apply 500 psi on backside. Perforated upper zones 3; 4 and 5. 
Zone 3 perforations: 28;058' - 28;121' MD (27;416' - 27;476' TVD). 
Zone 4 perforations: 27;762' - 27;913' MD (27;136' - 27;279' TVD). 
Zone 5 perforations: 27;392' - 27;543' MD (26;785' - 26;928' TVD).
Observe initial losses of 12 bph; losses stabilized at 3.2 bph on TT after 30 mins. Reverse out 1-1/2x DP volumes. Flow check well and R/D surface iron. TOH from 28;118 - 24;390'.

11/15/2018: Continue TOH with TCP assembly from 24;390' to 1;287'; L/D TCP assembly from 1;287' to surface; all shots fired. P/U and RIH with CleanWell Deburr assembly from surface to 639'.

11/16/2018: Continue P/U and RIH with Cleanwell Deburr assembly from 619' to 1;048'. TIH with Cleanwell Deburr assembly from 1;048' to 27;362'. Obtain parameters prior to activating eductor head on VacTech. Activate VacTech with 1-3/4" steel ball and wash down through perfs at 8 bpm. Shut down pumps and rotary. Slacked off and tagged no-go on VCH PKR at 28;138' with 20k. P/U 5 ft and circulate bottoms up and until brine was to spec. Shutdown pumps and P/U 1 stand above VCH PKR. Monitored well while letting debris fall - well losing at 1.2 bph.

11/17/2018: TOH from 28;000' to surface with Halliburton Deburr assembly. Rig up to pick up ESTMZ assembly. M/U and RIH with gravel pack service tool assembly on 4" wash pipe. M/U and RIH with Zone #3 assembly. Pressure tested Zone 3 assembly to 250 psi for 5 min to ensure sleeve integrity - good test.
","WAR_START_DT":"2018-11-11","WELL_NAME":"PS008"},{"   ":323,"API12":608124011606,"TEXT_REMARK":"11/18/2018: M/U and RIH with Zone 4 - Zone 5 GP assemblies. Pressure tested Zone 4 and 5 assemblies and isolation packer sleeve integrity to 250 psi for 5 mins. RIH with ratch-latch retrieval suspension tool on 4-1/2" fishing string (inner string) and retrieved ratch-latch and suspension tool. Pressure tested to 250 psi for 5 mins to ensure FCS/MCS sleeve integrity and performed 2 circulation tests. L/D pups and performed RIH pressure test to 250 psi for 5 min. P/U VCH packer and RIH with same. P/U gauge bundle carrier and RIH with ESTMZ assemblies on 5-7/8" DP to 8;614'. Function tested BOP and diverter. RIH with ESTMZ assemblies from 8;614' to 10;917'.

Function tested UBSR/LBSR from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod and from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod. Function tested BOP from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod and from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod. Functioned diverter from Driller's Panel.

11/19/2018: RIH with ESTMZ assemblies from 10;917' to 28;134'. Latched into lower zone VCH packer. Set upper VCH packer at 27;277' IES. Released Heavy Hang Weight Tool from VCH packer. Pressure tested VCH packer to 1;500 psi - good test. Set isolation packers (Zone 4 packer at 27;556' IES and Zone 3 packer at 27;932' IES). Pumped 50 bbl HEC pill down the work string and circulated surface to surface.

11/20/2018: Circulated surface to surface at 15 bpm. Pickled work string; RU frac boat and flush/test lines. Pump 580;804 lbs sand - max rate 35 bpm. Reversed out 15;229 lbs sand. 

Note: BSEE Inspectors Paul Reeves; Clint Campo; Gabe Orellana; Cedric Bernard arrived on ship at 09:00 hrs. Monthly inspection completed with no INCs. Departed ship at 13:00 hrs.

11/21/2018: Continued reversing out DP volume. Dumped seals and closed Zone 3 MCS. Tested MCS integrity. R/D Frac head. Space out service tool in Zone 4. M/U Frac head and lines. Opened MCS and Acidize Zone 4. Performed Main Frac on Zone 4 (pumped 566;766 lbs of sand @ 35 bpm). Strip up to reverse position and circulate 2 DP volumes. Dumped seals and closed Zone 4 MCS. R/D Frac head. Tested MCS integrity. Spaced out service tool in Zone 5 and tested same. M/U Frac head and lines. Obtained P/U and S/O weights and locate WDS position. Closed LAP; applied 500 psi to backside and strip up to reverse position. Broke circulation and filled surface lines.

11/22/2018: Flushed surface lines and pressure tested. Baker Stimulation Vessel Blue Dolphin waiting on inclement weather to pass. Brought in Stimulation Vessel and R/U Frac hose. Calibrated flow meters. P/U and opened MCS (observed 175 bph losses). Positioned tool in Rev position to stop losses. Filled and flushed lines from Frac boat. Pressure tested 4" lines to 14;000 psi. Acidized Zone 5. Performed Main Frac on Zone 5 (pumped 581;537 lbs of sand @ 35 bpm). Strip up to Rev position and circulate 2x DP volumes. Dumped seals and closed MCS. R/D Frac head. TOH to 27;002' and test MCS integrity. TOH to 20;030'.

11/23/2018: TOH with ESTMZ service tool to 1;273'. L/D ESTMZ service tool assemblies to surface (no abnormalities observed). R/D elevators; becket; bails and removed GP handling equipment from RF. Slip and cut drill line. Performed PMs on TDX; drawworks and iron roughneck. P/U and RIH with ESTMZ cleanout 3.5" wash pipe to 1;346'. P/U and RIH with Cleanwell tools to 1;613'. TIH with ESTMZ cleanout assembly on 5-7/8" DP to 9;758'. Functioned UBSR/LBSR from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod and from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod.

11/24/2018: TIH ESTMZ cleanout assembly to 27;113'. Activate VacTech activation ball. Washed down to lower VCH packer. Circulated bottoms up. TOH to 28;188'. Monitored well for 30 mins and allow debris to fall. TIH (no pumps) and landed out on VCH packer - no fill observed. TOH to 25;502'. 
","WAR_START_DT":"2018-11-18","WELL_NAME":"PS008"},{"   ":324,"API12":608124011606,"TEXT_REMARK":"11/25/2018: TOH with ESTMZ cleanout assembly to 23;892'. Pressure tested BOPs on 5-7/8" drill pipe from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod using 14.0 ppg CaBr2. Pressure tested rams to 300/ 8;000 psi; annular to 300/ 4;500 psi and Kelly hose to 300/ 7;000 psi. Function tested BOPs from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod and from Toolpusher's Panel on Yellow Pod. Function tested diverter from Toolpusher's Panel. R/D BOP test stand. TOH to 1;746'. Recovered debris from Cleanwell VacTech chambers.
Note: Choke manifold was pressure tested on 11/24/2018 to 300/ 10;000 psi.

11/26/2018: Recovered debris from CleanWell VacTech chambers. Laid out ESTMZ cleanout 3.5" washpipe. R/U handling equipment. P/U and RIH with HES Isolation assemblies (Zones 1 - 5) to 1;493'. TIH with Isolation assembly to 21;730'.

11/27/2018: TIH with Isolation assembly to 27;170'. TIH opening MJPS and FCS production sleeves across Zones 5 - 1 (max loss rate @ 600 bph). Sting into VCH seal bore at 28;624' (losses stopped). Confirmed latch with 30 klbs overpull. Pressure tested FS-2 and seals in VCH packer seal bore to 1;000 psi. Pumped down 1-7/8" ball and pressured up to 2;500 psi. Bled off and attempted to release from PBR with 30k overpull (no success). Pressured up to 2;500 psi and released from PBR. Obtained new string weights. Slacked off and tagged PBR at 27;146' with 10k. Closed MVBR to mark pipe. Pumped slug and TOH to surface. Slip and cut drill line. Performed planned rig maintenance. R/U handling gear. 

11/28/2018: P/U TNT packer and PBR assembly to 339'. R/D WFD handling equipment. TIH with TNT packer assembly to 26;706'. Locate tool joint and TIH 2 stands. Land out PFZ anchor latch by setting 30k down at 27;160' DPM (mule shoe depth). Confirm latch with 30k overpull and performed 1;000 psi "feel good" test. Set TNT permanent packer at 26;951' (IES). P/U 30 ft and S/O setting 10k down on PBR. Closed MVBRs and pressure tested TNT packer to 5;000 psi for 5 mins with 14.0 ppg CaBr2 (WSEA 10-E). Bled off pressure; opened MVBRs and TOH to 23;331'. 

11/29/2018: TOH with Halliburton TNT Packer running tool/ wash pipe from 23;331' to surface. P/U BOP jetting assembly and TIH to 7;342' (bit depth). Jet BOP with Tornar tool. Pump 50 bbl HEC sweep and circulate B/U. TOH with jetting assmeblies to 333'.

11/30/2018: L/D BOP jetting assembly. No debris recovered in Vali Tech; 3.5 lbs wet metal fines recovered on Mag Tech. Function test UBSRs/LBSRs from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod and from Toolpusher's Panel on Blue Pod. Function test CSRs from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod. TIH with BOPTT/Jetting assembly. Pressure test BOPs on 5-7/8" DP from Driller's Panel on Blue Pod; using 14.0 ppg CaBr2. Pressure tested rams and associated valves to 300/ 8;000 psi; annular to 300/ 4;500 psi. Choke manifold and all surface safety valves tested to 300/ 10;000 psi. Function tested BOP from Driller's Panel on Yellow Pod and from Toolpushers's Panel on Blue Pod. Function tested diverter from Driller's Panel. Jet BOP. Retrieved bore protector with 22k overpull. TOH hole with BPRRT to 7;345'. With Jet sub at 7;032'; jetted TH profile. Pumped 50 bbl HEC sweep and circulate out of hole. TOH with BPRRT on 5-7/8" drill pipe to 593'.

12/01/2018: TOH from 593' to surface. Laid out assemblies and inspected 10-3/4" ValiTech/ Bore Protector. Riser ValiTech = 1.5 lbs of LCM MagTech = 2.6 lbs (wet metal fines). 10-3/4" ValiTech = 0.75 lbs of LCM. TIH with 17.8" NuTec centralizer from surface to 7;030'. No obstruction observed while running/pulling 17.8" NuTec through BOPs. TOH to surface. Slip and cut drill line. R/U and run production tubing to 787'.
","WAR_START_DT":"2018-11-25","WELL_NAME":"PS008"},{"   ":325,"API12":608124011606,"TEXT_REMARK":"12/02/2018: RIH in stands with 4-1/2" 17 ppf Vam Top tubing from 787' to 15;289'. Drifted tubing from derrick with 3.615" drift. M/U tubing to 8;500 ft-lbs. Installed cross-coupling control line protector/clamps across every connection.

12/03/2018: TIH with production tubing from 15;289' to 17;433'. M/U pups; timed pup and SCSSV to string. Terminated and tested SCSSV control lines. RIH with remaining 4-1/2" tubing and 6" VIT. M/U tubing hanger. R/D WFD handling gear prepare to terminate lines. 

12/04/2018: Took P/U and S/O. Function tested SCSSV valves 3x. Took Well Dynamics gauge readings. Lowered Helix and positioned tubing for contol line termination. Rough cut control lines and passed thru Helix. Performed control line terminations and testing as per plan. TIH with upper completion on 7-5/8" MaXit landing string from 19;873' to 26;808'. Make up soft land stand and land tubing hanger at 26;908' (63' seal engagement) and applied 45k down(200 psi increase on soft land). Pick up and position hanger above BOP. 

12/05/2018: Spot 14.0 ppg CaBr2 inhibited packer fluid in tubing x casing annulus. Broke out soft landing stand. Rigged up CTLF and associated equipment. Picked up SFT and made up to LS. Get on CMC PHC (mid stroke). Installed torpedo packers. Land and lock tubing hanger. R/U HPDU and surface iron. R/U PXF hydraulic lines and function valves. Pressure tested tubing hanger upper seals (12;600 psia); SCSSV1 and SCSSV2 control lines (12;600 psia); gallery seal (12;600 psia); production bore (12;600 psia); casing x tubing annulus (5;000 psi). Engage and test electrical penetrators. Repeated gallery seal test. R/U slickline lubricator. 

12/06/2018: Continued R/U slickline lubricator. Pressure tested SFT and lubricator (10;000 psi). Pressure tested landing string; SFT body and production tubing (4;500 psi). Negative tested SCSSV (4;800 psi). 

12/07/2018: RIH and set with Lower Crown Plug. POOH with slickline to surface. Tested below LCP (7;400 psi differential) down kill line from cement unit with base oil. Make up; RIH and set UCP. POOH with slickline to surface. Perform pressure test between LCP and UCP via IWOCS (12;600 psia). Rigged down lubricator while cycling FS2 valve. Bullhead base oil and negative test SCSSV. 

BSEE Inspectors Gabe Orellana; Joshua Naquin; Chris Trelano; and Troy Boudreaux arrived at the Deepwater Conqueror on 12/7/2018; at 9:00 am. No INC's were issued and the inspectors departed the ship at 13:45 hrs.

12/08/2018: Sent in results of negative test on SCSSV for approval. Pumped base oil through the flow head and down the landing string. Pressure tested top of upper crown plug with cementer (12;600 psia). Displaced the kill line with 240 bbls of seawater. Prepared to unlatch THRT. Unlatched THRT and continued to displace with SW for 2x landing string volumes. Spiked LS and rigged down all surface lines on rig floor. Removed torpedo packers from landing string. Laid out SFT and CTLF. Rigged up landing string handling equipment. TOH with L&L on 7-5/8" LS. 

Note: As per Alternative Compliance #9 in the permit: Function and pressure tests on the BOP (including VBRs; BSRs; and annulars) and diverter will not be conducted when procedures require having completion tubulars across the stack. Specific instances include L&L is installed and locked with the tubing hanger landed.
","WAR_START_DT":"2018-12-02","WELL_NAME":"PS008"},{"   ":326,"API12":608124011606,"TEXT_REMARK":"12/09/2018: Rigged down tubing running equipment and cleaned rig floor. Performed diverter operator test. Back-spool expro umbilical through sheaves. Rig up riser running equipment. Rigged up riser handling equipment. Picked up diverter running tool. Laid out diverter and running tool. Made up landing joint to slip joint. Unlatched BOP/LMRP at 14:58 hrs. Move to DOZ. Remove drape hoses and storm loops. Lay out slip joint. Rig up riser turning device. 

12/10/2018: Crane crew continued to rig up riser turning devise on yoke and spreader beam while installing riser tilt cylinder on Main TDX. Pulled BOP/LMRP on marine riser from 6;884' to 6;509'. Deck crew replaced secondary retention on yoke. Continued pulling BOP/LMRP on marine riser from 6;509' to 3;509'. Held TOFS on rig floor to re-inspected riser handling equipment while crane crew recalibrated riser gantry crane (lost sync). Continued pulling BOP/LMRP on marine riser from 3;509' to surface. BOP on beams at 19:45 hrs. Lay out double and rig down riser running equipment.

12/11/2018: MSV Harvey Deep Sea installed tertiary tree cap and filled with Transaqua.
","WAR_START_DT":"2018-12-09","WELL_NAME":"PS008"}]
